(100, 38, 43, 40, '2021-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Mallory is \"overworked and underpaid\", she did not let that stop her from being totally driven to understand the factoring of polynomials.  It is very inspiring to watch as Mallory comes up with solutions by applying concepts that are new to her. Not only that, but when obstructed by a \"road block\" to comprehension, Mallory just reprograms her mental GPS and comes up with a \"new route\"!  My only concern is that there may be \"road hazards\" if that route goes through her room, which Mallory readily admitted requires attention  I am confident that the one-woman \"Mallory road crew\" will take the necessary steps to \"make necessary repairs\", and thereby remove her room from \"Caution: Construction Ahead\" status!  :)', '50', '2021-01-14 14:33:59', '2021-01-14 14:33:59'),
(101, 42, 44, 43, '2021-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I worked on more writing responses to different stories from mythology. His spelling is improving but still struggles to spell accurately, consistently. His reading fluency is hugely improved and his comprehension remains excellent.', '45', '2021-01-14 18:58:48', '2021-01-14 18:58:48'),
(102, 42, 48, 49, '2021-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked on multi-step addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division problems. She is absolutely excelling with addition and subtraction and is getting increasingly comfortable with division and multiplication. She occasionally switches around numbers and operations, so we will focus on getting her to slow down and double-check her work.', '45', '2021-01-14 19:01:34', '2021-01-14 19:01:34'),
(103, 42, 46, 47, '2021-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I dipped briefly back into our discussion of Julius Caesar, connecting the events of the play to recent current events. We then moved into a discussion of Much Ado About Nothing, focusing on character dynamics, different styles of comedic writing, and the use of prose vs. verse through the first three acts.', '45', '2021-01-14 19:04:14', '2021-01-14 19:04:14'),
(104, 45, 45, 46, '2021-01-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Learned the types of nouns: singular, plural, concrete, abstract, proper, common, possessive. Practiced identifying nouns in sentences. Reviewed differentiating the different types. Began learning about verbs and focused on action verbs. Next time: linking & helping verbs. Learned how to identify subject and verb in sentences.', '50', '2021-01-14 23:32:51', '2021-01-14 23:32:51'),
