(118, 60, 60, 62, '2021-01-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Went through Canvas and looked at unsubmitted Language Arts assignments. Worked through the 11/20 Independent Reading Letter and started working on the Creative Writing assignment. Set a plan for the rest of the week to finish all the remaining assignments in order to get caught up.', '20', '2021-01-21 01:33:28', '2021-01-21 01:33:28'),
(119, 38, 43, 40, '2021-01-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In what could have been our next to last lesson :( , Mallory and I worked industriously on graphing parabolas.  From vertices to x-intercepts, from orientation to y-intercepts, we covered the gamut of parabola graphing concepts, and Mallory surfaced form the ordeal entirely unscathed.  As part of the session, we reviewed factoring methodology, which  was extremely helpful in solving for the intercepts. The highlight of the session, however, was Mallory\'s status report on her room cleaning project - she made significant progress in finding her carpet again :).  Way to go Mallory!', '50', '2021-01-21 14:27:40', '2021-01-21 14:27:40'),
(120, 45, 45, 46, '2021-01-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Warm-Up: Part of Speech Sort using Nouns, Verbs and Adjectives. Brendon came up with sentences for each and we discussed how the same words can be used in different ways (ex: \"blue\" can be a noun or adjective, depending on how it is functioning in the sentence). Next, worked through Grammar Gorilla game to identify various parts of speech of words in sentences. In the Part of Speech slides, we reviewed nouns, verbs & adjectives and learned adverb. Review the difference between adverb and adjective next week.', '50', '2021-01-21 23:33:27', '2021-01-21 23:33:27'),
