(137, 45, 45, 46, '2021-01-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Warm-Up: Review adjectives & adverbs. Took notes on differences and questions each answers. Practiced using various Mad Lib stories. Reviewed differences of Adverb & Adjectives using Kahoot: https://create.kahoot.it/details/adjective-vs-adverb/042d18b1-17b7-4708-a2b5-b34ce739e732 Finish next week. Keep practicing with the differences.', '50', '2021-01-28 23:33:26', '2021-01-28 23:33:26'),
(138, 38, 43, 40, '2021-01-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'This session for Mallory was scheduled for Wednesday, but due to my own family issue, Mallory was kind enough to reschedule for today.  The change in time had effect no Mallory\'s great attitude and desire to advance.  We reviewed an assignment on the quadratic formula that Mallory was not able to hand in during the semester (see what I mean about her thirst for learning!), and of course, she did great!  She even wants to continue our sessions beyond the semester, and made her own executive decision about what we will cover. Thank you Mallory - I will be reporting for duty when and where you tell me! (Hey boss -  Can I get a new pencil sharpener?)  My sadness about what I thought was the end of our sessions has been transformed into jubilation over their continuation!  Yes, I DO enjoy working with Mallory.', '50', '2021-01-29 13:53:30', '2021-01-31 15:42:10'),
(139, 34, 58, 59, '2021-01-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Tested retention by looking at problems we looked at a few days before. Retention was low, but I suspect Addi is not processing the questions rather than forgetting the answers.', '70', '2021-01-30 21:10:13', '2021-01-30 21:10:13'),
(140, 34, 45, 46, '2021-01-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Played KenKen', '75', '2021-01-30 21:10:27', '2021-01-30 21:10:27'),
(141, 42, 48, 49, '2021-01-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena continued to work on division and multiplication in class, focusing on multiples of 10. She\'s continuing to do well in this area.', '45', '2021-01-31 16:06:02', '2021-01-31 16:06:02'),
(142, 42, 59, 61, '2021-01-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Jackson and I discussed his struggles with online school and came up with a plan to \"triage\" his schoolwork going forward, focusing on the assignments with the most weight and spreading out his work over the week.', '45', '2021-01-31 16:08:44', '2021-01-31 16:08:44'),
(143, 42, 44, 43, '2021-01-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I continued to read through our mythology book, breaking down words he found difficult. We\'re going to move on to the Percy Jackson series after and I am planning to build in writing assignments around the book.', '45', '2021-01-31 16:11:15', '2021-01-31 16:11:15'),
(144, 42, 46, 47, '2021-01-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I discussed a recent stage adaptation of Much Ado About Nothing, analyzing the director\'s choices in how they related to the text. We are going to read Jhumpa Lahiri\'s \"The Interpreter of Maladies\" next, so we discussed the history of Indian-American/Bengali culture and writing and Jhumpa Lahiri\'s background as a writer.', '45', '2021-01-31 16:14:05', '2021-01-31 16:14:05'),
(145, 42, 48, 49, '2021-01-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I continued to work on rounding numbers to the nearest 10 and 100. We played a dice/tic tac toe hybrid game and that helped solidify the concept', '45', '2021-01-31 16:18:44', '2021-01-31 16:18:44'),
