(156, 38, 57, 58, '2021-02-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was true pleasure to meet Ivanna today to help her with some of her second grade math units.  This young lady was a true gem, so animated and engaged.   After my feeble attempt to say \"good morning\" to Ivanna in Russian, she immediately took over, explaining to me what she needed assistance with (visual models, stretch and stack, number line math), how to help her, and what I needed to know to be able to assist.  I certainly appreciated her support, and together, we successfully navigated two of the three problem areas.  Ivanna was there when I needed her with technical issues as well, as I ran into some \"share screen\" issues that she attempted to troubleshoot for me.  I cannot express enough how impressed I was with Ivanna\'s maturity, magnetic personality, and stellar character traits.  Her math skills are solid, and I see my role as one of strengthening and review.  We will address the third area of concern at our next session. I look forward to working with this gifted young student!', '50', '2021-02-08 00:23:50', '2021-02-08 00:25:10'),
(157, 42, 59, 61, '2021-02-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Jackson and I organized his work for his first full week of the new quarter and prioritized his assignments. We then worked on his introductory powerpoint for his history class.', '45', '2021-02-09 15:19:43', '2021-02-09 15:19:43'),
(158, 42, 61, 63, '2021-02-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Adith and I worked on sequencing and basic addition skills through a puzzle. He struggled with focus and could only really do one or two questions in a row before needing a break.', '45', '2021-02-09 15:24:53', '2021-02-09 15:24:53'),
(159, 42, 48, 49, '2021-02-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I finished up our work on rounding numbers and continued to practice with multiplication and division. We will continue to reinforce those skills while branching out into some work on geometry. She continues to grow in confidence, even with more challenging problems.', '45', '2021-02-09 15:26:38', '2021-02-09 15:26:38'),
(160, 42, 46, 47, '2021-02-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I began our discussion of Jhumpa Lahiri\'s \"The Interpreter of Maladies.\" After finishing the book, we are planning on writing a research-based literary analysis paper. As a jumpstart, we looked at scholarly sources and literary reviews of Lahiri\'s work, briefly discussing how they could be incorporated in a literary paper.', '45', '2021-02-09 15:32:23', '2021-02-09 15:32:23'),
