(179, 60, 60, 62, '2021-02-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Over Zoom. Started working on IDR letter, and let Olivia do most of the prewriting process instead of guiding her  through it since we had already done numerous IDR letters together. Checked Canvas for late assignments and made sure they were completed and would be submitted through the chrome book after the session. Sent an email to Olivia\'s art teacher, letting her know that one of the over due assignments was left at home and would be submitted once Olivia returns back to Maryland.', '20', '2021-02-17 19:32:50', '2021-02-17 19:32:50'),
(180, 38, 43, 40, '2021-02-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mallory and I wrapped up our tutoring engagement (at least temporarily), as her class has ended and she will not be taking any additional math until the fall.  We experimented in this last session with an introduction to geometry as a preparation for what is to come, but Mallory felt that that without the demands and structure of a class, she would not derive maximum benefit from such an approach at this time. That is certainly understandable.  A follow-up email from Mom indicated that she would monitor the situation and be in touch if the need arises. It was a pleasure to work with Mallory.  I look forward to hearing of her successes in the future - and I know there will be many!', '50', '2021-02-18 15:29:29', '2021-02-18 15:29:29'),
(181, 42, 59, 61, '2021-02-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Jackson didn\'t have much in the way of schoolwork, but has a timed, in-class essay coming up shortly so we discussed strategies for writing timed essays. We also went over some of his history notes, reinforcing concepts he was struggling to understand.', '45', '2021-02-18 22:52:01', '2021-02-18 22:52:01'),
(182, 42, 44, 43, '2021-02-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam had a writing assignment for class to do this week, so we brainstormed ideas for his paragraph together before. Sam then wrote his rough draft which we reviewed together for spelling and grammar. His spelling is hugely improved, only making a few mistakes here and there.', '45', '2021-02-18 22:55:46', '2021-02-18 22:55:46'),
(183, 42, 46, 47, '2021-02-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I finished up our discussion of \"The Interpreter of Maladies\" before moving on to discuss how to find reliable sources of literary criticism. Next week, we plan to discuss thesis statements and the beginnings of crafting an outline.', '45', '2021-02-18 23:03:37', '2021-02-18 23:03:37'),
