(401, 38, 74, 71, '2021-05-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although the work we are doing increases in complexity with each lesson, Timur is not in the least bit rattled. In fact, he is teaching me a lot about being calm, cool, and collected!  We advanced to translating word problems into the functions they represent, and Timur seemed to pick up this skill fairly quickly. He was still struggling a bit with actually solving algebraic equations, so we struck a deal to practice from a worksheet of 20 problems (he dealt me down from the original 300 to 400 I wanted to assign him :) ).  He continues to amaze me with his quiet genius,  And let me take this opportunity to send out kudos to Timur\'s trusty assistant, his Mom, who does an excellent job of holding the headphones throughout the entire session!  What a team!', '50', '2021-05-27 14:02:51', '2021-05-27 14:02:51'),
(402, 42, 44, 43, '2021-05-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I worked on a school writing assignment. His spelling is much improved and he is starting to excel at creative writing.', '45', '2021-05-27 18:11:50', '2021-05-27 18:11:50'),
(403, 42, 46, 47, '2021-05-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I reviewed her essay on Interpreter of Maladies, focusing on her body paragraphs. We\'re going to start looking at The Joy Luck Club next and are going to focus on covering classic high school texts she doesn\'t seem to be touching at school.', '45', '2021-05-27 18:14:22', '2021-05-27 18:14:22'),
(404, 42, 44, 43, '2021-05-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam had another writing assignment to work on this week: an opinion piece on year-round school. We worked on brainstorming, pre-writing, and covered the structure of an opinion paragraph. Sam is writing long paragraphs and is even writing for fun in his spare time.', '45', '2021-05-27 18:16:56', '2021-05-27 18:16:56'),
(405, 42, 48, 49, '2021-05-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I reviewed some addition and subtraction before reviewing basic fraction concepts. I introduced adding fractions with shared denominators which went surprisingly well. We did some review on multiplication, which is still a challenge for Leena, especially when she gets to the 6-9 times table.', '45', '2021-05-27 18:50:27', '2021-05-27 18:50:27'),
(406, 42, 46, 47, '2021-05-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I reviewed her progress on her Interpreter of Maladies essay, addressing issues with passive voice, tweaking phrasing and style, and deepening her analysis. We also brainstormed a book list for the summer, focusing on classic texts she didn\'t touch this past school year.', '45', '2021-05-27 18:52:26', '2021-05-27 18:52:26'),
