(426, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked through some simple addition and subtraction worksheets. Completed three pages in the second grade Star Wars book. Realized that he did not know all of the months of the year in order so went through them a couple of times.', '20', '2021-06-04 22:20:04', '2021-06-04 22:20:04'),
(427, 38, 74, 71, '2021-06-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although our access to Timur\'s resource materials is not as open as we would prefer, we continue to do the best we can as we wade our way through sentence fragments, obstructed views, and incomplete presentations. Timur and I maintain a totally positive attitude, and today, we applied that upbeat approach to extracting functional expressions from word problems.  It was a bit of a jump from the previous material, but it was only our first exposure to it, so we know we will only get better during our second encounter.  The syllabus showed that we are scheduled for a review at our next session, so I assigned it to Timur as his homework.  I am confident that he will do just fine with it, and will be ready to continue building on his past successes. Timur is amazing!', '50', '2021-06-07 16:06:43', '2021-06-07 16:07:52'),
(428, 42, 44, 43, '2021-06-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam had another writing assignment for school. We continued to work with the pre-writing method and Sam managed to finish the assignment quickly and with excellent accuracy. Going forward into the summer, we\'re also going to look at some math preparation for fourth grade.', '45', '2021-06-09 01:30:50', '2021-06-09 01:30:50'),
(429, 42, 48, 49, '2021-06-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I continued to work on basic fractions concepts and I noticed there\'s been a bit of backsliding in her addition and subtraction skills, so we\'re going to focus on those skills for the time being.', '45', '2021-06-09 01:32:07', '2021-06-09 01:32:07'),
(430, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on two pages of 2nd Grade Language Arts book and 1 page of 2nd Grade Math book. For Language Arts talked about complete sentences and naming phrases. For math worked on identifying which numbers are greatest/least. Finished with basic addition flash cards.', '20', '2021-06-10 06:13:11', '2021-06-10 06:13:11'),
(431, 41, 47, 48, '2021-06-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'SAT math practice', '45', '2021-06-10 13:37:16', '2021-06-10 13:37:16'),
(432, 38, 74, 71, '2021-06-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I delved deeper into the world of functions today, focusing mainly on identifying and expressing mathematically domains and ranges.  Timur quickly acquired the necessary skills to accomplish this assignment, and demonstrated that proficiency through several practice problems. In fact, I was so confident in his abilities that I ended that part of the lesson early.  As we only had a few minutes left at that point, I suggested we go over the review I had assigned to Timur. Although he had not completed it, Timur promised to have it ready for our next lesson. I made sure to emphasize the importance of strong quantitative foundations before moving on to more advanced work. Timur is a pleasure to work with!', '50', '2021-06-10 14:19:34', '2021-06-10 14:19:34'),
(433, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Did two pages of the new Spectrum Language Arts book and focused on nouns. Started one page of Spectrum math book with a pretest of even and odd numbers.', '20', '2021-06-11 18:43:39', '2021-06-11 18:43:39'),
(434, 42, 48, 49, '2021-06-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I continued to practice with fractions and refreshed her multiplication skills. She continues to need to refresh her addition and subtraction skills and needs to embrace more strategies beyond mental math.', '45', '2021-06-13 17:44:04', '2021-06-13 17:44:04'),
(435, 42, 44, 43, '2021-06-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I got back into the swing of reading the Asterix books. He\'s starting to find it easier to journal and respond to stories in writing.', '45', '2021-06-13 17:45:51', '2021-06-13 17:45:51'),
(436, 38, 74, 71, '2021-06-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur was \"on his game\" today.  He had completed the review sheet as I requested, and we only needed to go over a couple of confusing problems.,  Then we tackled identification and description of domains and ranges, and Timur mastered that skill with no trouble at all.  We are building a math whiz here, and our progress is faster than I could have imagined.  I enjoy immensely watching Timur grow in his skills and confidence!', '50', '2021-06-14 15:25:50', '2021-06-14 15:25:50'),
(437, 74, 79, 76, '2021-06-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, I worked with Muskan on addition and subtraction. I found that Muskan understand addition quite well, especially with the help of physical objects to count, but struggles more with subtraction. Therefore, I assigned homework with both addition and subtraction and will focus more on subtraction during the next session.', '35', '2021-06-15 00:02:08', '2021-06-15 00:02:08');
INSERT INTO `timesheets` (`timesheet_id`, `tutor_id`, `student_id`, `user_id`, `date`, `time`, `duration`, `duration2`, `description`, `hourly_pay_rate`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(438, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'More practice with even and odd numbers. Completed one worksheet counting by 2s, 5s, and 10s, and talked about pennies, nickels, and dimes. Reviewed nouns and talked about common nouns and proper nouns.', '20', '2021-06-15 12:59:56', '2021-06-15 12:59:56'),
(439, 34, 45, 46, '2021-06-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sequences, arithmetic, geometric, recursive, Fibonacci', '75', '2021-06-15 16:08:12', '2021-06-15 16:08:12'),
(440, 34, 46, 47, '2021-06-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Hyperbolas equations and finding foci. Reviewed algebra concepts in this context, like dividing a fraction by a fraction, simplifying radicals, irrational numbers, etc.', '70', '2021-06-15 16:09:01', '2021-06-15 16:09:01'),
(441, 34, 45, 46, '2021-06-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Fibonacci sequence and golden ratio.', '75', '2021-06-17 15:04:43', '2021-06-17 15:04:43'),
(442, 38, 74, 71, '2021-06-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Word problems were the order of the day today, as Timur and I learned the art of translating words into quantitative expressions.  Our framework was that of literal equations, and the module wanted us to take a specific approach to setting them up. My \"thinking\" student Timur and I decided we liked another approach, which worked more efficiently.  Timur has so many talents - I am enjoying my treasure hunt in each session to see what I can discover in this gifted young man!  Although Timur still continues to wrestle a bit with actually solving equations, I am optimistic that he is on an upward trend towards mastery of that skill.  Good work Timur!', '50', '2021-06-17 15:41:54', '2021-06-17 15:41:54'),
(443, 45, 45, 46, '2021-06-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Student was 30 min late. Grammar review of contractions and active vs passive voice.', '50', '2021-06-17 22:32:16', '2021-06-17 22:32:16'),
(444, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced addition and subtraction in Spectrum book. Practiced counting by 2s, 3s, and 5s. Reviewed common and proper nouns.', '20', '2021-06-18 14:18:22', '2021-06-18 14:18:22'),
(445, 38, 74, 71, '2021-06-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'This evening\'s session with Timur was a true gem!  Timur was fully engaged, confident and flawless in his performance, coming away away as a true expert in the slope intercept form of the equation of a line. I was so impressed, and I look forward to more of the same when I return from my surgery.  Timur\'s growth is exponential! He has made me one proud tutor.  Way to go Timur!', '50', '2021-06-22 01:34:35', '2021-06-22 01:35:32'),
(446, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed addition and subtraction homework and completed another subtraction worksheet. Talked about pronouns and reflexive pronouns.', '20', '2021-06-22 14:54:37', '2021-06-22 14:54:37'),
(447, 34, 45, 46, '2021-06-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Exponents. Played NIM - logic game.', '75', '2021-06-22 15:12:36', '2021-06-22 15:12:36'),
(448, 74, 79, 76, '2021-06-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, I worked with Muskan on subtraction and place values. I noticed during the last session that she had difficulty saying three and four digit numbers out loud. We worked together on saying numbers out loud as well as doing subtraction with double digit numbers.', '35', '2021-06-24 00:55:25', '2021-06-24 00:55:25'),
(449, 34, 39, 35, '2021-06-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Played logic puzzles and NIM with Emma and Nick.', '70', '2021-06-24 14:58:06', '2021-06-24 14:58:06'),
(450, 34, 76, 73, '2021-06-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Geometric, arithmetic, and recursive sequence. Fibonacci sequence.', '70', '2021-06-25 00:04:36', '2021-06-25 00:04:36'),
(451, 34, 77, 73, '2021-06-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addition and subtraction up to 10. Word problems.', '70', '2021-06-25 00:05:05', '2021-06-25 00:05:05'),
(452, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Review of common nouns, proper nouns, pronouns, and reflexive pronouns. Started talking about verbs.', '20', '2021-06-25 15:31:19', '2021-06-25 15:31:19'),
(453, 38, 74, 71, '2021-06-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I were forced to improvise today... and we did wonderfully.  It seems that with the end of the school year came the closing down of the website we needed to review his work.  So after we put our heads together and received an excellent recommendation from Mom, we realized that we still had the homework I had assigned Timur from our last session. This module on the slope intercept formula of a line was a perfect way to continue the great momentum that we had established in previous sessions. Timur did great, I marveled at his performance, and Mom was proved right again!  Mom will do what is necessary to get access to Timur\'s syllabus from the school year so that we can continue to let Timur excel.  I hope Timur will forgive me for my \"zero joke production\", as I think the discomfort form my recovery from surgery took its toll on my humorous side.  Thank you Timur!  You are doing great!', '50', '2021-06-28 21:41:39', '2021-06-28 21:43:10'),
(454, 60, 75, 72, '2021-06-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed adding two digit numbers without having to carry over. Reviewed nouns and verbs.', '20', '2021-06-29 13:37:14', '2021-06-29 13:37:14'),
(455, 34, 45, 46, '2021-06-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'powers of fractions. KenKen logic puzzles.', '75', '2021-06-29 15:02:26', '2021-06-29 15:02:26'),
(456, 42, 44, 43, '2021-06-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I continued to work through \"Asterix and the Goths\" and played a few math games. His math skills are strong, though he needs to practice his times tables to get stronger.', '45', '2021-06-30 02:46:51', '2021-06-30 02:46:51'),
(457, 42, 44, 43, '2021-06-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I finished Asterix and the Goths and played \"Multiplication War\" to help build fluency with his multiplication tables.', '45', '2021-06-30 02:47:41', '2021-06-30 02:47:41'),
(458, 42, 46, 47, '2021-06-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I began our discussion of The Joy Luck Club, first digging into Amy Tan\'s life story, before discussing the historical context of the novel.', '45', '2021-06-30 02:50:06', '2021-06-30 02:50:06'),
(459, 42, 58, 59, '2021-06-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I spent this session getting to know Addie and discussing her interests. I assessed her reading, having her read aloud from \"Wonder\" and pausing to discuss after each major chapter.', '45', '2021-06-30 02:51:50', '2021-06-30 02:51:50'),
(460, 42, 80, 59, '2021-06-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmy and I got to know each other and discussed her interests and goals. I listened to her read aloud and we discussed her summer reading book \"The Wild Robot.\"', '45', '2021-06-30 02:52:57', '2021-06-30 02:52:57'),
(461, 42, 48, 49, '2021-06-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked on building up her addition and subtraction skills. She\'s still struggling with more complex problems and needs consistent practice to continue improving.', '45', '2021-06-30 02:55:31', '2021-06-30 02:55:31'),
(462, 42, 46, 47, '2021-06-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I discussed the first four chapters of The Joy Luck Club, focusing on how memory operates through the book and the way the female characters fight the patriarchal forces within the novel.', '45', '2021-06-30 02:57:53', '2021-06-30 02:57:53'),
(463, 34, 46, 47, '2021-06-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Began working through Algebra 1 summer packet.', '70', '2021-06-30 16:13:11', '2021-06-30 16:13:11'),
(465, 34, 39, 35, '2021-06-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'KenKen at various levels of difficulty. Will play again next time, by kids\' request.', '70', '2021-07-01 00:25:16', '2021-07-01 00:25:16'),
(466, 42, 58, 59, '2021-06-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addison and I continued to read Wonder together and also began reading \"We Were There Too,\" a chronicle of children through history.', '45', '2021-07-01 05:04:25', '2021-07-01 05:04:25'),
(467, 42, 80, 59, '2021-06-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmy and I continued reading the Wild Robot, working on identifying vocabulary using context clues.', '45', '2021-07-01 05:05:31', '2021-07-01 05:05:31'),
(468, 60, 73, 67, '2021-06-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on basic addition and subtraction and talked about what happens when you add/subtract zero or when you subtract a number from itself. Looked at pictures in order to write a story and talked about spelling.', '20', '2021-07-01 10:59:17', '2021-07-01 10:59:17'),
(469, 38, 74, 71, '2021-06-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Despite the bad news that we would not be able to access the course material from the completed school year, Mom came through with some other great resources, which Timur and I made great use of today to keep alive the strengthening process.  We took a step back to review some more fundamental number and algebra concepts, but  this change of direction also involved more consistent and active participation from Timur along the way.  Timur just put his head down, went to work, and showed how strong his skills actually are.  I am looking forward to continuing with this book and watch Timur shine!', '50', '2021-07-01 13:53:34', '2021-07-01 13:54:07'),
(470, 34, 77, 73, '2021-07-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addition and subtraction practice, subtracting the same number from itself, subtracting a number that is one less, playing NIM logic game, addition and subtraction word problems.', '70', '2021-07-02 00:07:13', '2021-07-02 00:07:13'),
(471, 34, 76, 73, '2021-07-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Playing NIM logic game, visual reasoning practice with lines of symmetry and sunflower spirals. Assigned homework to divide shapes into equal parts.', '70', '2021-07-02 00:08:04', '2021-07-02 00:08:04'),
(472, 60, 75, 72, '2021-07-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Went over addition of two two digit numbers with no regrouping. Spent a long time reviewing nouns for a quiz next week.', '20', '2021-07-02 01:32:36', '2021-07-02 01:32:36'),
(473, 34, 46, 47, '2021-07-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Summer packet: slopes, lines, graphing, functions.', '70', '2021-07-06 16:11:25', '2021-07-06 16:11:25'),
(474, 60, 75, 72, '2021-07-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Took quiz on common nouns, proper nouns, pronouns, and reflexive pronouns. Reviewed two digit subtraction without regrouping and adding three 2-digit numbers without regrouping.', '20', '2021-07-07 15:22:51', '2021-07-07 15:22:51'),
(475, 34, 39, 35, '2021-07-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Math games - KenKen 5x5', '70', '2021-07-08 15:18:27', '2021-07-08 15:18:27'),
(476, 38, 74, 71, '2021-07-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I continued in the wonderful Spectrum Math book that Mom recommended, with Timur clearly demonstrating that he has developed a solid foundation of quantitative skills. As far as Multiplying and Dividing Rational Numbers are concerned, Timur did not need a lot of review, and only needs to be careful with positive and negative signs. We will do a final review of Chapter 2 at our next session, and then proceed to Chapter 3, where I am sure I will see more of the same \"sharp as a tack\" Timur!', '50', '2021-07-08 15:53:31', '2021-07-08 15:53:31'),
(477, 38, 56, 57, '2021-07-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Welcome back Ian!  Actually, I guess he is welcoming me back, as he has been working consistently throughout the year with Smart Cookie Tutors!  It was so nice to see this talented young man again, although I had to tilt my head upwards an additional 30 degrees to adjust for his accelerated growth!  I have been requested to review on a macro basis Ian\'s work from last year, as well as to  give him a head start for the upcoming curriculum. We looked at his final exam review sheet, which we completed most of and which is meeting the review goal for last year.  Ian was \"on his game\" for most of the material!  We will complete it at our next session and then proceed with the preparatory work for next year.  The highlight of the day, of course, was our review of Mobile Suit Gundam Iron Blooded Orphans, and my post session viewing of Mikazuki\'s Last Stand.  I will ask for Ian\'s commentary on the matter at our next meeting, as I am not really sure for whom I am rooting!!', '50', '2021-07-08 16:12:33', '2021-07-08 16:17:28'),
(478, 60, 73, 67, '2021-07-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read Chicka Chicka Boom Boom and practiced both sounding out words and being able to quickly identify certain sight words such as \"and\", \"that\", \"it\", \"the\", and \"to\". Practiced addition and subtraction up to 10.', '20', '2021-07-09 03:33:47', '2021-07-09 03:33:47'),
(479, 60, 75, 72, '2021-07-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Retook a noun quiz and scored much better on it! Practiced adding and subtracting two digit numbers and started reading a book together. Focusing on comprehension and summarizing.', '20', '2021-07-09 03:34:42', '2021-07-09 03:34:42'),
(480, 34, 76, 73, '2021-07-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Exponents and KenKen.', '70', '2021-07-12 16:04:14', '2021-07-12 16:04:14'),
(481, 34, 77, 73, '2021-07-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Identifying pairs of numbers that add to 10. Subtraction practice and coloring.', '70', '2021-07-12 16:04:52', '2021-07-12 16:04:52'),
(482, 38, 74, 71, '2021-07-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I hope that the feeling is reciprocal, but I want Timur to know that I am having a wonderful time studying with him.  He is always so in control, and that allows him to focus and to maximize his progress.  Today, we successfully completed Chapter 2 of Spectrum Math and its post-test, with Timur demonstrating through a subset of problems that he knows his stuff!  We then proceeded to Chapter 3, which so far seems to be emphasizing the critical skill of being able to translate word problems into equivalent mathematical expressions.  Timur is blowing me away with how quickly he is mastering this concept.  Keep up the great work Timur!  Thanks for making tutoring so fun and rewarding!', '50', '2021-07-13 13:55:33', '2021-07-13 13:55:33'),
(483, 60, 75, 72, '2021-07-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Finished reading \"The Grumpy Octopus\". Since it ended with a cliffhanger, wrote a 2-3 sentence prediction for how it would continue. Started talking about addition/subtraction with regrouping.', '20', '2021-07-13 15:36:18', '2021-07-13 15:36:18'),
(484, 34, 46, 47, '2021-07-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Continued summer work: systems of equations, point-slope form, graphing, combining like terms of polynomials, operations with fractions review, synthetic division.', '70', '2021-07-14 18:09:25', '2021-07-14 18:09:25'),
(485, 60, 73, 67, '2021-07-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read “Chicka Chicka 1 2 3”. Focused on comprehension and sight words. Practiced basic addition and subtraction under 3.', '20', '2021-07-14 23:43:56', '2021-07-14 23:43:56'),
(487, 42, 81, 77, '2021-07-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Austin\'s mom and I discussed his reading needs for the coming year. He definitely struggles with comprehension and needs help with word problems and vocabulary. We\'re going to start reading together and will practice with word problems and key math words.', '45', '2021-07-15 16:19:53', '2021-07-15 16:19:53'),
(488, 42, 58, 59, '2021-07-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addison and I continued to read Wonder and discuss the overarching themes, carrying through the book. She is showing improvement with tracking and reading with expression.', '45', '2021-07-15 16:23:23', '2021-07-15 16:23:23'),
(489, 42, 80, 59, '2021-07-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmy and I continued reading The Wild Robot. She is reading out loud beautifully, and with expression and more importantly, is able to understand what she reads as she reads out loud. We also discussed prefixes, suffixes, and Latin roots as a way to help her decode vocabulary words.', '45', '2021-07-15 16:26:58', '2021-07-15 16:26:58'),
(490, 38, 74, 71, '2021-07-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur took in a ton today!  Not only did we complete the Chpt. 3  pretest, which involved writing equivalent mathematical expressions for word phrases as well as translating full word problems into equations, but we even took a detour to learn and apply the concept of percentages.  Timur did great throughout, and is well on his way to mastering the material he will need as a foundation for next year!  I look forward to continuing with him on his road to success!  Great job Timur!', '50', '2021-07-15 16:44:55', '2021-07-15 16:45:27'),
(491, 60, 75, 72, '2021-07-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Learned how to subtract with regrouping. Used manipulatives in order to break apart a 10 and move it over.', '20', '2021-07-16 01:58:53', '2021-07-16 01:58:53'),
(492, 74, 79, 76, '2021-07-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Muskan worked on subtraction and place value problems. I played a game with her called Nim after 30 minutes and also gave her stickers when she got problems right. She is doing well with addition and improving with place value. Muskan still finds it difficult to do subtraction without using her fingers to count.', '35', '2021-07-18 18:27:44', '2021-07-18 18:27:44'),
(493, 38, 74, 71, '2021-07-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur is one motivated young man.  It is the middle of summer, he is on time for every session, and he even brought me questions about the homework.  And very good questions at that!  Way to go Timur!  And to top off a very productive day, we spent  a good part of the session learning about per cents and word problems involving them. Timur continues to amaze!  Keep up the great work!', '50', '2021-07-20 13:02:45', '2021-07-20 13:02:45'),
(494, 38, 74, 71, '2021-07-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur is well on his way to mastering the art of translating word problems into equivalent mathematical language, as he demonstrated today through the many problems that he solved correctly.  It is such an important skill for a \r\n student  to have as he climbs the \"mathematical ladder\", and Timur has become an \"A-rated\" climber!  I gave him a couple of short homework assignments to reinforce his new talents, which I am certain he will have no problem with.  I look forward to moving on to inequalities at our next session, and to continue to watch Timur grow in his skills and confidence.', '50', '2021-07-22 13:38:07', '2021-07-22 13:38:50'),
(495, 38, 56, 57, '2021-07-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I successfully completed the review worksheet from last year\'s final exam, and although he may have been a bit rusty, we applied a healthy dose of WD-40 and got him \"working smoothly\" again!  The review included translating word problems into their equivalent mathematical language, as well as deriving equations for lines both parallel and perpendicular to a given line.   Ian is a real trooper to keep so \"tuned in\" during his vacation , and we will leverage that focus as we transition into next year\'s curriculum at our next session.  Great work Ian!', '50', '2021-07-22 13:46:55', '2021-07-22 13:46:55'),
(496, 74, 79, 76, '2021-07-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we worked more on subtraction and place values. Muskan has improved a lot since the last session and went through most of the subtraction problems without needing to use her fingers. She is also doing better with saying numbers out loud.', '35', '2021-07-23 03:13:05', '2021-07-23 03:13:05'),
(497, 60, 75, 72, '2021-07-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced capitalizing names in sentences. Started reading a book and worked on reading comprehension and figuring out the meaning of words based on the context.', '20', '2021-07-27 02:44:36', '2021-07-27 02:44:36'),
(498, 42, 44, 43, '2021-07-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I started reading the first book in the Time Warp Trio series, discussing the origins of the King Arthur legend. We also did some multiplication practice and will continue to work on the more difficult times tables (6, 7, 8, 9)', '45', '2021-07-28 00:53:36', '2021-07-28 00:53:36'),
(499, 42, 81, 77, '2021-07-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Austin and I worked on some word problems and identified words he needs to look for when decoding a problem. We also began reading The Invention of Hugo Cabret.', '45', '2021-07-28 00:55:24', '2021-07-28 00:55:24'),
(500, 42, 48, 49, '2021-07-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I continued reviewing her addition and subtraction skills. She has backslid slightly, rushing through problems and mistaking the operation in problems. We will continue to refresh and rebuild these skills.', '45', '2021-07-28 00:56:36', '2021-07-28 00:56:36'),
(501, 42, 48, 49, '2021-07-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I continued working through addition and subtraction problems. She is doing better at slowing herself down and is using other techniques beyond counting on her fingers.', '45', '2021-07-28 00:57:42', '2021-07-28 00:57:42'),
(502, 42, 46, 47, '2021-07-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I continued discussing The Joy Luck Club, continuing to discuss the overarching themes of memory and mother/daughter conflicts. Her responses to the book have been thoughtful and considered, showing an increased improvement in her close reading skills.', '45', '2021-07-28 00:59:09', '2021-07-28 00:59:09'),
(503, 60, 73, 67, '2021-07-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read “Bathtime for Biscuit” focusing on sight words and finding patterns. Learned how to count by 2s and practiced counting by 2s and 10s.', '20', '2021-07-28 12:51:17', '2021-07-28 12:51:17'),
(504, 60, 75, 72, '2021-07-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Finished reading \"Rocket Says Look Up!\" and wrote 2 sentences about something that Jaden looked forward to. Practiced addition and subtraction with regrouping.', '20', '2021-07-29 00:28:21', '2021-07-29 00:28:21'),
(505, 38, 74, 71, '2021-07-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It did not take long for Timur to become the \"inequalities expert\" that we all knew he could and would become.  Just a few practice problems and \"Voila\"! - Timur could handle any inequality that he was dealt.  And on top of that, that special rule that requires one to flip the inequality sign if multiplying or dividing by a negative number was no match for Timur\'s laser like recognition and steel trap memory!  Even more impressive is that these concepts were all being learned in the context of translating word problems into their equivalent quantitative language!  Timur, I cannot keep up with you!', '50', '2021-07-29 13:11:00', '2021-07-29 13:11:00'),
(506, 42, 44, 43, '2021-07-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I continued reading \"The Knights of the Kitchen Table,\" reviewing unfamiliar vocabulary words and discussing the \"chivalric code\" that inspired Arthurian legend.', '45', '2021-07-29 15:37:33', '2021-07-29 15:37:33'),
(507, 42, 81, 77, '2021-07-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Austin and I went over important words to look for in word problems to help him better decode what problems are asking him to do. He\'s going to need more practice, but he showed improvement within the session. We also continued reading \"Hugo Cabret.\"', '45', '2021-07-29 15:43:02', '2021-07-29 15:43:02'),
(508, 42, 58, 59, '2021-07-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addie found out she is changing schools this fall and so we had to pivot with her summer reading. She finished \"Wonder\" and we began discussing her new summer reading book \"A Wrinkle in Time.\"  We also went over her new summer reading assignment.', '45', '2021-07-29 15:44:56', '2021-07-29 15:44:56'),
(509, 42, 80, 59, '2021-07-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmy finished her first summer reading book \"The Wild Robot.\" She did an excellent job of identifying the book\'s major themes and message. We have moved on to reading \"Stuart Little\"', '45', '2021-07-29 15:46:33', '2021-07-29 15:46:33'),
(510, 38, 82, 78, '2021-07-30', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'It was a true pleasure to meet and begin work with Cora today, who succeeded in charming me in about three seconds.  She truly is gifted and talented (just as advertised), and in ways well beyond academic disciplines!  Cora will be learning 7th grade math while only in 5th grade next year, and Mom wants to be sure that Cora \'s skills are as up to date as they can be before that time. Two areas of concern are dividing by decimals and multiplying large numbers, and it did not take long to detect that Cora is displaying symptoms of \"calculator dependency\". Fortunately, she does not yet have severe case of CD, and I gave Mom a \"heads up\" to intervene as soon as possible. Cora seems very willing as well to address the issue, and I assigned her some relevant problems to solve.  I look forward to working with this very gifted and talented young lady.', '50', '2021-08-01 16:16:17', '2021-08-01 16:16:17'),
(511, 42, 48, 49, '2021-07-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked on mixed operation word problems and subtraction/addition math riddles. She is going to be out of town for much of August, so I left Leena with multiple worksheets to continue practicing over the break.', '45', '2021-08-01 19:55:03', '2021-08-01 19:55:03'),
(512, 34, 46, 47, '2021-08-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Continued with summer review packet.', '70', '2021-08-02 19:05:57', '2021-08-02 19:05:57'),
(513, 34, 45, 46, '2021-08-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reducing first when multiplying fractions.', '75', '2021-08-03 15:01:35', '2021-08-03 15:01:35'),
(514, 38, 56, 57, '2021-08-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In another of our dynamic bi-weekly sessions, Ian and I ventured into some preparatory work for next year, mainly covering slopes and intercepts.  Although Ian went incognito today with no camera, I could still tell how accomplished he felt with his quick comprehension and application of these subjects.  I am optimistic that just having seen these ideas will give him a great head start on future material.  Although Ian had no updates for me on any of the graphic novel characters we have discussed in the past, I hope that he will advise me how I can keep up with their adventures after our upcoming last lesson.  Ian is wonderful!', '50', '2021-08-05 14:46:43', '2021-08-05 14:46:43'),
(515, 34, 45, 46, '2021-08-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Multiplication trick: how to multiply quickly by 15. Reviewed multiplication by 10, including decimal numbers, and practiced dividing odd numbers by 2.', '75', '2021-08-05 15:14:08', '2021-08-05 15:14:08'),
(516, 45, 45, 46, '2021-08-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Figurative language review using metaphor, simile, imagery and personification. 10/10 score on review. Reading comprehension activity and metaphor identification. Personification identification activity.', '50', '2021-08-05 21:59:13', '2021-08-05 21:59:13'),
(517, 60, 73, 67, '2021-08-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on addition and subtraction word problems and understanding what the answer means in terms of the problem. Learned what the sum and the difference are. Practiced counting by 2s.', '20', '2021-08-08 19:04:10', '2021-08-08 19:04:10'),
(518, 38, 82, 78, '2021-08-06', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'After getting a full understanding of Cora\'s multicolored hair, we proceeded to work on a multiplication problem involving numbers with multiple digits.  Cora has her own \"modern math\" way to do these problems, which I never learned in school.  Although she did come up with the correct answer, I was concerned about he amount of time that it took her.  This may be the same issue that we brought up at our last session, a need to become more proficient at her multiplication tables.  Cora and I transitioned over to a times tables practice website, and at her request, we worked on the \"sevens\" table. I think that with disciplined review and practice, Cora will be on her way to increased proficiency in calculations.  And Cora, thanks for the great riddle!', '50', '2021-08-08 23:13:06', '2021-08-08 23:13:06'),
(519, 60, 75, 72, '2021-08-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Spent some time reviewing what needs to be in a sentence. Practiced writing capital letters. Worked on addition and subtraction with regrouping.', '20', '2021-08-10 01:39:50', '2021-08-10 01:39:50'),
(520, 38, 74, 71, '2021-08-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I both returned from mini-vacations with renewed energy available to give a significant recharge to our tutoring sessions.  We are already up to Chapter 4 in the book that we are using, with today\'s material focusing on proportions and slopes.  Although he sometimes claims he does not know how to do something (that I know he knows how to do!), an expression of disbelief on my part and a little prodding always bring out the best in Timur!  He continues to advance and inspire.  Great work Timur!', '50', '2021-08-10 14:07:30', '2021-08-10 14:07:30'),
(521, 34, 46, 47, '2021-08-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Review mental math tricks multiplication by 11 and 15, continued work on summer packet (completing the square, finding domain of rational functions, simplifying radicals), and quick logic game: Mystery Box.', '70', '2021-08-10 17:23:12', '2021-08-10 17:23:12'),
(522, 34, 45, 46, '2021-08-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mystery Box game, adding fractions and decimals, review how to multiply by 15 mentally.', '75', '2021-08-10 17:23:37', '2021-08-10 17:23:37'),
(523, 60, 73, 67, '2021-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed what the vowels are and what silent E does. Practiced addition and subtraction up to 10.', '20', '2021-08-12 02:27:02', '2021-08-12 02:27:02'),
(524, 38, 82, 78, '2021-08-11', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Cora\'s tropical background has me totally relaxed when we work together....but we still get a lot done!  Today, we worked through a long division problem with decimals, for which Cora became quite comfortable.  We then proceeded to review the \"nine\'s tables\", with Cora teaching me the associated shortcuts. I successfully stumped Cora with two of my riddles, which was probably my biggest accomplishment of the day, considering how bright a young lady Cora is!  Yea Cora!', '50', '2021-08-12 13:34:12', '2021-08-12 13:34:12'),
(525, 38, 74, 71, '2021-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur is becoming the king of cross-multipliers!  In today\'s session, we delved deeply into ratios, proportions, and cross-multiplication, with Timur successfully learning and applying the concepts.  It is clear to me that Timur will enter the upcoming school year extremely well armed, as he has been committed to putting in the time and effort at our sessions and with the homework (Not a lot!) that I assign. I was disappointed, however, when Timur was not willing to ask his Mom if I may come on future family vacations so as not lose any tutoring momentum.  Oh well!  I guess everyone has their limits.', '50', '2021-08-12 13:44:01', '2021-08-12 13:45:04'),
(526, 34, 45, 46, '2021-08-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mystery box game to work on logical processing. Practice with adding and subtracting decimals and fractions.', '75', '2021-08-12 15:05:27', '2021-08-12 15:05:27'),
(527, 60, 75, 72, '2021-08-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Began talking about adding with three place values. Practiced writing lower case letters. Read two poems and talked about what a poem is and worked on comprehension.', '20', '2021-08-13 16:05:28', '2021-08-13 16:05:28'),
(528, 42, 81, 77, '2021-08-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Austin and I continued working on decoding word problems. He\'s showing improvement in identifying keywords and phrases and translating them to the correct operations. We\'re also continuing to read \"Hugo Cabret.\"', '45', '2021-08-14 17:03:05', '2021-08-14 17:03:05'),
(529, 42, 58, 59, '2021-08-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addie and I continued working on \"A Wrinkle in Time,\" tracking the plot and character development and identifying and defining unfamiliar vocabulary.', '45', '2021-08-14 17:04:19', '2021-08-14 17:04:19'),
(530, 42, 80, 59, '2021-08-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmy and I continued reading Stuart Little, going over unfamiliar vocabulary. We also picked out the project she\'s going to do for \"The Wild Robot.\"', '45', '2021-08-14 17:05:57', '2021-08-14 17:05:57'),
(531, 42, 46, 47, '2021-08-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I finished our discussion of \"The Joy Luck Club,\" exploring repeating imagery and overarching themes. We\'re going to discuss Steinbeck\'s \"The Pearl\" next.', '45', '2021-08-14 17:07:49', '2021-08-14 17:07:49'),
(532, 42, 44, 43, '2021-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I began our session with a game of \"Multiplication War\" and went over additional strategies for multiplying 2 digit numbers. After, we discussed medieval castles and weaponry as background for our book \"The Knights of the Kitchen Table.\"', '45', '2021-08-14 17:09:37', '2021-08-14 17:09:37'),
(533, 42, 81, 77, '2021-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Austin and I tried more difficult, multi-step word problems and he\'s showing huge improvement in correctly decoding the language. We also continued with Hugo Cabret and will do some additional practice with writing next week.', '45', '2021-08-14 17:11:01', '2021-08-14 17:11:01'),
(534, 42, 58, 59, '2021-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addy and I covered the fifth chapter of A Wrinkle in Time and discussed and took notes on the rising action of the story. This is a challenging book for Addy, conceptually, so we also took some time to clarify the scientific concepts discussed in the story.', '45', '2021-08-14 17:12:29', '2021-08-14 17:12:29'),
(535, 42, 80, 59, '2021-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmy and I are almost finished with Stuart Little and are on the hunt for our next book. We also did some pre-writing for her summer reading project.', '45', '2021-08-14 17:15:01', '2021-08-14 17:15:01'),
(536, 42, 46, 47, '2021-08-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Zoe and I began our discussion of John Steinbeck\'s The Pearl, focusing on Steinbeck\'s life and career and the history and perspectives that informed his writing. We will begin discussing the text itself next week.', '45', '2021-08-14 17:16:19', '2021-08-14 17:16:19'),
(537, 74, 79, 76, '2021-08-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Muskan worked on reviewing all the topics that we have worked on during our sessions, which include addition, subtraction, and place values. Muskan has improved greatly in doing subtraction without counting with her fingers. She has also gotten much better at saying 3 and 4 digit numbers out loud.', '35', '2021-08-16 00:58:40', '2021-08-16 00:58:40'),
(538, 38, 74, 71, '2021-08-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I encountered a more challenging topic today in rates and proportions, although with Timur\'s serious work ethic and great discipline, I refuse to be concerned. We will just consider a few different angles from which to present and review the material, and I am confident that one of them will hit the target.  In fact, I am excited about getting back to work, as I know that Timur really wants to continue along his exponential growth curve. Timur is fantasic!', '50', '2021-08-16 23:14:42', '2021-08-16 23:15:09'),
(539, 38, 74, 71, '2021-08-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'On my second attempt to convey the principles of ratio, proportion, and constant of proportionality, Timur\'s ability to answer my questions and to solve the problems indicated that I was successful.  Of course, that is a reflection of Timur\'s academic gifts, as one could not expect one to process bad information and draw anything of it.  I should have quit while I was ahead, as my initiative to find and tell over \"proportion\" math jokes failed miserably.  Have a great trip Timur! See you in about 10 days!', '50', '2021-08-19 15:41:55', '2021-08-19 15:41:55'),
(540, 38, 82, 78, '2021-08-18', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'After showing me her proficiency in long division, both with and without remainders, Cora and I proceeded to  vanquish the \"9\'s\" multiplication tables.  What a great job this young lady did!  To me that is reason enough for Cora to be able to take Roo for a walk, even if she is under 11!   Rooby-dooby-do will not cause any trouble, and if he does, Cora will discipline him with her \"purple tips\"!  Let Cora walk!  Let Cora walk!', '50', '2021-08-19 15:47:38', '2021-08-19 15:47:38'),
(541, 38, 56, 57, '2021-08-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian had a bit of a headache today, but he still managed to push beyond the pain to learn a ton about arithmetic and geometric sequences, as well as recursive and explicit formulas.  I hope that all of this math did not make the headache any worse for one of my favorite students.  We will continue working next time on the packet provided by the school to get Ian ready for next year.  Feel better Ian!', '50', '2021-08-19 15:51:31', '2021-08-19 15:51:31'),
(542, 60, 75, 72, '2021-08-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on adding and subtracting three digit numbers with regrouping. Reviewed parts of a sentence (ex. Capital letter to start and period at the end).', '20', '2021-08-19 18:04:05', '2021-08-19 18:04:05'),
(543, 60, 73, 67, '2021-08-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced subtraction under 10s. Started talking about how addition and subtraction can be reversed (8-2=6 and 6+2=8). Will need some reinforcement next time, but began grasping the concept.', '20', '2021-08-19 18:05:18', '2021-08-19 18:05:18'),
(544, 45, 45, 46, '2021-08-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Grammar practice activity - parts of speech, contractions. Figurative language review using oxymorons', '50', '2021-08-19 21:56:11', '2021-08-19 21:56:11'),
(546, 60, 75, 72, '2021-08-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read a book about teachers in nature. Worked on comprehension. Basic practice with identifying greater and less than numbers with three digits.', '20', '2021-08-21 20:40:57', '2021-08-21 20:40:57'),
(547, 60, 75, 72, '2021-08-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Talked about regrouping when you have a 0 in the next place value so you have to move to the next one. Read \"Enemy Pie\" and worked on following words with his finger so that he doesn\'t lose his place as well as comprehension.', '20', '2021-08-24 14:03:29', '2021-08-24 14:03:29'),
(548, 34, 45, 46, '2021-08-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Multiplication by 11. Mystery box challenge.', '75', '2021-08-24 15:01:36', '2021-08-24 15:01:36'),
(549, 38, 56, 57, '2021-08-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I are both thrilled that we will continue to work together during the school year.  That he wants to build upon what we have done over the summer is a true compliment.  Today, as part of his summer packet, we continued to focus on linear functions, examining them through three (3) different lenses: graph, table, and equation.  Ian seems to be doing very well with all of them,  and should be well prepared to transition into next year.  I raised a concern with Mom about ian keeping his camera off for the entire session, as I suspect it hampers his focus and sense of responsibility.  As of the time of this review, I have not heard back from her.  I am looking forward to a productive year with Ian!', '50', '2021-08-27 15:23:44', '2021-08-27 15:23:44'),
(550, 60, 75, 72, '2021-08-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed addition with two, three-digit numbers. Talked about how you can check addition with subtraction.', '20', '2021-08-29 01:03:40', '2021-08-29 01:03:40'),
(551, 60, 73, 67, '2021-08-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read Pinkalicious Tutu-riffic. Started learning about \"Addition Fact Families\". (ex. 2+3=5 ; 5-3=2)', '20', '2021-08-29 01:18:14', '2021-08-29 01:18:14'),
(552, 42, 58, 59, '2021-08-30', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Addie and I continued working on her summer reading project, completing the bulk of the work. We are going to meet again on Wednesday to finish things off. Addie struggled with this book and I think is going to need extra support as she transitions to a new school with more rigorous academics.', '45', '2021-08-31 13:57:55', '2021-08-31 13:57:55'),
(553, 42, 83, 79, '2021-08-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I assessed Jayda\'s addition and subtraction skills. Her mental math skills are very strong and she has many strategies for breaking down more difficult problems. Sometimes she mixes up operations and definitely finds word problems challenging.', '45', '2021-08-31 14:01:28', '2021-08-31 14:01:28'),
(554, 42, 44, 43, '2021-08-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sam and I finished reading \"The Knights of the Kitchen Table.\" His reading fluency is hugely improved and is comfortable working through difficult words.', '45', '2021-08-31 14:05:28', '2021-08-31 14:05:28'),
(555, 42, 80, 59, '2021-08-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmy and I finished Stuart Little and completed edits on her summer reading project. We began our next book \"The Trumpet of the Swan.\"', '45', '2021-08-31 14:07:22', '2021-08-31 14:07:22'),
(556, 42, 58, 59, '2021-08-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addie and I continued working through \"A Wrinkle in Time,\" completing some of her summer reading work along with it. I find Addie often gives up when it comes to working through difficult words, so we are working on strategies to help her slow down and break down tough words.', '45', '2021-08-31 14:11:56', '2021-08-31 14:11:56'),
(557, 34, 45, 46, '2021-08-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Logic puzzles: Tit Tac Total, X marks the spot, and Thinking in reverse.', '75', '2021-08-31 15:02:36', '2021-08-31 15:02:36'),
(558, 60, 75, 72, '2021-08-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Talked about Fact Families and how if you add two numbers you can subtract one from the sum to get the other. Worked on \"Question Mark\" practice in Language Arts Book.', '20', '2021-09-01 03:43:50', '2021-09-01 03:43:50'),
(559, 34, 45, 46, '2021-09-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Negative numbers, NIM with expanded game board, and goodbye for now - Brendon will transition to working with Jeff this school year.', '75', '2021-09-02 15:03:53', '2021-09-02 15:03:53'),
(560, 34, 58, 59, '2021-09-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed summer math packet in preparation for Glenelg.', '70', '2021-09-02 18:21:20', '2021-09-02 18:21:20'),
(561, 38, 56, 57, '2021-09-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Ian left his work at school, his steel trap memory enabled us to conduct a productive session. With camera on and smartphone (eventually) on the table, Ian and I explored linear expression word problems and their graphical expression.  Ian is truly a bright young man, and when he lets others marvel at his talents, he can compete with the best of them!  I am optimistic it is going to be a year of solid growth for Ian!  Now just in case the Khan Academy website is down next week, my hope is that that steel trap memory of his will remember to bring home his work for our next session! :)', '50', '2021-09-02 18:54:38', '2021-09-02 18:54:38'),
(562, 45, 45, 46, '2021-09-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', '23 minutes late. Creative writing prompt warm-up. Practice with similes vs. metaphors using Kahoot.', '50', '2021-09-02 21:58:04', '2021-09-02 21:58:04'),
(563, 60, 75, 72, '2021-09-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read \"How Do Dinosaurs Say I Love You\" and did two comprehension questions. Talked about how you can check subtraction with addition and did a couple practice problems.', '20', '2021-09-07 13:47:46', '2021-09-07 13:47:46'),
(564, 34, 58, 59, '2021-09-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Finished summer packet review.', '70', '2021-09-07 14:59:03', '2021-09-07 14:59:03'),
(565, 60, 75, 72, '2021-09-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Finished up with how you can check subtraction with addition and three-digit addition and subtraction. Will start time on Friday. Started reading about Pinkerton. Focused on defining unknown words and comprehension. Talked a little bit about the historical parts of the book.', '20', '2021-09-08 00:25:11', '2021-09-08 00:25:11'),
(566, 60, 73, 67, '2021-09-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Spent the first 15 minutes looking at a globe and identifying the continents, will reinforce next time. Talked about the associative property (without naming it) and how you can flip addition. Talked about doubles and near doubles in addition.', '20', '2021-09-08 00:26:38', '2021-09-08 00:26:38'),
(567, 60, 60, 62, '2021-09-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Went through Canvas and redid assignments that were still open and did not reflect what Olivia was capable of. Got her organized for the homework that she needed to do that night. Reviewed how to multiply fractions and started a little bit of multiplication review.', '20', '2021-09-12 20:29:13', '2021-09-12 20:29:13'),
(568, 60, 75, 72, '2021-09-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read a couple more pages of \"The Eye that Never Sleeps\" and put it in historical context. Worked on comprehension and him being able to retell to me what had happened so far in the story. Talked about how to tell time on a regular clock.', '20', '2021-09-12 20:30:32', '2021-09-12 20:30:32'),
(569, 38, 74, 71, '2021-09-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur came well prepared today in more ways than one.  Not only did he bring his classwork for us to review together, but he also demonstrated that his hard work in our sessions over the summer provided him with the necessary tools to breeze through the current unit.  The rewards from Timur\'s diligence and discipline are now being collected!  Our focus today was on functions and their different manifestations (i.e., table, graph, and equation), with Timur hitting a home run in all of them. It is very inspiring to see Timur\'s growth come to fruition in the \"real time\" of the classroom.  Great work Timur!', '50', '2021-09-13 13:32:03', '2021-09-13 13:32:03'),
(570, 45, 45, 46, '2021-09-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Student no showed.', '50', '2021-09-16 22:00:28', '2021-09-16 22:00:28'),
(571, 45, 45, 46, '2021-09-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Creative writing prompt. Metaphor explanation activity. Practice with similes and metaphors. Figurative language review.', '50', '2021-09-16 22:01:09', '2021-09-16 22:01:09'),
(572, 60, 60, 62, '2021-09-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Checked through Canvas. Went through school math packet and made sure that she understood everything. There was a practice page in the packet so she completed that.', '20', '2021-09-18 11:23:01', '2021-09-18 11:23:01'),
(573, 60, 75, 72, '2021-09-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed time and talked about quarter hours. Learned about units of measurement and practiced measuring with inches and cm. Finished reading about Pinkerton, will work on comprehension questions on Sunday.', '20', '2021-09-18 11:24:51', '2021-09-18 11:24:51'),
(574, 60, 75, 72, '2021-09-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed three comprehension questions about \"The Eye That Never Sleeps\" to finish it off. Reviewed units of measurement and learned how to make a line plot.', '20', '2021-09-19 19:43:52', '2021-09-19 19:43:52'),
(575, 38, 56, 57, '2021-09-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In a unusual Friday session (thank you Mom and Ian for your flexibility), Ian and I had a dynamite hour of tables, graphs and equations - all representations of functions. Ian only continues to grow, showing that he is willing to put in the work in order to produce the results., And the results are great!  Keep plugging Ian! There\'s no stopping you now!', '50', '2021-09-20 02:43:16', '2021-09-20 02:43:16'),
(576, 60, 86, 83, '2021-09-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on 1.9 Homework and clarified unknown topics.', '25', '2021-09-20 03:40:21', '2021-09-20 03:40:21'),
(577, 41, 46, 47, '2021-09-19', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'functions quiz review: transformations, inverse', '50', '2021-09-21 03:33:39', '2021-09-23 00:33:29'),
(578, 82, 68, 69, '2021-09-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics C - How to calculate the electrostatic force between charges.  How to calculate the elctric filed at a given point due to a single point charge, and due to multiple charges.', '50', '2021-09-22 23:24:21', '2021-09-22 23:24:21'),
(579, 60, 73, 67, '2021-09-21', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on adding and subtracting up to 10. Completed 2/5 word problems.', '20', '2021-09-23 19:23:18', '2021-09-23 19:23:43'),
(580, 60, 66, 67, '2021-09-21', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Completed math homework, which was subtracting on the number line by counting up and counting down. Reviewed a little bit of multiplication.', '20', '2021-09-23 19:24:48', '2021-09-23 19:24:48'),
(581, 45, 45, 46, '2021-09-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Creative writing prompt: video game. Reading comprehension passage and figurative language identification.', '50', '2021-09-23 22:30:15', '2021-09-23 22:30:15'),
(582, 60, 60, 62, '2021-09-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Went over math notes from class and made sure that she understood everything and could describe what she needed to do. Did a couple of practice problems and reviewed multiplication.', '20', '2021-09-24 04:19:24', '2021-09-24 04:19:24'),
(583, 38, 56, 57, '2021-09-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian came prepared today to discuss some \"Linear Functions as Mathematical Models\" problems today, specifically only two problems out of a set for which  Ian was otherwise very successful.  The skill involved was mainly one of translating a word problem dealing with a linear model into an equation and graph.  Once Ian and I worked together on \"Speed on a Hill Problem\", and he had learned and integrated the tools necessary for solution, Ian had no problem with \"Calorie Consumption Problem\".  Ian deserves so much credit over these past few weeks, as he has been willing to meet late on a Friday afternoon when he should be all rights be chilling after a hard week in school.  Thanks Ian! I really appreciate it.  You are doing great!', '50', '2021-09-26 15:52:34', '2021-09-26 15:52:34'),
(584, 38, 74, 71, '2021-09-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I are getting into a good groove with our once per week schedule, although he did express the fact that he misses the jokes. I admit that I have gone more lightly on them over the last month, but his pointing it out has inspired me to revive my \"less serious\" side.  As far as Timur\'s math skills are concerned, they are as seriously strong as ever, as he demonstrated today when we worked on proportions.  Keep up the great work Timur! And do not fear!  The jokes will be back!', '50', '2021-09-26 16:00:13', '2021-09-26 16:00:13'),
(585, 60, 75, 72, '2021-09-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on basic measurement calculations (finding which is longer) and measuring in inches and centimeters.', '20', '2021-09-26 17:30:09', '2021-09-26 17:30:09');
INSERT INTO `timesheets` (`timesheet_id`, `tutor_id`, `student_id`, `user_id`, `date`, `time`, `duration`, `duration2`, `description`, `hourly_pay_rate`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(586, 60, 75, 72, '2021-09-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed how to use a ruler. Measured some objects. Learned about perimeter and how to find it. Started reading book about the Tooth Fairy.', '20', '2021-09-26 17:31:07', '2021-09-26 17:31:07'),
(587, 41, 46, 47, '2021-09-26', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'precalc: vertex form/standard form, finding vertex and x-intercepts', '50', '2021-09-26 17:41:20', '2021-09-26 17:41:20'),
(588, 38, 74, 71, '2021-09-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I was back on track with my joke telling skills (at least I thought so!), and at the very least, Timur was his extremely polite self and rewarded me with a smile.  As far as the math was concerned, Timur not only successfully nailed down the ability to model a word problem with a linear equation, but he also refreshed his basic algebraic equation solving skills in the process!  Timur seems confident with his skills, and that is very inspiring! You are moving in the right direction Timur.  Keep it going!', '50', '2021-09-27 18:48:01', '2021-09-27 18:48:01'),
(589, 82, 68, 69, '2021-09-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Yash asked to move Monday 9/27 session to Sunday 9/26 to get ready to take a test Monday.  We met Sunday 9/26; solved problems in physics and calculus.', '50', '2021-09-27 19:54:21', '2021-09-27 19:54:21'),
(590, 60, 73, 67, '2021-09-28', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed vowels. Worked on handwriting on the beginner type of paper. Reviewed identifying numbers that are greater and less than others.', '20', '2021-09-29 02:21:58', '2021-09-29 02:21:58'),
(591, 60, 66, 67, '2021-09-28', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Completed math homework for this week (breaking apart a number to add) and reviewed multiplication of 3s.', '20', '2021-09-29 02:22:33', '2021-09-29 02:22:33'),
(592, 42, 93, 85, '2021-09-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I assessed where Matthew is with his math skills, focusing on multiplication and division. He struggles to show his work which leads to small mistakes on more extensive problems. He\'s definitely bright enough to move more quickly with 4th-grade material, so we are going to start with 2 digit multiplication and go from there.', '45', '2021-09-30 13:24:34', '2021-10-31 13:28:26'),
(593, 60, 60, 62, '2021-09-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Went over volume. Looked through math homework and started explaining surface area. Tried to explain that SA = 2lw + 2lh + 2wh, but something about the formula has not clicked yet.', '20', '2021-10-01 04:39:50', '2021-10-01 04:39:50'),
(594, 45, 45, 46, '2021-09-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Student’s mother texted the teacher 10 minutes into the session to let her know that Brendon would not be home in time for the lesson.', '50', '2021-10-01 11:07:14', '2021-10-01 11:07:14'),
(595, 60, 75, 72, '2021-10-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed three digit addition and subtraction. Read The Lonely Polar Bear, worked on comprehension and using pictures to help tell the story. Practiced with exclamation points.', '20', '2021-10-02 14:10:57', '2021-10-02 14:10:57'),
(596, 41, 46, 47, '2021-10-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'review function test, polynomial zeros and sketching graphs', '50', '2021-10-03 18:23:27', '2021-10-03 18:23:27'),
(597, 38, 56, 57, '2021-10-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a hardcore geometry day for Ian and me, as we started with basic circle anatomy and did not stop until we had developed expertise in inscribed, central, and circumscribed angles, as well as chords, secants, and tangents. And all of this in only one hour!  And if that was not enough, I got an exclusive close-up look at Ian\'s hand painted Vulcan Unicorn.  That experience alone made the whole session worthwhile, and made all other aspects of the lesson pale in comparison.  But as far as the geometry is concerned, Ian is integrating and applying the relevant concepts...and doing great!  (Mom: Are we keeping Friday, or is it back to Wednesday?)', '50', '2021-10-04 02:08:00', '2021-10-04 02:08:00'),
(599, 38, 74, 71, '2021-10-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur is ramped up his game this evening as we transitioned from the isolation of  \"regular\" algebraic variables to that of variables from literal equations.  All of those letters can get confusing, but after a few valiant attempts, Timur was a master!  We also reviewed Timur\'s classwork on understanding the interaction between variables.  Timur\'s two sides clearly surfaced this evening, as in one instance he reeled off a solution after solving the problem in his head, while just a few minutes earlier, the same type of problem was \"unsolvable\".  Timur said he may have been tired.  \"Further research is required\" :).   It is still the beginning of the year, so Timur\'s work load is still very manageable.  I filled in some pauses with some formerly undiscovered riddles, which stumped Timur, but produced some nice smiles.  Timur is doing great!', '50', '2021-10-04 19:51:32', '2021-10-04 19:51:32'),
(600, 38, 89, 85, '2021-10-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a pleasure to meet Sarah and her Mom today to begin our tutoring engagement.  Sarah is an extremely bright young lady with stellar character traits, as well lofty goals.  And from just the short I have spent with Sarah, it is just about a \"lock\" that she will achieve those goals.  She is currently in 7th grade regular math, is testing to be in 7th grade honors math (8th grade level), and would like me to advance her much as possible through 7th grade GT math (9th grade level).  And all of this \"jockeying for position\" is for Sarah to be able to transition smoothly and immediately into 8th grade GT math next year (10th grade level)!  Now if that is not a demonstration of drive, discipline, and determination, then I do not know what is!  The biggest obstacle Sarah may have is the tutor\'s ability to keep all of that straight :) ! But I think I have it now, and I am looking forward to accompanying Sarah on her journey.  We will use the GT 7th grade math curriculum provided by Mom, which we began yesterday from transformations.  Best of all, Sarah did not mind my corny jokes. Thank you Sarah!', '50', '2021-10-05 15:11:44', '2021-10-05 15:11:44'),
(601, 38, 45, 46, '2021-10-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a pleasure to meet and begin work with Brendon today, and as well, to meet Mom.  Brendon\'s joyful demeanor and bright smile captivated me instantly.  My positive impression about this sharp young man was only enhanced by his quick wit and great attitude about his work.  It seems that Brendon\'s Mom has requested some academic support throughout the school year, and if my wonderful first experience with Brendon is any indication of what is to come, I am enthusiastically \"all in\".   Our work today began with finding areas of polygons, and ended with a tank fight led by Commander Brendon.  While I was out of breath after that last ordeal, Brendon was calm, collected  and the destroyer of every tank he encountered.,  Way to go Brendon! I look forward to working with you!', '50', '2021-10-05 15:24:24', '2021-10-05 15:24:24'),
(602, 38, 45, 46, '2021-10-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'After his dynamic victories in the tank battles of yesterday, Brendon was back to face a barrage of problems involving areas of parallelograms and triangles. It seems like his tank commander skills are transferrable, as Brendon handily disposed of the assigned worksheet.  In those few areas where he did struggle a bit, some minimal guidance from me got him right back on track.  Although we did not have time for Brendon to  teach me a new game, I was able to squeeze in a couple of good riddles.  That\'s about the only thing for which I can stump Brendon!  He is doing great!', '50', '2021-10-06 19:01:47', '2021-10-06 19:01:47'),
(603, 60, 73, 67, '2021-10-05', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced the letter combinations \"sh\", \"ch\", \"th\", \"ed\", and \"ing\" and came up with three words for each category. Reviewed different vowels and the continents on the globe.', '20', '2021-10-07 01:59:15', '2021-10-07 01:59:15'),
(604, 60, 66, 67, '2021-10-05', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on math homework that was adding and subtracting three digit numbers. Introduced how to add and subtract when you have the numbers under each other. Talked about carrying over with addition (will introduce subtraction next time). Learned about factors and prime numbers while reviewing multiplication facts.', '20', '2021-10-07 02:24:13', '2021-10-07 02:24:13'),
(605, 42, 93, 85, '2021-10-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I reviewed the 12 times table and worked on discovering the pattern that would help him memorize the table more effectively. We also continued practice on multiplying 2-digit numbers and reviewed how to check his work.', '45', '2021-10-07 15:01:36', '2021-10-31 13:28:24'),
(606, 38, 56, 57, '2021-10-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a \"serious series\" session for Ian and me today, as his teacher dumped two whole pages of practice problems upon us.  Ian seemed significantly more proficient with these exercises over even his last tutoring session, and I was very impressed with the upward movement.  In my effort to learn more about my clients and their interests, I requested that Ian demonstrate one of his favorite games to me for a few minutes as a halftime break. Ian was more than willing to oblige, and he took me on a peaceful and calming tour of MORTAL KOMBAT. During our stroll, Ian handily finished his opponent, and made certain that I did not miss out on my ration of blood and guts.  Thank you Ian!  I look forward to our next \"vacation\" together! :)  Ian is a true pleasure to work with.', '50', '2021-10-07 16:41:21', '2021-10-07 16:41:21'),
(607, 38, 84, 80, '2021-10-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a pleasure to begin work today with Margaret, an extremely talented young lady with stellar character traits who is focusing on her SSAT Math preparation. WOW! I am still amazed! It became clear almost immediately how gifted Margaret truly is, and I plan to leverage those gifts to challenge her as much as I am able in the time we will spend together. We began with an SSAT prep book, to be certain that Margaret builds up her recognition of the various problem types dealt to the student by the SSAT, as well as to identify and eliminate any specific weaknesses (I am certain very few!) that Margaret may have. I anticipate that Margaret will benefit greatly from our tutoring relationship, and I look forward to working with her.', '55', '2021-10-08 14:00:59', '2021-10-08 14:00:59'),
(608, 60, 60, 62, '2021-10-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed assignments on Canvas. Went through packet and talked about surface area and nets. Created a net for a cube in order to see what measurements were important and how to find surface area from the net.', '20', '2021-10-08 17:30:51', '2021-10-08 17:30:51'),
(609, 60, 75, 72, '2021-10-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed that sentences need to start with upper case letters and end with punctuation marks. Practiced handwriting by writing sentences and questions. Learned how when coming before words that start with vowels you should use \"an\".', '20', '2021-10-10 04:18:48', '2021-10-10 04:18:48'),
(610, 38, 74, 71, '2021-10-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur showed me tonight that he truly DOES know his algebraic principles!  In several problems that we faced, he successfully set up the equation and solved it.  I was thrilled to see that the ideas we have been reviewing have solidified, and that Timur can access them with ease.  Although it was difficult to detect specifically the impetus of many of the assigned problems, Timur\'s excellent demonstration of his talents made the evening truly worthwhile. Great job Timur!', '50', '2021-10-11 18:24:46', '2021-10-11 18:24:46'),
(611, 38, 89, 85, '2021-10-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I continued our excursion into 7th Grade GT Math, but took a \"different exit\" after I learned that she is already covering last week\'s topic, transformations, in class.  Since my mission is to build Sarah\'s skill base in order to facilitate her transition into 8th Grade GT math next year, I feel that out focus should be on new concepts. So we took a look at the syllabus, and ventured into per cent changes for most of the session, with a little bit of exponents added in at the end for flavor!  By the way, congratulations to Sarah for passing her entrance exam into 7th Grade Honors Math. It is certainly a step that befits her!  Sarah is a quick study and a pleasure to work with.', '50', '2021-10-12 21:56:56', '2021-10-12 21:56:56'),
(612, 38, 45, 46, '2021-10-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I missed Brendon for our scheduled session this evening.  I do not blame him for enjoying the day off from school :).  I look forward to continuing with Brendon on Thursday.  Be well Brendon!', '50', '2021-10-12 21:59:03', '2021-10-12 21:59:03'),
(613, 82, 68, 69, '2021-10-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Gauss\'s Law', '50', '2021-10-13 14:47:48', '2021-10-13 14:47:48'),
(614, 82, 68, 69, '2021-10-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Calculus and Gauss\'s Law-Solving Problems', '50', '2021-10-13 14:48:50', '2021-10-13 14:48:50'),
(615, 41, 46, 47, '2021-10-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Precalc test review polynomials', '50', '2021-10-14 03:36:44', '2021-10-14 03:36:44'),
(616, 60, 73, 67, '2021-10-12', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed continents. Worked on spelling with some of the words from class, some basic words, and some words with the letter combinations that we learned last week.', '20', '2021-10-14 05:08:48', '2021-10-14 05:08:48'),
(617, 60, 66, 67, '2021-10-12', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Completed math homework, which was adding three digit numbers by taking apart one of the addends. Reviewed what prime numbers and factors were.', '20', '2021-10-14 05:11:04', '2021-10-14 05:11:04'),
(618, 42, 93, 85, '2021-10-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I reviewed multiplying 2 digit by one digit numbers before we looked at multiplying 3 digit by 1 digit numbers. He is still extremely resistant to writing problems down and I am concerned that virtual tutoring may be enforcing this. I’ve used the white board function on Zoom, but I don’t know if this is offering the same thing pen and paper would.', '45', '2021-10-14 15:49:12', '2021-10-31 13:28:22'),
(619, 38, 56, 57, '2021-10-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian is really getting into some high level mathematics these days.  This evening, for example, we began estimating the equation of a line that represented the best fit to a scatterplot.  Ian did very well with the new and difficult concepts, and with some additional practice should be able to integrate the necessary skills into his inventory.  I look forward to joining him as he enhances his quantitative knowledge.  Way to go Ian!', '50', '2021-10-14 23:06:32', '2021-10-14 23:06:32'),
(620, 38, 84, 80, '2021-10-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I missed Margaret for our scheduled session today,  Mom later reported that an unexpected conflict arose with a tennis match, I certainly hope that Margret fared well in the match!  I look forward to continuing with Margaret in her SSAT preparation at our next meeting.  Be well!', '55', '2021-10-15 14:24:06', '2021-10-15 14:24:06'),
(621, 60, 60, 62, '2021-10-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Went through Canvas. Reviewed geography quiz and discussed what approximate means. Read over Language Arts assignment, and discussed plan to finish it by Wednesday. Learned about squares and square roots.', '20', '2021-10-16 05:52:14', '2021-10-16 05:52:14'),
(622, 60, 75, 72, '2021-10-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed the difference between length and width and how to make line plots. Talked about bar graphs and how to read them. Read \"The Little Red Pen\", emphasis on comprehension and reading the whole word instead of guessing.', '20', '2021-10-16 05:55:19', '2021-10-16 05:55:31'),
(623, 34, 91, 88, '2021-10-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Distributive property, combining like terms, simplifying expressions by substituting values for variables.', '79', '2021-10-17 19:08:57', '2021-10-17 19:08:57'),
(624, 38, 74, 71, '2021-10-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur has become a master at translating a word problem into mathematical  format.  He demonstrated that clearly this evening in his assignment, and although Timur does not cease to impress me, his growth in his quantitative skills does not surprise me. He is consistent, controlled, and dedicated.  As a reward, I printed out some new math jokes for future sessions. I hope this will please \"the master\" :)!', '50', '2021-10-18 18:02:17', '2021-10-18 18:02:17'),
(625, 38, 89, 85, '2021-10-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'One thing is for sure!  After spending an hour working on exponents and their properties, Sarah has definitely added a new quantitative tool to her inventory.  This young lady picks up information so quickly.  I already trust her to do MY exponents homework! With each session, Sarah is succeeding in getting herself primed to succeed in 8th grade GT Math next year.  Don\'t change a thing Sarah. You are doing great!', '50', '2021-10-19 14:38:30', '2021-10-19 14:38:30'),
(626, 38, 45, 46, '2021-10-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was so nice to collaborate with Brendon again after a short layoff (although I enjoy working with this young man so much that any layoff is too long!).  This evening, we focused on odd-shaped quadrilaterals and finding their areas, mainly by decomposing them into familiar shapes for which the area calculations are known.  Brendon was exceedingly diligent, and by the end of the session, had acquired a comfort level with the methodology.  The teacher gave the students a very long assignment, so I trust that Brendon will be able to complete it independently.  Great work Brendon!', '50', '2021-10-19 15:27:08', '2021-10-19 15:27:08'),
(627, 60, 73, 67, '2021-10-19', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Started reading \"Sam and the Firefly\". Want to focus on identifying letter combinations in order to be able to quickly piece together words. Learned \"oo\" sound and \"ee\" sound.', '20', '2021-10-20 03:31:28', '2021-10-20 03:32:12'),
(628, 60, 66, 67, '2021-10-19', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Completed math homework. Learned about how to subtract with regrouping and did 7 practice problems.', '20', '2021-10-20 03:31:57', '2021-10-20 03:31:57'),
(629, 82, 68, 69, '2021-10-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics-C.  Solved worksheet problems, mainly on Gauss\'s law applications', '50', '2021-10-20 13:34:31', '2021-10-20 13:34:31'),
(630, 42, 93, 85, '2021-10-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I began by working on some multi-step missing number problems before moving onto 2 digit by 2 digit multiplication. Matthew is still extremely resistant to writing down his work and struggled with the multi-step problems until I made him write everything down. Once he did that, he absolutely excelled. When we moved on to more complex multiplication, he was forced to write down all of his steps and got everything right.', '45', '2021-10-20 21:33:46', '2021-10-31 13:28:20'),
(631, 38, 56, 57, '2021-10-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Ian and I continued our treacherous journey through the jungle of linear regression.  Although Ian\'s work on his assignment prior to our session indicated he had gone a bit off course, I was able to \"right the ship\" in my role as navigator with minimal effort.  Ian picked up quickly on the correct approach to predict dependent variables from the regression equation, and all was so well, that we took a break to see another of his exciting games.  This time it was a \"super shark\" that caused all the blood and gore, and I got seasick from being in the water for too long.  Ian came to the rescue, and all is good,  Have a great week Ian.  Keep up the super work!', '50', '2021-10-21 15:05:14', '2021-10-21 15:05:14'),
(632, 38, 45, 46, '2021-10-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon and I were very creative this evening, as we used technology and cameras to make the session work. The most important fact is that Brendon seemed very confident with the material (e.g., proportions), and was able to arrive at solutions independently  And by the end of it all, we completed his assignment with a few minutes to spare.  So Brendon showed me how to construct a military base and defend it from intruders.  I was exhausted from all the suspense and warfare, but felt secure that Brendon was leading the charge.  Happy Birthday Brendon!', '50', '2021-10-22 18:47:14', '2021-10-22 18:47:14'),
(633, 42, 45, 46, '2021-10-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon and I discussed his interests, favorite and least favorite things about school, and where he wants to improve. We discussed his interest in history and I plan to use that to help him improve with his reading fluency and comprehension.', '50', '2021-10-23 00:31:45', '2021-10-23 00:31:45'),
(634, 34, 91, 88, '2021-10-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Solving two step equations with variables on both sides. Assigned a little homework for extra practice.', '79', '2021-10-24 14:04:04', '2021-10-24 14:04:04'),
(635, 38, 74, 71, '2021-10-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In a \"to the point\" session  today, Timur and I completed an assignment for which he had an opportunity to get some extra points.  Some of the questions were unclear, but we managed to decipher the sheet enough to come up with about 80% of it.  We both thought that we could use the word \"horizontal\" to describe  a function with zero slope, but the automated grading system would not accept it.  So not to be deterred, we moved on with a smile and accepted whatever we could get.  Timur has a great attitude, and continues to excel!', '50', '2021-10-25 17:58:38', '2021-10-25 17:58:38'),
(636, 60, 60, 62, '2021-10-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on simplifying ratios. Learned how to factor two numbers, find their GCF, and simplify them.', '20', '2021-10-26 02:37:01', '2021-10-26 02:37:01'),
(637, 38, 89, 85, '2021-10-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah soaks up whatever topics we decide to cover in her preparatory work for next year, and today was no exception. From scientific notation to transformation rules, and then to the Pythagorean Theorem, Sarah was as focused as a laser, going from theory to practice with no problem.  And she continues to think my jokes are funny (or at least she is very polite).  8th Grade G&T Math  - get ready for Sarah!', '50', '2021-10-26 15:38:25', '2021-10-26 15:38:25'),
(638, 38, 45, 46, '2021-10-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon reported that he had a wonderful birthday, and it seems that he is all in one piece after an active game of laser tag!  This young man is truly living life to the fullest, as demonstrated by his perpetual joyful attitude. This evening, we successfully handled another of his homework assignments, which in this case included ratios, and tape diagrams. That last one was a new one for me! Unfortunately, the assignments are long and we ran out of time, but Brendon seemed to be confident with his understanding of the material.  Brendon continues to shine!', '50', '2021-10-26 16:18:17', '2021-10-26 16:18:17'),
