(706, 42, 96, 92, '2021-11-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Drew and I continued to work on Macbeth, finishing up with act one and moving on to act two. He\'s beginning to show more interest in the play and was very interested in the context and performance history of the play. We\'re beginning to build a report, though mom remains anxious that she hasn\'t seen improvement yet.', '54', '2021-11-30 01:09:15', '2021-11-30 01:09:15'),
(707, 42, 45, 46, '2021-11-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon and I began reading War Horse, discussing the lead-up to the war and the unique perspective from which the book is written. He continues to improve when it comes to his ability to analyze.', '50', '2021-11-30 01:11:23', '2021-11-30 01:11:23'),
(708, 42, 97, 93, '2021-11-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Kennedy and I worked on some different addition and subtraction techniques. Her number sense is strong, but she struggles with carrying numbers and place value. We plan to meet every other week.', '54', '2021-11-30 01:13:26', '2021-11-30 01:13:26'),
(709, 34, 91, 88, '2021-11-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Review for upcoming make-up test: estimation, area, perimeter, solving equations in one variable and one step, metric units.', '79', '2021-11-30 18:11:28', '2021-11-30 18:11:28'),
(710, 34, 95, 88, '2021-11-30', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Review for upcoming make-up test: estimation, area, perimeter, solving equations in one variable and one step, metric units.', '79', '2021-11-30 18:11:36', '2021-11-30 18:11:36'),
(711, 38, 89, 85, '2021-11-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'After a review of the elimination method for solving simultaneous linear equations, for which Sarah has become a true expert, we proceeded to look into a more obscure method (i.e., matrix method).  But after seeing how obscure it is, we moved on to other topics!  Sarah and I began to review areas, volumes, and surface areas. We just scratched the surface today, and plan to make greater inroads at our next session.  Sarah is truly a talented young lady!', '50', '2021-11-30 20:34:43', '2021-11-30 20:34:43'),
(712, 60, 73, 67, '2021-11-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Quick review of sight words. Started reading \"No Jumping on the Bed\", has much more difficult words than the last book. Practiced counting by 2s, 3s, and 5s.', '20', '2021-12-01 03:25:34', '2021-12-01 03:25:34'),
(713, 60, 66, 67, '2021-11-30', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on completing a full multiplication table.', '20', '2021-12-01 03:25:58', '2021-12-01 03:25:58'),
(714, 60, 60, 62, '2021-11-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Checked over canvas for missing assignments. Worked on math homework for finding unit price and multiplying it to get other amounts. Matching activity for units of measurement. Completed a multiplication table for practice.', '20', '2021-12-01 03:27:13', '2021-12-01 03:27:13'),
(715, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Homework on exponents. Review concept and worked through problems.', '79', '2021-12-02 02:43:37', '2021-12-02 02:43:37'),
(716, 34, 80, 59, '2021-12-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on adding and subtracting fractions with unlike denominators, adding and subtracting whole and mixed numbers, and general review.', '70', '2021-12-02 02:44:26', '2021-12-02 02:44:26'),
(717, 38, 56, 57, '2021-12-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian is a very special young man.  He was pretty much caught up in his work before today\'s session, but was willing to admit  that there are other areas in which he needs enrichment.  And the area he chose to work on today was his basic multiplication skills. It requires a strong character to admit a weakness, and Ian did not hesitate to express an interest in improving himself.  We tried to find some games, but the ones we found were too elementary.  So we settled on timestables.com, and Ian received his diploma in three different tables, Great job Ian!  I am proud to call you my student.', '50', '2021-12-02 16:46:45', '2021-12-02 16:46:45'),
(718, 94, 98, 95, '2021-12-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I worked with Mason on a reading and writing lesson. We read the book together \"The most beautiful thing\" about a Hmong family and a grandmother who fled difficulties in her country to search for a better life. I had him write about it, reflect upon his grandparents and their history, and draw a picture representing the theme of the book. I gave him the homework of asking his grandparents about their life growing up in Korea and their stories. He said that his take home message from the book was that when he looks into the mirror he will see his imperfections as beautiful because it\'s his story (like the main character of the book). It was very sweet.', '25', '2021-12-04 04:36:16', '2021-12-04 04:36:16'),
(719, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-04', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Prime factorization, prime and composite numbers.', '79', '2021-12-04 14:32:51', '2021-12-04 14:32:59'),
(720, 34, 80, 59, '2021-12-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Prep for chapter test.', '70', '2021-12-04 21:41:53', '2021-12-04 21:41:53'),
(721, 34, 95, 88, '2021-12-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed which assignments were missing, set goals for grades, completed homework assignment on GCD', '79', '2021-12-04 21:43:12', '2021-12-04 21:43:12'),
(722, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked with Markus and Tyler on homework assignments from the past week. Exponents and GCD.', '79', '2021-12-06 01:39:00', '2021-12-06 01:39:00'),
(723, 82, 94, 91, '2021-12-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Newton\'s laws application problems', '60', '2021-12-06 13:38:48', '2021-12-06 13:38:48'),
(724, 82, 68, 69, '2021-12-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'E;ectric Current Density and Drift Velocity', '50', '2021-12-06 13:42:23', '2021-12-06 13:42:23'),
(725, 60, 75, 72, '2021-12-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced identifying a word\'s meaning by using context clues. Started learning about fractions. Started learning about multiplication, learned the rules for 0s and 1s. Read \"No Jumping on the Bed\".', '20', '2021-12-07 15:42:53', '2021-12-07 15:42:53'),
(726, 94, 98, 95, '2021-12-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason wanted to learn about dogs today. So, we read a book about dogs and learned a lot of new vocabulary words. He drew his favorite part of the book and explained it. Then, we learned how to make an origami dog. I had him make the dog and then write a story about his dog and give it a name. We did a quick review of the difficult words from the last two sessions. He is doing great and I hope, having fun too!', '25', '2021-12-07 22:54:35', '2021-12-07 22:54:35'),
(727, 34, 80, 59, '2021-12-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Exponents, square roots, and general review.', '70', '2021-12-08 00:57:31', '2021-12-08 00:57:31'),
(728, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Made up homework from last week on factors and divisibility rules. Played NIM.', '79', '2021-12-08 00:57:59', '2021-12-08 00:57:59');
INSERT INTO `timesheets` (`timesheet_id`, `tutor_id`, `student_id`, `user_id`, `date`, `time`, `duration`, `duration2`, `description`, `hourly_pay_rate`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(729, 60, 73, 67, '2021-12-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on basic addition facts. Read about Christmas in Germany and answered comprehension questions. Kept reading \"No Jumping on the Bed\".', '20', '2021-12-08 15:06:12', '2021-12-08 15:06:12'),
(730, 60, 66, 67, '2021-12-07', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on multiplication with 2s and 3s. Math homework on division.', '20', '2021-12-08 15:08:47', '2021-12-08 15:08:47'),
(731, 38, 89, 85, '2021-12-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Thank you Sarah for your flexibility due to my need to change the session time.  I really appreciate it!  And as my expression of gratitude, I subjected you today to a \"grab bag\" of problems involving volume and surface area.  But as always, you rose to the occasion and did superbly!  We covered mostly prisms today, and may spend some time on some of the other classic figures at our next session.   Great job Sarah!', '50', '2021-12-08 16:10:04', '2021-12-08 16:10:04'),
(732, 42, 93, 90, '2021-12-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I continued to work on the multiplication of multi-digit numbers. He\'s beginning to find it easier and is more adept at catching his mistakes. We also began looking at long division.', '54', '2021-12-08 20:00:55', '2021-12-08 20:00:55'),
(733, 42, 96, 92, '2021-12-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Drew and I continued to work on his Macbeth homework. He has excellent insights on character motivation and expresses himself in writing very well. He does need a non-parental motivator and is still not doing independent work outside of our sessions.', '54', '2021-12-08 20:04:37', '2021-12-08 20:04:37'),
(734, 34, 45, 46, '2021-12-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'd=rt formula, solving word problems based on unit rates.', '75', '2021-12-09 01:03:10', '2021-12-09 01:03:10'),
(735, 38, 56, 57, '2021-12-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Ian may have left his work in school, he still came to the tutoring session prepared to learn. And so we picked up where we left off last week, and worked on Ian\'s multiplication skills. We played well designed games on Education .com, as well as grinding our way through the tables on timestables.com.  Ian is much more confident in his \"6\" and \"7\" tables, and seemed to enjoy the whole process.  He certainly showed great results!  Way to go Ian!', '50', '2021-12-09 17:36:32', '2021-12-09 17:36:32'),
(736, 82, 94, 91, '2021-12-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practice Problems on Applyng Newton\'s Laws on Friction Force', '60', '2021-12-10 16:18:54', '2021-12-10 16:19:55'),
(737, 42, 93, 90, '2021-12-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I looked at simplifying fractions and converting fractions in order to determine which was greater. He is using his multiplication and division skills well in this new unit and has no problem speaking up when he doesn\'t understand the concepts.', '54', '2021-12-10 23:32:32', '2021-12-10 23:32:32'),
(738, 42, 96, 92, '2021-12-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Drew and I worked through his homework for Act 3 of Macbeth. He had actually completed a few questions before coming to meet with me. We finished all but two questions and Drew already seems more confident in his ability to get the work done well.', '54', '2021-12-10 23:37:00', '2021-12-10 23:37:00'),
(739, 42, 45, 46, '2021-12-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon and I read sections from \"Boots on the Ground.\" His reading fluency is hugely improved, though he continues to need help decoding difficult vocabulary words.', '50', '2021-12-10 23:39:50', '2021-12-10 23:39:50'),
(740, 60, 60, 62, '2021-12-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Met online. Checked through Canvas and then worked on math review sheet that involved ratios and some cross multiplying.', '20', '2021-12-11 01:38:48', '2021-12-11 01:38:48'),
(741, 38, 74, 71, '2021-12-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I were challenged this evening by expressing linear equations in standard form.  Although we have previously and frequently utilized many of skills required for this task, Timur seemed to struggle somewhat in accessing and applying them.  Upon asking him, he did admit that he often does not understand the teacher\'s presentation, and does not ask for clarification.  I will  continue to incorporate different ways to explain the concepts in the hope that one of them will click with Timur.  I remain optimistic that Timur will return to the levels of focus and progress that I have seen him attain in the past.', '50', '2021-12-13 20:47:14', '2021-12-13 20:47:14'),
(742, 38, 89, 85, '2021-12-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I finished up our review of surface areas and volumes today, as our survey of 7th grade G&T Math topics continues.  We specifically focused on world problems, and Sarah, as always, had no problem integrating and applying new concepts. We plan to begin probability and statistics at our next session.  Mom will let me know if that will be next week or next year.  Great job Sarah!', '50', '2021-12-14 17:19:41', '2021-12-14 17:19:41'),
(743, 42, 97, 93, '2021-12-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Kennedy and I reviewed place value through the expanded form method. We later moved to adding 3 digit numbers. When Kennedy continued to struggle with place value, we added using expanded form. While Kennedy still made a few small errors, this method generally worked for her and when she started checking her work, her accuracy improved.', '54', '2021-12-14 19:48:58', '2021-12-14 19:48:58'),
(744, 94, 98, 95, '2021-12-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason told me last week that he wanted to learn about cars. So, this week\'s lesson was all about sports cars. He told me the cars he wants and we discussed describing words. We read a book about sports cars (he read it and we practiced the difficult words). We learned about physics and aerodynamics. He summarized the book and his takeaway was about how cars are low to the ground to allow them to go faster. We then did a \"make your own car\" game. After he designed his own sports car, I had him write a story about it using describing words. We then played a word game: how many words can you make out of the word TRANSPORT. It is so fun to see Mason making progress in his reading skills and watch him use strategies such as breaking down words, sounding them out, and repeating the word three times once he has mastered it.', '25', '2021-12-14 22:56:11', '2021-12-14 22:56:11'),
(745, 96, 48, 49, '2021-12-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'This was my introduction meeting with Leena. She filled me in on her situation with teachers at school and we went through her homework. Her mom let me know that she needs to work on multiplication and prime vs composite numbers. We played card games to go through multiplication and composite numbers.', '20', '2021-12-14 23:47:14', '2021-12-14 23:47:14'),
(746, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Simplifying fractions with exponents.', '79', '2021-12-15 01:59:59', '2021-12-15 01:59:59'),
(747, 38, 43, 40, '2021-12-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Welcome back Mallory!  What a pleasure it was today to see and chat with this bright young lady and to hear about her successful (with difficulties :) ) transition to high school.  When we got down to business, Mallory humbly displayed her proficiency with geometric proofs, and made it clear that she wanted to get even better.  I was happy to assist, although Mallory is already just about where she needs to be,.  I look forward to playing whatever constructive role I am asked to do to assist her through the obstacle course of geometry.  So nice to see you again Mallory!', '50', '2021-12-15 14:48:01', '2021-12-15 14:48:01'),
(748, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Prepped for quiz and reviewed scientific notation.', '79', '2021-12-15 20:23:27', '2021-12-15 20:23:27'),
(749, 82, 100, 98, '2021-12-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Algebraic Fractions', '54', '2021-12-15 20:40:18', '2021-12-15 20:40:18'),
(750, 42, 93, 90, '2021-12-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I continued working on simplifying and comparing fractions. His focus was not great today and he needed to be redirected multiple times. He also continues to be resistant to writing down problems, though he is beginning to see that when he doesn\'t write things down, he makes more mistakes.', '54', '2021-12-16 00:43:57', '2021-12-16 00:43:57'),
(751, 82, 46, 47, '2021-12-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Logarithms', '45', '2021-12-16 02:29:18', '2021-12-16 02:29:18'),
(752, 38, 56, 57, '2021-12-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In our last session for 2021, ian and I completed a thorough review of exponents and their properties.  I almost did not recognize Ian with his \"hair loss\" :) (i.e., his haircut), but once I regained my composure, Ian demonstrated his quick integration and application of the various rules that govern exponents. We even went ahead a bit, with Ian maintaining full focus throughout the session.  Have a wonderful holiday Ian. I look forward to reuniting in 2022!', '50', '2021-12-16 15:12:56', '2021-12-16 15:12:56'),
(753, 82, 94, 91, '2021-12-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Circular Motion', '60', '2021-12-17 00:40:01', '2021-12-17 00:40:01'),
(754, 38, 43, 40, '2021-12-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Polygon dilations was trending today, as Mallory and I spent our time preparing for her upcoming exam on that exact topic.  We approached our preparation from various \"angles\",  using Khan Academy\'s array of resources to make sure the concepts were understood.  Mallory did great, and that was despite the fact that she had to wait hours for a COVID test before our session, and had to travel 40 minutes after our session to get to volleyball practice!  How does Mallory do all that?  I do not know.  But  one thing is for sure...she is no Mediocre Mallory! :)', '50', '2021-12-17 14:38:35', '2021-12-17 14:38:35'),
(755, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed two step equations and exponents.', '79', '2021-12-17 20:41:25', '2021-12-17 20:41:25'),
(756, 60, 60, 62, '2021-12-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Met online. Looked over english essay and talked about keeping consistent tense. Realized that she probably misunderstood directions and directed her to talk to her teacher about the prompt. Reviewed multiplication and negatives.', '20', '2021-12-18 00:33:25', '2021-12-18 00:33:25'),
(757, 34, 91, 88, '2021-12-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed exponents, solving two step equations, simplifying fractions before multiplying, scientific notation.', '79', '2021-12-19 16:09:57', '2021-12-19 16:09:57'),
(758, 82, 68, 69, '2021-12-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Resistivity and Temperature Coefficient', '50', '2021-12-20 14:41:46', '2021-12-20 14:41:46'),
(759, 38, 74, 71, '2021-12-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur had a strong session this evening, as he called up his inner strengths and applied them to solve problems which he had previously struggled with.  The main focus in our session was converting linear equations to standard form, a process which requires skills that Timur and I have been looking a for quite some time.  With renewed enthusiasm, Timur recognized that he DOES know how to navigate the necessary steps, and proved to himself that he COULD take the problem to its conclusion.  What a great way to end the year. \r\n Great job Timur!', '50', '2021-12-20 22:31:20', '2021-12-20 22:31:20'),
(760, 38, 89, 85, '2021-12-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I moved on to Probability and Statistics today, using Khan Academy for the exercises to supplement the concepts. Sarah is so bright, that I was sure we could dive right in to the applications, with me providing necessary explanations to get us started or to bridge from one problem set to the next. It worked out great, and Sarah kept up her end of the bargain by performing superbly on the questions.  I jut knew that our dynamite teamwork would come through for us once again!  Great work Sarah!', '50', '2021-12-21 17:43:15', '2021-12-21 17:43:15'),
(761, 94, 98, 95, '2021-12-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we learned about \"how to take care of dogs\", which Mason requested because his family got a miniature poodle puppy. We read a book together and did several fun activities about dog behavior and how to safely interact with dogs. We filled out a doggy chore sheet and learned many new vocabulary words.', '25', '2021-12-21 22:05:27', '2021-12-21 22:05:27'),
(762, 96, 48, 49, '2021-12-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I had a virtual session where we played a game to practice multiplication facts with composite/prime numbers. I have another game, as well as two worksheets, that we were not able to get to, but that Leena and I have saved for our next session.', '20', '2021-12-22 22:48:02', '2021-12-22 22:48:02'),
(763, 38, 43, 40, '2021-12-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'From dilations to reductions to similar triangles, Mallory has got it covered!  This young lady has been through a lot lately: a multi-hour wait for a COVID test and now a brother who has taken over the basement while in quarantine. And yet she still comes to the sessions eager to review old things and to learn new things.  I think the end of year break has come at a good time for Mallory, and I know she will get the rest and relaxation she deserves. ( I hope!)  Have a great holiday Mallory!', '50', '2021-12-23 02:58:47', '2021-12-23 02:58:47'),
(764, 60, 75, 72, '2021-12-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Basic review of punctuation and contractions. Read about Christmas in the Netherlands and completed a comprehension worksheet. Reviewed adding and subtracting three digit numbers, with and without regrouping. Talked about multiplication as repeated addition.', '20', '2021-12-24 08:34:34', '2021-12-24 08:34:34'),
(765, 34, 80, 59, '2021-12-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Homework on percentages and reviewed common denominators when adding fractions.', '70', '2021-12-29 19:33:00', '2021-12-29 19:33:00'),
(766, 38, 89, 85, '2021-12-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I started our grandest topic today, as we entered the world of probability and statistics.  We used Khan Academy as our guide, and as I expected, Sarah either already had some familiarity with the various sub-topics, or used her natural talents to pick up on new concepts very quickly.  Sarah never lets me down!  I anticipate that we will (or at least could) be involved in stats for awhile, as the subject matter is deep and Sarah will strengthen her already vast knowledge base in the process.  Have a wonderful holiday Sarah!', '50', '2021-12-31 14:09:55', '2021-12-31 14:09:55'),
(767, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed solving two step equations, dividing by a fraction, and scientific notation.', '79', '2022-01-03 20:35:47', '2022-01-03 20:35:47'),
(768, 34, 95, 88, '2022-01-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed solving two step equations, dividing by a fraction, scientific notation, and simplifying exponents.', '79', '2022-01-03 20:36:06', '2022-01-03 20:36:06'),
(769, 94, 98, 95, '2022-01-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we learned about Peru through a book and several readings. He wrote a recipe and drew a picture of his favorite food. We learned many words and animals.', '25', '2022-01-04 23:20:45', '2022-01-04 23:20:45'),
(770, 96, 48, 49, '2022-01-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I had a virtual session where we played a math game. She had to go through each number 1 through 100 and decide if it was prime or composite, as well as discover the factors for each composite number.', '20', '2022-01-04 23:39:18', '2022-01-04 23:39:18'),
(771, 34, 80, 59, '2022-01-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Comparing fractions, with unlike denominators. Reducing.', '70', '2022-01-05 00:44:30', '2022-01-05 00:44:30'),
(772, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Two step equations, scientific notation, simplifying fractions with exponents.', '79', '2022-01-05 00:50:48', '2022-01-05 00:50:48'),
(773, 38, 43, 40, '2022-01-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Even though Mallory was still enjoying her extra (snow) days out of school, she still came with a ton of enthusiasm to our lesson today.  She even brought her own lesson plan, as she had not yet received any new assignments.  We went over to Khan Academy, and began a thorough review of many of the the geometric concepts she had learned so far this year.  As her final exam will be comprehensive, I commend her on her proactive approach to her preparation.  None of the concepts were extremely difficult, but the large amount of material suggests that a refresh was an excellent idea. Way to go Mallory!', '50', '2022-01-05 18:49:16', '2022-01-05 18:49:16'),
(774, 34, 45, 46, '2022-01-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'KenKen logic practice.', '75', '2022-01-06 01:00:29', '2022-01-06 01:00:29'),
(775, 38, 56, 57, '2022-01-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian is doing a great job of keeping ahead of the curve! He knows he has a test coming up so he made sure that we spent our time reviewing the material and making sure that he is ready. The topics included functions and sequences, and the review accomplished its purpose by refreshing concepts that may have become a bit rusty.  The exam is not for two more weeks, so Ian and I will have plenty of opportunity to lock in the skills and tools that he will need for the exam.  Excellent work Ian!', '50', '2022-01-06 15:02:30', '2022-01-06 15:02:30'),
(776, 60, 60, 62, '2022-01-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on math homework on  percentages. Talked about how you can convert percentages to fractions and multiply with the value to find x% of the value. Showed her prealgebra on khan academy and made a plan to start looking at that.', '20', '2022-01-07 19:45:36', '2022-01-07 19:45:36'),
(777, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'ixl prep for test: reducing fractions, scientific notation, GCF with variables and exponents', '79', '2022-01-07 20:35:30', '2022-01-07 20:35:30'),
(778, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'IXL skills practice: exponents, solving equations with variable exponents.', '79', '2022-01-08 20:06:28', '2022-01-08 20:06:28'),
(779, 38, 43, 40, '2022-01-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today\'s highlights with Mallory (who never was mediocre!) included a thorough review of similar triangles and the Pythagorean Theorem.  My star student handled it all with ease, and was not even rattled by a surprise visit from Sully (who makes a habit out of coming in unannounced!). When we were faced with a challenging application of designing a ramp that conforms with the requirements of the ADA, Mallory and I put our heads together and came up with a dynamite solution.  As always Mallory, you are a pleasure to work with!', '50', '2022-01-09 02:53:37', '2022-01-09 02:53:37'),
(780, 44, 45, 46, '2022-01-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We worked on Spanish homework. His homework was to describe his room in Spanish. He learned new descriptive words as well as \"where\" descriptors.', '45', '2022-01-09 17:11:35', '2022-01-09 17:11:35'),
(781, 34, 95, 88, '2022-01-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'IXL practice: scientific notation and exponents.', '79', '2022-01-09 17:29:44', '2022-01-09 17:29:44'),
(782, 38, 74, 71, '2022-01-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I were back in business today, and it was a thrill to see my wonderful student after the holiday break.  Timur admits that he forgets a bit over a layoff, so we got right back to work to get the blood flowing again. Today\'s highlights included solving simultaneous equations through graphing, and expressing the solution as an ordered pair and in algebraic format. (We had a bit of trouble interpreting that last request, so Timur has taken it upon himself to clarify with his teacher). We also successfully categorized equations pairs by number of solutions: one, none or infinite.  Welcome back Timur!  So nice to see you again!', '50', '2022-01-10 16:32:13', '2022-01-10 16:32:13'),
(783, 38, 89, 85, '2022-01-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I continued with our survey of introductory statistics today, and specifically focused on frequency tables and relative frequency tables. Sarah easily grasped the logistics of completing the tables. Who would have doubted that?  But where she truly shined was when we analyzed what the numbers mean. Sarah absorbed, pondered and conjectured with the best of statisticians!  I am truly proud to call Sarah my student.  Wonderful work Sarah!', '50', '2022-01-11 15:05:22', '2022-01-11 15:05:22'),
(784, 96, 48, 49, '2022-01-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked on division. She worked through a worksheet from her teacher on long-division with three digits and remainders; she then worked through a worksheet I provided comparing division facts and multiplication facts.', '20', '2022-01-12 00:37:22', '2022-01-12 00:37:22'),
(785, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Prep for chapter test: scientific notation, exponent operations.', '79', '2022-01-12 01:05:31', '2022-01-12 01:05:31'),
(786, 34, 80, 59, '2022-01-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Place value exercises.', '70', '2022-01-12 01:05:52', '2022-01-12 01:05:52'),
(787, 60, 73, 67, '2022-01-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed three worksheets: one on addition up to 20, one where she had to label the continents on a world map, and one where she had to match the correct verb tense to the subject in a sentence. Finished reading \"No Jumping on the Bed\". Did a great job with sounding out new vocabulary!', '20', '2022-01-12 03:33:15', '2022-01-12 03:33:15'),
(788, 60, 66, 67, '2022-01-11', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on nines multiplication table by writing it, playing a game with it, and then being quizzed on it.', '20', '2022-01-12 03:33:48', '2022-01-12 03:33:48'),
(789, 34, 45, 46, '2022-01-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Challenge questions on adding and subtraction fractions with unlike denominators.', '75', '2022-01-13 01:07:05', '2022-01-13 01:07:05'),
(790, 38, 56, 57, '2022-01-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I used our time wisely today (as we always do!) to prepare for his upcoming midterm.  Our focus was on that aspect of the exam dealing with solving systems of simultaneous linear equations.  We reviewed the three major solution methods: graphing, substitution, and elimination.  Ian had an opportunity to demonstrate his talents in all three methodologies, and appears quite confident.  We should be able to squeeze in one more session of review before Ian takes the exam.  He is on his way to success!', '50', '2022-01-13 15:55:36', '2022-01-13 15:55:36'),
(791, 44, 45, 46, '2022-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We practiced some conversational Spanish. He asked for help on the positioning of words. We then broke down some song lyrics from the movie Encanto.', '45', '2022-01-14 00:04:50', '2022-01-14 00:04:50'),
(792, 60, 60, 62, '2022-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed for \"Coming for Age\" quiz. Reviewed the plot of the first three chapters of \"Red Scarf Girl\". Did a practice worksheet on finding percentages of numbers and finding what number a percentage is taken of (ex. 5 is 10% of what number). Started a worksheet finding equivalent fractions, decimals, and percentages.', '20', '2022-01-14 01:39:51', '2022-01-14 01:39:51'),
(793, 38, 43, 40, '2022-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mallory has truly arrived as a mathematician, for she has now entered the world of trigonometry.  We made sure not to proceed without the protection of SOHCAHTOA, which Mallory immediately found to be her best friend.  After a barrage of practice problems, Mallory became quite proficient, and her confidence was readily apparent.  My advice to my wonderful student is to stay on the straight path, do not go off on any \"tangents\", and pay heed to all warning \"sines\". :)', '50', '2022-01-14 17:53:01', '2022-01-14 17:53:01'),
(794, 38, 99, 97, '2022-01-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a true pleasure to have a chance to work with Octavio today, a \"GT\" young man with stellar character traits and an unquenchable thirst to learn and grow.  Although I was given the \"heads-up\" that he needed assistance with place values and rounding, it only took a minimal amount of practice before this young man was well on his way to proficiency.  We did not have a real opportunity to address the \"word problems\" issue, but I am certain that Octavio will master that area of concern with limited intervention.  He was a pleasure to work with, and his best quality was that he enjoyed my jokes! He is certainly on his way to success.  Nice to meet you Octavio!', '50', '2022-01-14 18:00:04', '2022-01-14 18:00:04'),
(795, 82, 100, 98, '2022-01-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Polynomials', '54', '2022-01-16 14:13:01', '2022-01-16 14:13:01'),
(796, 38, 74, 71, '2022-01-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I mastered some new vocabulary this evening as it applies to concepts that we have already covered. Consistent / inconsistent  and independent / de[pendent systems of equations are the unfamiliar terms, but the subject of equations pairs that have either one, infinite or no solutions is the familiar concept.  Once we got comfortable with the terms, Timur and I went through examples of each scenario, and Timur felt quite comfortable and confident by the end of the session. He continues to grow in his quantitative skills.  Good work Timur!', '50', '2022-01-17 16:20:09', '2022-01-17 16:20:09'),
(797, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-17', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Converting decimals and fractions.', '79', '2022-01-18 01:45:31', '2022-01-19 01:03:19'),
(798, 60, 75, 72, '2022-01-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Finished worksheet reviewing adding and subtracting three digit numbers with regrouping. Completed a summary worksheet about a short story. Reviewed multiplication as repeated addition. Did a \"Madlib\" type story to review parts of speech.', '20', '2022-01-18 22:21:35', '2022-01-18 22:21:35'),
