(801, 94, 98, 95, '2022-01-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today Mason wanted to learn about dental hygienists and their jobs. We read a book about it and did several comprehension activities. Then, we did a science experiment putting an egg in soda and milk overnight (the eggshell is the tooth) to see whether calcium or sugar is better for teeth. Then, he will brush the eggs to remove stains like he would normal teeth. We learned the different teeth and practiced sounding out difficult words.', '25', '2022-01-19 03:34:16', '2022-01-19 03:34:16'),
(802, 96, 48, 49, '2022-01-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked on a few division problems from her teacher, then continued with worksheets and practice I had prepared.', '20', '2022-01-19 11:46:54', '2022-01-19 11:46:54'),
(803, 34, 45, 46, '2022-01-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reducing fractions before multiplying. Finding common factors.', '75', '2022-01-20 01:02:47', '2022-01-20 01:02:47'),
(804, 38, 56, 57, '2022-01-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I did a final review of his functions material for his upcoming. Although he is confident (which is fantastic), I strongly recommend that he get the many different concepts sorted out in his mind as part of his own study.  The potential for careless mistakes is a force to be reckoned with, and Ian will certainly be able to minimize its influence with some careful review.  I know he can do it!  Best of luck on the exam Ian!', '50', '2022-01-20 15:31:29', '2022-01-20 15:31:29'),
(805, 60, 73, 67, '2022-01-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on basic addition and subtraction worksheets. Read a whole book, \"No Visitors for Bear\". Practiced counting by 2s, 3s, 4s, and 5s.', '20', '2022-01-20 20:23:06', '2022-01-20 20:23:06'),
(806, 38, 43, 40, '2022-01-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Despite Mallory\'s disappointment at her performance on a 3 question trigonometry test, she happily subjected herself to a review of what went wrong. it only  took a few tweaks and some practice to get her back on track, and of course, Mallory maintained her great attitude throughout the entire ordeal.  I am confident that she will quickly recover and resume her journey towards excellence.  You are doing great Mallory!  No doubt about it!', '50', '2022-01-21 16:11:22', '2022-01-21 16:11:22'),
(807, 82, 101, 99, '2022-01-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Solved Problem Handout on Springs and Hook\'s Law', '50', '2022-01-22 11:50:46', '2022-01-22 11:50:46'),
(808, 60, 60, 62, '2022-01-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed chapters 4-6 of Red Scarf Girl for her quiz. Reviewed percentages, decimals, and fractions on Khan Academy.', '20', '2022-01-22 21:41:23', '2022-01-22 21:41:23'),
(809, 60, 75, 72, '2022-01-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced reading comprehension and finding the answers to questions in the text. Practiced spelling words with \"ed\" and \"ing\" and when you should double the last letter. Talked about using quotation marks and read a book using different voices for different characters based off the quotation marks. Practiced multiplication as repeated addition and started learning factors of two.', '20', '2022-01-22 21:47:24', '2022-01-22 21:47:24'),
(810, 38, 74, 71, '2022-01-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Timur did not initially know what material we should cover this evening (and I encouraged him to give that some thought each week prior to our meeting to maximally take advantage of our time together), he made a quick recovery and pulled up some exercises from recent classes.  The focus of these problems was solving equations by substitution. With some guidance, Timur was able to figure out many of the problems, although my hope is that he will put in some review time between sessions in order to achieve more independence. This young man is very bright, and he is more hesitant than he should be to utilize his natural gifts.  The more he will demonstrate his abilities to himself, the less of an issue this will be. I will continue to attempt to lead Timur down the path of self reliance.  Timur can do it!', '50', '2022-01-24 17:28:45', '2022-01-24 17:28:45'),
(811, 94, 45, 46, '2022-01-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In our first tutoring session, we did a quick \"get to know you\" segment. I learned about some things Brendon likes to do and learn about. I shared with him a little about me. We read a book about Minecraft and castles and I had him draw his own castle and write a story about it. He is a very advanced reader so I will work with him on advanced reading comprehension, punctuation and writing.\r\nNext class we will learn about how to take care of cats as he is very excited about getting a kitten in a month.', '35', '2022-01-24 23:03:50', '2022-01-24 23:03:50'),
(812, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Go formative: word problems on working backwards, multiplying and dividing fractions and mixed numbers, and unit sense and unit conversion.', '79', '2022-01-25 00:06:42', '2022-01-25 00:06:42'),
(813, 38, 89, 85, '2022-01-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'After a few weeks break, from which Sarah and I were back in business and ready to resume our assault on probability and statistics.  The material is creeping upwards in its level of difficulty, but that is in no way preventing Sarah from putting in her best effort to absorb and integrate new concepts.  We dealt with relative probabilities today, and even though I also need to really focus to interpret some of the tables, we managed as a team to make significant advances. We plan to take a second stab at the material next week.  Sarah is a pleasure to work with!', '50', '2022-01-25 15:41:29', '2022-01-25 15:41:29'),
(814, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Units of measurement and converting in the U.S. Customary System', '79', '2022-01-26 01:05:26', '2022-01-26 01:05:26'),
(815, 34, 80, 59, '2022-01-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mixed review', '70', '2022-01-26 01:05:42', '2022-01-26 01:05:42'),
(816, 96, 48, 49, '2022-01-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through her homework and an extra worksheet her teacher had provided. Leena also assumed the role of teacher to create additional division problems to work through.', '20', '2022-01-26 01:19:17', '2022-01-26 01:19:17'),
(817, 94, 98, 95, '2022-01-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today Mason wanted to learn about ninjas. We focused on training, routine, and the importance of hard work. We read a book about their history, learned many new words, and we learned about the function of a comma. We did an exercise of adding commas to sentences, which was hard but he caught on. Then, I had him draw a ninja and write a story about it. We learned and identified the parts of a story such as exposition, rising action, climax, falling action and resolution. We applied these parts to his ninja story.', '25', '2022-01-26 03:13:00', '2022-01-26 03:13:00'),
(818, 60, 73, 67, '2022-01-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on math homework with the commutative property and fact families. Did two word problems and another fact family worksheet. Read “If you give a mouse a cookie”', '20', '2022-01-26 04:11:18', '2022-01-26 04:11:18'),
(820, 42, 93, 90, '2022-01-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I worked on finishing a take-home test dealing with mixed operations. He was much more focused and did an excellent job identifying and fixing his mistakes.', '54', '2022-01-27 00:01:17', '2022-01-27 00:01:17'),
(821, 42, 93, 90, '2022-01-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I practiced working on comparing decimals and converting decimals to fractions.  Matthew often rushed through some steps and struggled to explain how to solve problems. He needs to work on listening and not rushing through steps.', '54', '2022-01-27 00:04:47', '2022-01-27 00:04:47'),
(822, 34, 45, 46, '2022-01-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Played No Dice. Brendon beat me by one!', '75', '2022-01-27 01:05:44', '2022-01-27 01:05:44'),
(823, 94, 45, 46, '2022-01-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we went over Brendon\'s Spanish homework. It was an article about different religions and blended families. We emphasized words \"criarse\" and \"también\" and practiced rolling the R. Brendon picked up fast on certain words and I told him to repeat, repeat, repeat! It was a fun read!', '35', '2022-01-27 01:57:51', '2022-01-27 01:57:51'),
(824, 60, 66, 67, '2022-01-25', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on multiplication with 3s and 9s.', '20', '2022-01-27 02:13:36', '2022-01-27 02:13:36'),
(825, 38, 56, 57, '2022-01-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Ian reported that he did not do as well on his recent exam as he would have liked, at least he self reported the reason why such a thing happened:  He did not study enough on his own!   I always emphasize to my students that they cannot rely on the sessions alone to become proficient with the material.  I sense that ian will make the necessary adjustments.  Today\'s highlights included a review of the three major methods to solve linear equations: substitution, linear combinations, and graphing.  Ian is back in the saddle!  He has a lot to look forward to!', '50', '2022-01-27 16:06:56', '2022-01-27 16:06:56'),
(826, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Working backward to solve word problems, work problems, and operations with fractions.', '79', '2022-01-27 20:06:18', '2022-01-27 20:06:18'),
(827, 38, 43, 40, '2022-01-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a day of solid trig review for Mallory and me, with Mallory demonstrating clearly that she knows this stuff! She even shared with me the fact that she is carrying on the tutoring torch to her classmates who have not grasped the concepts as well as Mallory has. Today we solved for missing angles, missing sides, and became proficient at using our calculators to streamline our work.  Mallory continues to make me one proud tutor to have such a wonderful student. Go Mallory!', '50', '2022-01-28 14:07:38', '2022-01-28 14:07:38'),
(828, 60, 60, 62, '2022-01-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed “Red Scarf Girl” chapters 7-9. Looked through math packet and reviewed percentages. Talked about the difference between “What is 5% of a number” and “5 is 5% of what number” and how to calculate them.', '20', '2022-01-29 05:17:30', '2022-01-29 05:17:30'),
(829, 60, 75, 72, '2022-01-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Spent time memorizing 2s times table. Worked on a worksheet and created flash cards. Did a worksheet with calculating change and finding what coins could make up that amount.', '20', '2022-01-29 05:18:19', '2022-01-29 05:18:19'),
(830, 38, 74, 71, '2022-01-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur\'s teacher is giving him plenty of opportunities to improve his skills in modelling word problems with equations and finding their solutions, as well as using the different standard methods to solve simultaneous equations.  No matter what the situation is, Timur is clearly showing that his skill set is improving. I encouraged Timur to spend some private time with each type of situation and focus on the solution method that applies. By \"locking it\" in his mind, recall should become that much easier.  Timur is on the road to success!', '50', '2022-01-31 17:13:49', '2022-01-31 17:13:49'),
(831, 94, 45, 46, '2022-01-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon learned about how to take care of cats. We read several books, practiced paraphrasing, summaries and conclusions. He made an origami cat and wrote a story about him. He successfully identified all of the parts of a story. We did a ninja comma exercise finding where to put commas in sentences and practicing pauses when reading. He taught me about Vietnamese new year this weekend.', '35', '2022-01-31 23:09:39', '2022-01-31 23:09:39'),
(832, 34, 91, 88, '2022-01-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Review of operations with fractions, Nerdle game, and solving one step equations with fractions.', '79', '2022-02-01 00:50:38', '2022-02-01 00:50:38'),
(833, 38, 89, 85, '2022-01-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah is truly on her way to becoming a statistician!  We spent another solid session learning statistical concepts, including frequency tables, dot plots, and their analysis.  When Sarah admitted that she had not seen some of the ideas before, I felt good in that we were learning brand new things. Of course, Sarah continues to learn very quickly, and I think that staying on this topic for awhile would be a good idea. But I did leave it up to her of she wanted to explore other areas of interest.  Sarah will excel in whatever discipline we choose.', '50', '2022-02-01 15:33:01', '2022-02-01 15:33:01'),
