(850, 42, 93, 90, '2022-02-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I continued to work on adding and subtracting fractions. Matthew struggled to focus for much of our session and required a lot of re-direction.', '54', '2022-02-06 20:54:01', '2022-02-06 20:54:01'),
(851, 42, 93, 90, '2022-02-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I went over his mistakes on a take-home test. Most of his mistakes were made by writing down his answers and re-copying them on his second and third attempts. I recommended printing out a copy of his test going forward.', '54', '2022-02-06 20:58:38', '2022-02-06 20:58:38'),
(852, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, his mom asked me to switch Spanish and English because he has a Spanish assessment coming up. So we worked on Spanish comprehension by watching several videos and answering questions. I gave him a lesson on conjugating normal verbs (-ar and -er). We repeated difficult vocabulary words from the previous classes. I am happy with how he is progressing.', '35', '2022-02-07 23:08:06', '2022-02-07 23:08:06'),
(853, 96, 48, 49, '2022-02-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through a worksheet on two-digit multiplication, another on division, and a third on math facts from her teachers.', '20', '2022-02-08 11:54:22', '2022-02-08 11:54:22'),
(854, 38, 89, 85, '2022-02-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Despite being tired, Sarah called forth all of her energy to survive another session of introductory statistics.  Today\'s focus was on comparing data displays and data distributions, and Sarah is rapidly becoming a statistics expert.  I am truly impressed with her willingness to attempt all problems, and learns from her mistakes. Sarah continues to build a strong inventory of skills that will serve her well next year. great job Sarah!', '50', '2022-02-08 21:48:23', '2022-02-08 21:48:23'),
(855, 34, 80, 59, '2022-02-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Spiral homework, extra practice on place value, and learned to play nerdle.', '70', '2022-02-09 00:03:40', '2022-02-09 00:03:40'),
(856, 34, 91, 88, '2022-02-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Markus only: reviewed exponent and extra practice on solving for a variable with rational coefficients. Set up Prodigy account.', '79', '2022-02-09 00:04:17', '2022-02-09 00:04:17'),
(857, 94, 98, 95, '2022-02-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Mason wanted to learn about the piano. We read a book all about pianos and music in general. We did several critical thinking exercises and Mason learned many new words. I showed him a video on the positive effect that music has on the brain and we made inferences about other things that are good for the brain. Mason was very excited to talk about music. We read a reading comprehension story about the history of pianos and answered multiple choice questions. He is struggling with less words when we are reading and I am very happy to see him excited about learning.', '25', '2022-02-09 00:05:31', '2022-02-09 00:05:31'),
(858, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon wanted to learn about robots, specifically medical robots. This is right up my ally! We read a book about robots in medicine, watched a few quick videos, and practiced critical thinking and inference skills. We filled out a story chart and made predictions as to what could happen if robots replace humans in medicine. I was so impressed by his knowledge and interest! He then drew his own robot and wrote a story (following the story rollercoaster of background, rising action, climax, falling action, and resolution). He did a great job today and his passion for science is evident!', '35', '2022-02-09 00:09:34', '2022-02-09 00:09:34'),
(859, 60, 66, 67, '2022-02-08', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed multiplication of 3s, 5s, and 9s. Took a quiz. Quick practice of multiplication by 2s.', '20', '2022-02-09 04:29:19', '2022-02-09 04:29:19'),
(860, 60, 73, 67, '2022-02-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on word problems (identifying the operation and using units). Learned about place value for tens and ones and did a practice worksheet. Read \"If You Give a Pig a Pancake\". Completed a \"correct the sentence\" worksheet with incorrect capitalization and/or word order.', '20', '2022-02-09 04:30:30', '2022-02-09 04:30:30'),
(861, 96, 48, 49, '2022-02-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through two worksheets of multiplication and division problems from her teacher. We worked on drawing models and writing equations for these problems.', '20', '2022-02-09 12:22:10', '2022-02-09 12:22:10'),
(862, 42, 93, 90, '2022-02-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew missed out on learning how to multiply decimals in class today, so we went over the process together and did several practice problems. He is a little hesitant still about implementing strategies to help him work with his learning difference, but we had a good talk about why and I think he\'s beginning to understand. Matthew often engages in negative self-talk around his intelligence and I\'m trying hard to stop and re-direct him.', '54', '2022-02-09 22:00:55', '2022-02-09 22:00:55'),
(863, 34, 91, 88, '2022-02-09', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: learned more exponent rules. Nerdle and nonogram\r\nTyler: worked out finding solutions to help him remember to do his homework, set up calendar, completed missing homework assignment, Nerdle.', '79', '2022-02-10 00:10:00', '2022-02-10 00:10:00'),
(864, 34, 45, 46, '2022-02-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Nerdle and mini Nerdle.', '75', '2022-02-10 01:03:18', '2022-02-10 01:03:18'),
(865, 82, 94, 91, '2022-02-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics: Solved problems on potential energy, momentum and kinetic energy', '60', '2022-02-10 01:59:00', '2022-02-10 01:59:00'),
(866, 38, 56, 57, '2022-02-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian reported the disappointing news that he did not perform well on his recent exam.  Sequences, regressions and solving equations seemed to be skills that Ian had added to his inventory. We will have to put our heads together to figure out the disconnect between the tutoring sessions and the exam.  Ian said that maybe it is test anxiety, but that is the first I have heard him mention that. I know that he is trying his best and will continue to do so.  Keep plugging Ian!', '50', '2022-02-10 19:46:40', '2022-02-10 19:46:40'),
(867, 60, 60, 62, '2022-02-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed “Red Scarf Girl” chapters 13-17. Worked on math homework which was dividing fractions and word problems for dividing fractions. Talked about why you can make improper fractions by multiplying g the constant by the denominator and adding the numerator.', '20', '2022-02-11 17:07:14', '2022-02-11 17:07:14'),
(868, 82, 100, 98, '2022-02-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Polynomials', '54', '2022-02-12 17:16:28', '2022-02-12 17:16:28'),
(869, 34, 91, 88, '2022-02-12', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Reviewed homework on exponents (power to a power). Had to redo. Got another assignment on same topic, plus Prodigy work.\r\nTyler: Reviewed homework and continues with ratios.', '79', '2022-02-12 20:27:09', '2022-02-12 20:27:09');
INSERT INTO `timesheets` (`timesheet_id`, `tutor_id`, `student_id`, `user_id`, `date`, `time`, `duration`, `duration2`, `description`, `hourly_pay_rate`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(870, 60, 75, 72, '2022-02-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed 2s time tables. Worked on memorizing 3s times table.', '20', '2022-02-12 20:49:43', '2022-02-12 20:49:43'),
(871, 38, 43, 40, '2022-02-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'After our successful session last week with the Law of Sines, Mallory and I carried that momentum successfully through today\'s session with the Law of Cosines.  I want to thank my dear student again for our collaboration in making these two laws clearer than they have ever been before.  Mallory, of course, mastered the ability to distinguish the situations that require the application of each law,  Great job Mallory.  Have a great weekend!', '50', '2022-02-13 20:36:49', '2022-02-13 20:36:49'),
(872, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I helped Brendon work through his Spanish homework on Ser vs. Estar. I taught him a mnemonic device for remembering when to use both (Ser=DOCTOR and Estar=PLACE). Then, we practiced the conjugations (present). We put together the teachings to do the homework. He caught on fast and wrote down the mnemonic so he can remember it and use it in the future.', '35', '2022-02-14 02:08:44', '2022-02-14 02:08:44'),
(873, 38, 74, 71, '2022-02-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur returned from his week off ready to go.  The time off was a good refresh for this sharp young man, and those benefits came through clearly in our work this evening on solving simultaneous inequalities.  With only some indirect guidance, Timur was able to set up the problems and come up with the required solutions.  He continues to integrate new information, solidify his skills, and climb the learning curve. Timur is doing great!', '50', '2022-02-14 15:04:39', '2022-02-14 15:04:39'),
(874, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Per request from Brendon\'s mother, we did the first half completing a Spanish homework. Then, I had him read a short book about soccer (what he wanted to learn about). We learned about first person, second person, and third person. I had him draw a soccer ball and invent a story of if he were the soccer ball to practice first person. We also did a comma exercise. He is doing a great job!', '35', '2022-02-14 23:09:23', '2022-02-14 23:09:23'),
(875, 38, 89, 85, '2022-02-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah felt well rested this week, and that gave her the energy to thrive in another tutoring session on statistics.  Today\'s focus was \"comparing data distributions\", and after we took the time to really dissect and understand the various presentation methods, Sarah became quite skilled at answering the questions being asked.  She is such a bright young lady, and the time investment she is making now will pay great dividends in her future academic pursuits.  Wonderful job Sarah!', '50', '2022-02-15 14:23:57', '2022-02-15 14:23:57'),
(876, 94, 98, 95, '2022-02-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Mason wanted to learn about tennis. We read a book about tennis and practiced sounding out words and identifying where the commas go in each sentence. We did an exercise on commas and how to pause when reading. We read several sentences and decided where the commas should go in each one. We also learned about perspectives and made a first person story being a ball. Mason was a little tired today, but he powered through and got into the lesson towards the end!', '25', '2022-02-15 22:59:03', '2022-02-15 22:59:03'),
(877, 96, 48, 49, '2022-02-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through two worksheets from her teacher on fractions. We then went back and forth creating fractions on whiteboards. We also played some of a computer game Leena uses on division and multiplication.', '20', '2022-02-15 23:07:05', '2022-02-15 23:07:05'),
(878, 34, 95, 88, '2022-02-15', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Reviewed exponents and studied operations with fractions and decimals\r\nTyler: reviewed unit rates and studies two step equations', '79', '2022-02-16 00:05:43', '2022-02-16 00:05:43'),
(879, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we reviewed the difference between \"Ser\" and \"Estar\", going over the mnemonics that I taught him yesterday. He knows, repite, repite, repite (repeat, repeat, repeat!). We worked on conjugations of ser and estar and I helped him with his homework on this topic.', '35', '2022-02-16 01:22:14', '2022-02-16 01:22:14'),
(880, 34, 80, 59, '2022-02-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'IXL practice in four topics', '70', '2022-02-17 00:05:21', '2022-02-17 00:05:21'),
(881, 34, 91, 88, '2022-02-16', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Reviewed operations with fractions and decimals. Tried to see if focus would be better while eating simultaneously.\r\nTyler: Solving 2 step equations review.', '79', '2022-02-17 00:06:08', '2022-02-17 00:06:08'),
(882, 34, 45, 46, '2022-02-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Nonograms 5x5 and started 10x10', '75', '2022-02-17 01:06:59', '2022-02-17 01:06:59'),
(883, 82, 102, 100, '2022-02-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Solving Polynomials', '45', '2022-02-17 02:23:55', '2022-02-17 02:23:55'),
(884, 38, 56, 57, '2022-02-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Exponential growth and decay was the \"dinner special\" for Ian and me today, and I am quite impressed with how well Ian is absorbing and applying these rather conceptually difficult topics.  We worked through several problems, and after just a few iterations, Ian was able to develop the formula to describe the  exponential situation. We even extended the applications to per cent growth and decay, and Ian made a masterful transition.  One extra kudo to ian  -  He is ALWAYS on time!  Thank you Ian!', '50', '2022-02-17 15:15:50', '2022-02-17 15:15:50'),
(885, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we worked on his Spanish listening assignment. I taught him a little bit about Lima, Peru and we also learned the Spanish accent and \"vosotros\". He is doing great at remembering words he learned in previous sessions.', '35', '2022-02-17 23:49:46', '2022-02-17 23:49:46'),
(886, 60, 60, 62, '2022-02-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on English \"Coming of Age\" essay about \"Red Scarf Girl\" by creating an outline of everything that she would include.', '20', '2022-02-18 04:19:38', '2022-02-18 04:19:38'),
(887, 60, 75, 72, '2022-02-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed multiplication of 3s. Practiced subtraction word problems with showing work. Reading comprehension worksheet about a fiction story.', '20', '2022-02-19 03:07:31', '2022-02-19 03:07:31'),
(888, 34, 91, 88, '2022-02-19', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Worked on operations with fractions. Memorized the steps and did hand motions to go along with the steps.\r\nTyler: Proportions.', '79', '2022-02-19 16:46:34', '2022-02-19 16:46:34'),
(889, 38, 43, 40, '2022-02-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was quite an interesting and challenging set of topics that Mallory and I spent our time on today.  Actually, the cross sectional areas piece was more on the interesting side, while the rotations in 2-D space is a topic I have never favored. Nevertheless, the two of us put our heads together and were able to come out on top in both instances.  Between her sports practices and her academic pursuits, Mallory is successfully juggling the various facets of her life, and seems to be thriving in all aspects.  Mallory is super!', '50', '2022-02-20 03:18:58', '2022-02-20 03:18:58'),
(890, 82, 94, 91, '2022-02-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'AP Physics', '60', '2022-02-22 03:32:43', '2022-02-22 03:32:43'),
(891, 38, 89, 85, '2022-02-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I continued on our tour of statistics today, although we are considering taking a brief pause next week to explore other topics.  Sarah is doing great, and has assured me that she is fine with the subject matter. I just want to be sensitive that our goal is to prepare for next year, and she may want to expand our horizons.  She tells me that she is working on systems of equations in school, so I may look to challenge Sarah in that area a bit.  Sarah is a model student with wonderful character traits.  It is a pleasure to work with her!', '50', '2022-02-22 17:45:21', '2022-02-22 17:45:21'),
(892, 96, 48, 49, '2022-02-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I played division and simple math facts games from Math Playground, as well as going through different fractions games on Education.com.', '20', '2022-02-22 22:58:28', '2022-02-22 22:58:28'),
(893, 34, 80, 59, '2022-02-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Homework completed and taught Emme how to play nonograms.', '70', '2022-02-23 00:02:27', '2022-02-23 00:02:27'),
(894, 34, 91, 88, '2022-02-22', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Nerdle, reviewed operations with fractions homework, and I assigned it again.\r\nTyler: Discussed why his homework isn\'t getting done/low quality, re-did it, and he got the same topic for homework again, on proportions.', '79', '2022-02-23 00:03:35', '2022-02-23 00:03:35'),
(895, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we did a Spanish lesson about \"el clima\" the weather, and parts of the body. We made up gestures for the weather and practiced weather dances to promote word association and better retention of words. We read a book about the weather in Spanish and practiced pronunciation.', '35', '2022-02-23 02:01:36', '2022-02-23 02:01:36'),
(896, 94, 98, 95, '2022-02-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Mason wanted to learn about computers. We read a book about computers and then a story about the negatives of technology. We did a reading comprehension and practiced summarizing. We did a mini-lesson about ethics for kids and the pros/cons of technology. He practiced word comprehension, summarizing, commas, and critical thinking.', '25', '2022-02-23 02:03:33', '2022-02-23 02:03:33'),
(897, 42, 93, 90, '2022-02-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew is keeping up well with his classwork on decimals, but mentioned that he is struggling with long division. We went over a few problems together, but Matthew struggled to complete problems without help. I am going to investigate other strategies to help him.', '54', '2022-02-23 21:53:46', '2022-02-23 21:53:46'),
(898, 42, 93, 90, '2022-02-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I tried the grid method for long division which I think was helpful for him in organizing and comprehending problems. He was able to successfully complete several problems on his own and seemed much more confident at the end of the lesson.', '54', '2022-02-23 21:58:46', '2022-02-23 21:58:46'),
(899, 34, 91, 88, '2022-02-23', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Nerdle, Mighty Mind, and operations with fractions. Highlighted the operations. There is improvement!\r\nTyler: Similar Figures', '79', '2022-02-24 00:14:19', '2022-02-24 00:14:19'),
(900, 34, 45, 46, '2022-02-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Nonograms 10x10', '75', '2022-02-24 01:00:52', '2022-02-24 01:00:52'),
(901, 82, 101, 99, '2022-02-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics', '50', '2022-02-24 12:48:28', '2022-02-24 12:48:28'),
(902, 82, 101, 99, '2022-02-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics-Conservation of Momentum', '50', '2022-02-24 12:48:57', '2022-02-24 12:48:57'),
(903, 82, 102, 100, '2022-02-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Precalculus-Solving High Order Equations', '45', '2022-02-24 12:50:06', '2022-02-24 12:50:06'),
(904, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We worked on Brendon\'s Spanish homework and practiced feminine vs. masculine, singlular vs. plural, ser vs. estar, and conjugations. He was catching on and I started him on the habit of writing down new words which will take him far.', '35', '2022-02-24 23:57:43', '2022-02-24 23:57:43'),
(905, 60, 73, 67, '2022-02-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed four addition and subtraction word problems that required her to identify which operation she should us. Read \"If You Take a Mouse to School\" and then reviewed days of the week in order.', '20', '2022-02-25 05:43:49', '2022-02-25 05:43:49'),
(906, 60, 66, 67, '2022-02-23', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed multiplication with a focus on 3s, 6s, 7s, 8s, and 12s.', '20', '2022-02-25 05:44:17', '2022-02-25 05:44:17'),
(907, 60, 60, 62, '2022-02-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Checked through Canvas. Talked about long division and the different ways you can express a remainder (just saying remainder of x, putting it as a fraction over the divisor, or making it a decimal). Did practice on Khan Academy.', '20', '2022-02-25 05:45:12', '2022-02-25 05:45:12'),
(908, 38, 43, 40, '2022-02-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Many of my students have been dealing with dilations recently. and Mallory has become a welcome member of the club.  Our focus today was on finding the area and volume of such dilations, and Mallory put it all together to become quite proficient at the task. Our sessions are so upbeat and fun. thanks to Mallory\'s wonderful character and personality.  She remains a true pleasure to work with.', '50', '2022-02-25 19:45:36', '2022-02-25 19:45:36'),
(909, 82, 46, 47, '2022-02-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Precalculus-Solved Problems', '45', '2022-02-26 02:34:45', '2022-02-26 02:34:45'),
(910, 60, 75, 72, '2022-02-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Learned about perimeter and worked on 6 examples showing all work. Read a story about a cat wanting to be different animals and answered comprehension questions.', '20', '2022-02-27 16:00:10', '2022-02-27 16:00:10'),
(911, 94, 45, 46, '2022-02-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today Brendon wanted to learn about satellites because he is very interested in the space race. I made it into a lesson about critical thinking skills and reading comprehension. We read two books about satellites and interconnectivity. He was so excited talking about it. We delved deeper into reading comprehension questions about who benefits from it, who holds the power, pros/cons of the internet, and the motivations behind the space race. He practiced sounding out difficult words and slowing down a bit when he reads. Brendon is so bright and lights up when talking about things he loves!', '35', '2022-02-28 23:05:11', '2022-02-28 23:05:11'),
(912, 60, 75, 72, '2022-02-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed multiplication of 2s and 3s. Reviewed perimeter and talked about how it can be calculated with multiplication for regular shapes. Learned 4s time table.', '20', '2022-03-01 03:18:43', '2022-03-01 03:18:43'),
(914, 34, 80, 59, '2022-03-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed homework - mixed review.', '70', '2022-03-02 00:12:47', '2022-03-02 00:12:47'),
(915, 34, 95, 88, '2022-03-01', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Reviewed homework on operations with fractions. Began Hand-on-Algebra curriculum.\r\nTyler: Completed the homework that he didn\'t do at home on proportions. Continued with proportions.', '79', '2022-03-02 00:13:45', '2022-03-02 00:13:45'),
(916, 94, 98, 95, '2022-03-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we did a lesson about cars. We read a book, practicing context clues. I had him do fill in the blank exercises with synonyms to figure out words he didn\'t know with context clues. After the book, I had him do a creative writing exercise about designing his own car. We practiced critical thinking skills by thinking of pros and cons of innovations and how that effects safety. Masons reading has improved significantly since the beginning and I see him using skills on his own of sounding out words and using root words to figure out word meanings.', '25', '2022-03-02 01:12:10', '2022-03-02 01:12:10'),
(917, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we worked together on Brendon\'s Spanish homework, reviewing ser vs. estar. He has been using the mnemonic device that I taught him (DOCTOR & PLACE) to figure out whether or not to use ser vs. estar. He was having trouble figuring out for which word to conjugate so I taught him how I like to think of it (singular vs. plural) and since then, he hasn\'t gotten that mixed up. I showed him my roomate\'s cat because he wanted to be on camera and I taught him words in Spanish in the theme of \"how to take care of a cat\". We practiced figuring out words in Spanish using what we know about other words.', '35', '2022-03-02 01:16:54', '2022-03-02 01:16:54'),
(918, 96, 48, 49, '2022-03-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through some fractions worksheets from her teacher with computer and whiteboard visual assistance. We also played some of her class computer games on fractions and operations.', '20', '2022-03-02 13:37:51', '2022-03-02 13:37:51'),
(919, 42, 103, 101, '2022-03-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Susanna and I went over her reading homework for school before starting on \"Horton Hatches an Egg.\" Susanna is super bright and has already picked up strategies for decoding difficult words. She has very high reading comprehension even if she struggles with some of the mechanics of reading.', '54', '2022-03-02 22:12:04', '2022-03-02 22:12:04'),
(920, 42, 93, 90, '2022-03-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I looked at dividing 3 digit numbers by 2 digit numbers using the grid method. He was initially nervous and resistant to trying, but once we slowed down and took a breath, he started to understand. He is much more confident about division in general now and I\'m hoping that confidence will continue to grow.', '54', '2022-03-02 22:15:44', '2022-03-02 22:15:44'),
(921, 34, 45, 46, '2022-03-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Homework on negative numbers. Reviewed order of operations. Played No Dice.', '75', '2022-03-03 01:31:06', '2022-03-03 01:31:06'),
(922, 60, 73, 67, '2022-03-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Finished up addition and subtraction word problems that required operation identification. Read \"Froggy Plays T-Ball\".', '20', '2022-03-03 04:15:31', '2022-03-03 04:15:31'),
(924, 38, 56, 57, '2022-03-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian gave a great effort this evening on a practice test for an actual exam that he has tomorrow.  Sequences and simplifying radicals were among the highlights, and Ian is handling such problems with much more ease that I have seen recently.  I was very encouraged and optimistic that he will be able be able to carry that growth to similar performance on the actual test.  Ian can do it! He WILL do it!', '50', '2022-03-03 16:57:03', '2022-03-03 16:57:03'),
(925, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, I gave Brendon a lesson on \"present progressive\" ex. I am running, she is teaching. We did example questions and he wrote down the new words/words he didn\'t know in his notebook.', '35', '2022-03-04 01:05:12', '2022-03-04 01:05:12'),
(926, 34, 95, 88, '2022-03-06', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Continued with hands on algebra, Lesson 5.\r\nTyler: Reviewed proportions and began fractions, decimals, percents', '79', '2022-03-06 15:46:03', '2022-03-06 15:46:03'),
