(930, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we did a lesson on the Space Race. We learned about bias, practiced perspectives, context clues, critical thinking and making predictions. We read a book on the space race, thought of examples of biases in the book, and I had him invent his own space invention. I then asked him reflection questions such as, what are the potential problems with this invention and how can it help people? Brendon is so gifted in understanding difficult readings and history. Sometimes, I feel like he is teaching me-- Haha!', '35', '2022-03-07 23:00:57', '2022-03-07 23:00:57'),
(931, 38, 89, 85, '2022-03-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I returned to statistics this week, as we have decided that we will alternate between this very broad subject and other important topics,  Today\'s highlights included mean, median, and mode, with Sarah quickly becoming proficient at applying the concepts.  Every time we start a session, I have a \"rush\" of being impressed with this young lady, as our whole tutoring engagement is based on her desire to enrich her skills in advance of entering a more advanced level math course next year.  Hats off to Sarah!', '50', '2022-03-08 16:05:55', '2022-03-08 16:05:55'),
(932, 94, 98, 95, '2022-03-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we did a lesson on Pokemon. We read a book and we learned words such as mentor, inspire, and role model. He said that his role model and mentor was his mom because \"she is like a teacher\", which I thought was very sweet. I had him design his own Pokemon and practice describing words. He was very excited to show me his pokemon toys and I thought it was funny that he did class from his fort. His reading skills have improved and I now only have to help him with one word per paragraph, instead of one word every two sentences like in the beginning. He is doing great!', '25', '2022-03-09 00:07:58', '2022-03-09 00:07:58'),
(933, 34, 91, 88, '2022-03-08', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Lesson 5 from Hands on Algebra. Played No Dice with both boys.\r\nTyler: Fractions, decimals, and percents.', '79', '2022-03-09 00:11:20', '2022-03-09 00:11:20'),
(934, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, for Spanish class, we read a book about inventions. He got a journal per my recommendation, which I am very proud of him for. I have him write down every new word and every word he doesn\'t know in there. I want him to take these skills with him. We learned lots of new words from the book. Then, I had him make an invention in Spanish from the inventions he learned about. We learned a list of adjectives in Spanish, and I had him describe his invention using these new adjectives.', '35', '2022-03-09 00:12:08', '2022-03-09 00:12:08'),
(935, 96, 48, 49, '2022-03-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I played some of her math games through MathPlayground and Prodigy for addition and subtraction, as well as fractions. We also worked through some of the games on fractions from Education.com.', '20', '2022-03-09 01:39:22', '2022-03-09 01:39:22'),
(936, 60, 75, 72, '2022-03-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on school homework. Practiced multiplication with 3s and 4s.', '20', '2022-03-09 06:22:15', '2022-03-09 06:22:15'),
(937, 38, 74, 71, '2022-03-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In a rare weekday session, Timur demonstrated his thirst for learning by making up for a previously missed session.  The topic was quite interesting this evening, and Timur learned, integrated and applied the concepts like the pro that he is.  More specifically, we dealt with recursive and explicit functions to describe sequences, as well as specified the domain and range.  Timur may not always fully understand new topics while in class, but with only minimal guidance and support, he puts it all together in our sessions - without fail.  What a bright young man my student is!', '50', '2022-03-09 22:01:14', '2022-03-09 22:01:14'),
(938, 42, 103, 101, '2022-03-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Susanna and I finished reading \"Horton Hatches the Egg\" and went over the rules for igh, ough, soft c, and hard c sounds. She made progress recognizing the patterns and was undaunted by longer words.', '54', '2022-03-09 22:03:51', '2022-03-09 22:03:51'),
(939, 42, 93, 90, '2022-03-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew began working on dividing decimals in school this week and was feeling overwhelmed by the method his teacher used. We slowed down, and I showed him how to use our grid method for decimals. He grasped this method quickly and was able to complete several problems without help.', '54', '2022-03-09 22:08:58', '2022-03-09 22:08:58'),
(940, 34, 91, 88, '2022-03-09', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Building with Ideal Box, Lesson 7 in Hands on Algebra. 100% on homework!\r\nTyler: Building with Ideal Box. Checked homework - Tyler shut down completely when we were doing corrections and spent the majority of class with his head down on the desk, covering himself with his hood. I had asked him to explain how he was (correctly) converting 45% to 0.45 and when he was unable to explain, I tried guiding him through it, but he shut down.', '79', '2022-03-10 01:01:56', '2022-03-10 01:01:56'),
