(951, 38, 74, 71, '2022-03-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'What a treat to have two sessions in one week with my dear student Timur. And I was not disappointed in the least, as Timur cam ready to learn...and learn he did!  We focused on arithmetic and geometric sequences, with special attention given to recursive and explicit formulas.  Even when we finish his assigned work before the end of the session, Timur is more than happy to work through some additional applications, knowing that he will have his skill base further solidified.  Great work Timur!', '50', '2022-03-14 15:58:00', '2022-03-14 15:58:00'),
(952, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We worked on adverbs in Spanish, then I helped him with his homework putting together adverbs, adjectives, and conjugations of verbs. He has great speaking skills!', '35', '2022-03-14 22:03:45', '2022-03-14 22:03:45'),
(953, 60, 75, 72, '2022-03-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Learned 5s times table and reviewed 2s-5s by playing games.', '20', '2022-03-15 14:18:44', '2022-03-15 14:18:44'),
(954, 38, 89, 85, '2022-03-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In an effort to keep my extremely bright student Sarah challenged, I extrapolated from a theoretical topic that she will cover before year end to apply it to real world situations. Sarah has had some exposure to the Pythagorean Theorem, and will cover it in more depth in the coming months. I quickly reviewed the basics with her, and then found some 2D and 3D applications for us to work on.  Sarah rose to the occasion and did a wonderful job.  She is a math magnet!   I look forward to keeping this young lady on her toes (at least sometimes!) in future sessions.', '50', '2022-03-15 15:01:28', '2022-03-15 15:01:28'),
(955, 42, 103, 101, '2022-03-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Susanna had a difficult day at school, so we spent the first part of her session decompressing before starting a new book \"The Isle of Me.\"', '54', '2022-03-15 15:04:08', '2022-03-15 15:04:08'),
(956, 42, 104, 102, '2022-03-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I assessed Caden\'s reading and writing abilities and discussed his interests and general likes and dislikes about school. His comprehension is strong, but needs help with fluency and expression.', '54', '2022-03-15 15:08:43', '2022-03-15 15:08:43'),
(957, 96, 48, 49, '2022-03-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I completed two homework worksheets she had received from her teacher. We then completed a review that I had prepared, with fraction, division, and multiplication problems.', '20', '2022-03-15 22:09:41', '2022-03-15 22:09:41'),
(958, 34, 95, 88, '2022-03-15', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Continued with Hands on Equations, lessons 10 and 11\r\nTyler: Reviewed homework on percents, and completed a 10x10 nonogram', '79', '2022-03-15 22:27:59', '2022-03-15 22:27:59'),
(959, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon wanted to learn about science in Antarctica. We read a book about Antarctica and the research projects going on there. We learned many vocab words, practiced making inferences, adjectives, critical thinking, and comparing and contrasting. I had him write a letter practicing perspective, writing to Santa about how he is now his neighbor and telling him all about life there. He has amazing critical thinking skills and is very gifted in science.', '35', '2022-03-15 23:31:31', '2022-03-15 23:31:31'),
(960, 94, 98, 95, '2022-03-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we read a book about geography and learned about sorting into continent, country, and city. We learned about arctic animals and did a worksheet on adjectives, describing words. I had him write a letter home to mom explaining what life was like living in another continent. We practiced formatting a letter and introductions and closing statements. Mason was very interested and engaged!', '25', '2022-03-15 23:33:50', '2022-03-15 23:33:50'),
(961, 34, 91, 88, '2022-03-16', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Lessons 12 and 13 in Hands-on-Algebra\r\nTyler: Homework on percents was mostly incorrect. Reviewed and redid.', '79', '2022-03-16 23:19:59', '2022-03-16 23:19:59'),
(962, 60, 73, 67, '2022-03-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed place value. Learned how to add two, two-digit numbers without regrouping. Introduced how to add a three digit and two digit number as well as a basic introduction to regrouping. Read the first story in \"Anna\'s Adventures\".', '20', '2022-03-17 02:09:53', '2022-03-17 02:09:53'),
(963, 60, 66, 67, '2022-03-16', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed multiplication by playing two board games.', '20', '2022-03-17 02:10:31', '2022-03-17 02:10:31'),
(964, 38, 56, 57, '2022-03-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although we did not review the fundamentals of public speaking, Ian and I did prepare him for a one minute presentation he will be giving on a sample regression scenario,  We had a lot of fun getting it together, and I am confident that Ian will deserve a standing ovation.  We prepared bullet points and some explanation, which is about all we could squeeze in to sixty seconds.  It is exciting for me as the tutor to see Ian \"put it all together\" in this way.  Ian is definitely \"putting it all together:\'!', '50', '2022-03-17 16:04:02', '2022-03-17 16:04:02'),
(965, 82, 68, 69, '2022-03-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics C problem sheet.  Faraday\'s law applications', '50', '2022-03-21 13:01:18', '2022-03-21 13:01:18'),
(966, 38, 74, 71, '2022-03-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timir is amazing!  He may seem as if he struggles sometimes in our sessions, and he may seem as if he\'s tired (he shared his weekend and summer sleep schedules with me, and it would not be surprising if he IS tired). But bottom line, he tells me is carrying a 92 average in class.  So whatever he is doing, it is working! And even if all of those symptoms seemed to be present in our recent review of recursive and explicit formulas form geometric sequences, I defer to success. So keep it up Timur.  Your results speak for themselves!', '50', '2022-03-21 19:01:32', '2022-03-21 19:01:32'),
(967, 34, 95, 88, '2022-03-18', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Continued with Hands on Algebra\r\nTyler: Worked outside measuring and calculating volume of cylinders and rectangular prisms, with unit conversions of inches to feet to yards.', '79', '2022-03-22 01:43:10', '2022-03-22 01:43:10'),
(968, 38, 89, 85, '2022-03-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I returned to statistics today, after having spent last week \"away from base\".  Today\'s highlights included standard deviation and interquartile range, with Sarah even learning how to do a manual SD calculation. And I was so happy that my super student was well rested for the session!  Thank you Sarah for the continued opportunity to be inspired by your hard work. And most of all, thank you for clarifying what a (a Mexican dish?) is.  Now I can\'t remember what it was called.  Sarah, please help!', '50', '2022-03-22 14:07:37', '2022-03-22 14:07:37'),
(969, 94, 98, 95, '2022-03-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we learned about electric cars. We did an ESL reading with lots of difficult vocab words such as \"advantage\", \"disadvantage\", and \"rely on\". We discussed cost/benefits and critical thinking. We answered reading comprehension questions that involved summarizing and main ideas of each paragraph. I had Mason design his own electric car and write about it, presenting to me a summary like we practiced from the reading. He did a great job and stayed engaged!', '25', '2022-03-22 21:52:19', '2022-03-22 21:52:19'),
(970, 96, 48, 49, '2022-03-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through two worksheets from her teacher, one on fraction word problems and another on fractions with a number line. We then played review games on fractions and addition/subtraction.', '20', '2022-03-22 22:00:16', '2022-03-22 22:00:16'),
(971, 34, 80, 59, '2022-03-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Homework on dividing mixed numbers by mixed numbers.', '70', '2022-03-22 23:04:27', '2022-03-22 23:04:27'),
