(976, 42, 104, 102, '2022-03-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I began reading \"Outcasts United.\" He was pretty tired during the lesson and struggled to stay focused. I\'m noticing many deficits in his understanding of phonics and will need to improve his understanding of certain vowel sounds.', '54', '2022-03-24 13:53:06', '2022-03-24 13:53:06'),
(977, 42, 93, 90, '2022-03-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew had a test coming up on decimals, so we reviewed multiplying and dividing decimals in preparation. He is increasingly confident and is more willing to write down his work, leading to fewer mistakes.', '54', '2022-03-24 13:55:45', '2022-03-24 13:55:45'),
(978, 42, 93, 90, '2022-03-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew is about to begin a new unit, so we looked over the concept of the Order of Operations and complex, multi-step math problems. Matthew excelled with this new concept and quickly found and fixed his few mistakes.', '54', '2022-03-24 13:57:26', '2022-03-24 13:57:26'),
(979, 38, 56, 57, '2022-03-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian shared with me that he did exceedingly well in his one-minute regression presentation last week, and I am so proud of him.  He even had tom put together a written summary of the analysis, and \"set the house on fire\" with a 13 out 0f 14 on that.  Great work Ian!  Today, as Ian did not have any specific assignments, we took the opportunity to enrich his grasp of regression concepts through a \"from the ground up \" review.  It went quite well, reinforcing my perception that Ian continues his ascension of the learning curve, Go Ian! Here\'s to you: Spider-Man, Spider-Man, Does whatever a spider can. Spins a web, any size, Catches thieves just like flies. Look Out!', '50', '2022-03-24 14:43:38', '2022-03-24 14:43:38'),
(980, 82, 102, 100, '2022-03-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Math-Solving problems', '45', '2022-03-25 01:17:23', '2022-03-25 01:17:23'),
(981, 38, 74, 71, '2022-03-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur has an exam coming up on Tuesday that will cover arithmetic and geometric sequences, including their recursive and explicit formulas, so we used the session to review and practice.  The \"refresh\" served its purpose well, as Timur may not have seen a comprehensive look at the topic in a while.  By the end of the session, he was demonstrating his proficiency.  I am confident he will keep up his excellent performance to date in the class.', '50', '2022-03-28 14:37:03', '2022-03-28 14:37:03'),
(982, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon had Spring Break last week, so we picked up where we left off. We learned about rockets and space exploration per Brendon\'s request. With that, we practiced commas, summarizing, critical thinking, and creative writing . He wrote a story about an alien encounter and practiced evoking the 5 senses through his writing. He is very gifted in writing!', '35', '2022-03-28 21:55:29', '2022-03-28 21:55:29'),
(983, 60, 73, 67, '2022-03-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Learned about how to add with regrouping and completed a worksheet. Read the second story in \"Anna\'s Adventures\".', '20', '2022-03-29 03:48:40', '2022-03-29 03:48:40'),
