(987, 60, 75, 72, '2022-03-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed multiplication for 2-5s. Did additional practice for 3s and 5s. Completed reading comprehension worksheet about the Origin of Chinese Zodiacs.', '20', '2022-03-29 03:56:49', '2022-03-29 03:56:49'),
(988, 38, 89, 85, '2022-03-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'The earth shakes and trees topple when Sarah studies mathematics!  That\'s exactly what happened today right outside her window as she was mastering similar triangle properties and concepts. I am sure glad I work with her virtually!  Sarah demonstrated her \"ccc\" side (calm, cool, and collected) throughout the ordeal, which was quite impressive.  Maybe we will go back to boring statistics next week as a pre-indicator  of a more mundane session.  Whew!', '50', '2022-03-29 14:49:27', '2022-03-29 14:49:58'),
(989, 96, 48, 49, '2022-03-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through a computer assignment from her teacher on mixed numbers and improper fractions, using both the numerical methods and diagrams to understand the concepts.', '20', '2022-03-29 21:20:22', '2022-03-29 21:20:22'),
(990, 34, 80, 59, '2022-03-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Coordinate plane review and review for upcoming test.', '70', '2022-03-29 23:18:30', '2022-03-29 23:18:30'),
(991, 94, 98, 95, '2022-03-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Mason learned about space and aliens. With that, we practiced summarizing, critical thinking, pronunciation, prefixes and root words. We reviewed vocabulary words from previous sessions such as \"species\" and we used them in sentences and thought of examples. We practiced skimming, sight reading, and pulling out main ideas. He practiced creative writing using 5 senses. He was excited to share with me a book he was reading in school.', '25', '2022-03-29 23:20:40', '2022-03-29 23:20:40'),
(992, 94, 45, 46, '2022-03-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we reviewed conjugating present tense regular verbs, both -ir/-er and -ar verbs. We reviewed the rules of each conjugation. Then, we put them together in filling out a crossword puzzle with new verbs and conjugations. I had him write down the new verbs in his journal. He did a great job catching on once he got in the zone.', '35', '2022-03-29 23:25:11', '2022-03-29 23:25:11'),
(993, 42, 93, 90, '2022-03-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew had his best session to date today. He is working on multiplying and dividing fractions and is finding them conceptually easy and is making few mistakes. We then tested out his new skills by adding fractions to Order of Operations problems. I did notice Matthew doesn\'t always simplify his fractions completely and will review this with him next week.', '54', '2022-03-30 20:58:12', '2022-03-30 20:58:12'),
(994, 38, 56, 57, '2022-03-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian handed me the reins this evening as he felt all caught up with his work. Thanks Ian!  I used the opportunity presented to me do a thorough review of exponents, roots, and radicals. I would have preferred to conduct the lesson while Ian was wearing one of his super hero costumes, but Ian\'s performance in our practice problems was of \"super hero\" caliber by just being himself. Great work Ian!', '50', '2022-03-31 14:10:16', '2022-03-31 14:10:16'),
(995, 60, 73, 67, '2022-03-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on 2-digit addition word problems that involved regrouping. Started reading \"The Little Mermaid\".', '20', '2022-03-31 17:28:42', '2022-03-31 17:28:42'),
(996, 60, 60, 62, '2022-04-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Checked through Canvas and made sure everything was complete for the end of third quarter. Kept reading \"The Sword in the Stone\" and focused on using context to define words. Started working on single variable expressions.', '20', '2022-04-02 01:53:19', '2022-04-02 01:53:19'),
(997, 60, 66, 67, '2022-04-01', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Learned about how to add fractions with the same denominator. Learned how to create equivalent fractions by multiplying the numerator and denominator by a constant. Learned about the GCF to simplify fractions and the LCM to create a common denominator to add two fractions.', '20', '2022-04-02 02:02:19', '2022-04-02 02:02:19'),
(998, 60, 75, 72, '2022-04-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced nouns, adjectives, verbs, and adverbs with objects around the room. Reviewed 2-5 multiplication table and started learning 6s.', '20', '2022-04-02 02:14:52', '2022-04-02 02:14:52'),
(999, 96, 48, 49, '2022-04-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I prepared a fractions review lesson for Leena to work through, where we discussed what fractions are, representing fractions, comparing fractions, and mixed numbers and improper fractions.', '20', '2022-04-02 09:33:16', '2022-04-02 09:33:16'),
(1000, 34, 91, 88, '2022-04-02', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Reviewed KenKen rules, worked on writing equations from word problems.\r\nTyler: Reviewed KenKen rules, chapter 6.9', '79', '2022-04-02 15:11:45', '2022-04-02 15:11:45'),
(1001, 82, 94, 91, '2022-04-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics-Solved Problems in Rotational Motion and Conservation of Angular Momentum', '60', '2022-04-02 19:14:36', '2022-04-02 19:14:36'),
(1002, 34, 95, 88, '2022-04-03', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Word problems and continued with lesson 15 in Hands on Algebra\r\nTyler: Challenging KenKen and percentage word problems.', '79', '2022-04-03 15:39:44', '2022-04-03 15:39:44'),
(1003, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we reviewed for Brendon\'s Spanish exam tomorrow. We went over conjugations of normal verbs, present progressive, stem changers, forming sentences, and items of clothing. He did great! There is a lot of material covered on the exam but I feel that Brendon has a good grip on conjugations and he has come a long way. Go Brendon go!', '45', '2022-04-04 22:03:12', '2022-04-04 22:03:12'),
(1004, 38, 89, 85, '2022-04-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'With the tree incident behind us and Sarah once again safe and sound, we returned to a fully focused and dynamic session as before.  Sarah and I circled back to statistics today, with a focus on the manual calculations one would do to arrive at standard deviation and variance from a set of observations.  Although one rarely does the manual calculation in actual statistical analysis, it was a beneficial to see the workings behind the statistic.  Sarah is doing great!', '50', '2022-04-05 14:04:51', '2022-04-05 14:04:51'),
(1005, 34, 95, 88, '2022-04-05', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Lesson 16 in Hands on Algebra\r\nTyler: Chapter 6 review, working through percentage word problems and unit rates.', '79', '2022-04-05 23:11:52', '2022-04-05 23:11:52'),
(1006, 34, 80, 59, '2022-04-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Homework review, and learned to play a 10x10 nonogram!', '70', '2022-04-05 23:18:01', '2022-04-05 23:18:01'),
(1007, 94, 98, 95, '2022-04-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Last week, Mason was ecstatic to teach me about his rubiks cube. We read a book about rubiks cube and its history and significance. We practiced paraphrasing, summarizing, critical thinking, doing a cost/benefit analysis, and vocabulary. We did an activity about comma rules for kids and practiced putting commas in sentences. We will start using workbooks next week.', '25', '2022-04-06 03:00:48', '2022-04-06 03:00:48'),
(1008, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we studied more for his Spanish exam day 2, particularly vosotros conjugations and o to ue and e to ie stem changers. We worked on the crossword assignment and practiced the names of different items of clothing. Brendon was feeling very down about his Spanish exam and I tried to encourage him to not take it to heart and focus on having fun learning the Spanish language.', '45', '2022-04-06 03:03:48', '2022-04-06 03:03:48'),
(1009, 96, 48, 49, '2022-04-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I worked through three worksheets from her teacher on adding decimals and identifying the names of places for decimals. Then we practiced these skills where Leena assumed the role of teacher to work through different problems.', '20', '2022-04-06 23:17:54', '2022-04-06 23:17:54'),
(1010, 34, 91, 88, '2022-04-06', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Lesson 16 in Hands on Math\r\nTyler: Reviewed chapter 6 and began chapter 7, with 2-step equations', '79', '2022-04-06 23:19:26', '2022-04-06 23:19:26'),
(1011, 34, 45, 46, '2022-04-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Operations with fractions and exponents using negative number.', '75', '2022-04-07 00:06:08', '2022-04-07 00:06:08'),
(1012, 38, 56, 57, '2022-04-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian is no longer just learning tools that he can use to simply come up with an answer, He is now being asked to analyze situations, as we did today when we compared commuter age to mode of transportation.  I consider this a very positive reflection on his growth in his mathematical abilities, and I am optimistic he will continue to progress.  We used bar charts for the commuter application, and with some time remaining, reinforced this tool though some additional exercises.  Great job Ian!', '50', '2022-04-07 14:42:52', '2022-04-07 14:42:52'),
(1013, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, I started teaching Brendon past tense. We finished the crossword from last class and we worked on a homework assignment on identifying past tense verbs. We reviewed vocab and I prepped him for the basics of past tense conjugations and their patterns.', '45', '2022-04-07 23:29:19', '2022-04-07 23:29:19'),
(1014, 60, 60, 62, '2022-04-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on variable expressions and talked about coefficients vs constants. Reviewed operations with negative numbers. Continued reading \"The Sword in the Stone\" and talked through some comprehension questions.', '20', '2022-04-09 19:58:58', '2022-04-09 19:58:58'),
(1015, 34, 91, 88, '2022-04-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed work on Lessons 18 - 21 in Hands on Algebra', '79', '2022-04-09 21:39:48', '2022-04-09 21:39:48'),
(1016, 34, 95, 88, '2022-04-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Studied chapters 7.2 and 7.3', '79', '2022-04-09 21:40:08', '2022-04-09 21:40:08'),
(1017, 38, 74, 71, '2022-04-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I shared a hearty laugh as we worked  through adding and multiplying polynomial expressions.  I guess you have to be a mathematician, as the both of us are, to understand that one. Timur seemed to have a significant uptick in confidence today, which was gratifying to see. He continues to grow in his skills as our work together proceeds.  As always, Timur is a pleasure to work with.', '50', '2022-04-11 13:32:28', '2022-04-11 13:32:28');
INSERT INTO `timesheets` (`timesheet_id`, `tutor_id`, `student_id`, `user_id`, `date`, `time`, `duration`, `duration2`, `description`, `hourly_pay_rate`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1018, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we went over conjugations again (present regular, present irregular, and stem changers). We reviewed vosotros form. We reviewed the list of clothing items, seasons, and writing sentences describing the clothing for his oral quiz tomorrow. He has truly improved in conjugations.', '45', '2022-04-12 12:34:12', '2022-04-12 12:34:12'),
(1019, 38, 89, 85, '2022-04-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I continued to build our statistical expertise today, as we learned and mastered box plots and mean absolute deviation.  My super student makes sure to show me that she understands new concepts through her proficiency in solving actual problems.  And most of impressive of all was that Sarah is officially on spring break... and did not even ask Mom for the day off today!  Now that\'s dedication!  Sarah is definitely  going places!', '50', '2022-04-12 13:25:31', '2022-04-12 13:25:31'),
(1020, 42, 93, 90, '2022-04-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I focused on multi-step and multi-function word problems, which he tends to find difficult. Pre-emptive panic is an issue for Matthew and we are working on strategies to break down problems to make them less intimidating.', '54', '2022-04-12 19:59:04', '2022-04-12 19:59:04'),
(1021, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'During Alex’s first session, I assessed where he is with his language skills. We went over the letters A and B, which he was easily able to identify and match to the correct sound. Vocabulary is tricky for him, but he was able to identify objects starting with A and B from pictures. He is an absolute delight.', '54', '2022-04-12 20:02:10', '2022-04-12 20:02:10'),
(1022, 42, 104, 102, '2022-04-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden is finding reading out loud to be difficult and counterproductive, so, in order to better assess his comprehension and fluency skills, I gave him a reading with questions attached. At first, he struggled and missed questions, but improved quickly when we went over the answers again. He did another reading independently and did much better.', '54', '2022-04-12 20:04:48', '2022-04-12 20:04:48'),
(1026, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I did some reinforcement on the letters A and B before reading two books and playing some games related to identifying colors. He continues to respond beautifully to tutoring and is becoming more willing to speak with me.', '54', '2022-04-12 20:08:08', '2022-04-12 20:08:08'),
(1027, 42, 104, 102, '2022-04-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I worked more on reading comprehension, focusing on identifying necessary information and note taking. He has made major strides forward and is growing in curiosity.', '54', '2022-04-12 20:16:00', '2022-04-12 20:16:00'),
(1028, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I went over the letters C and D before reinforcing his color vocabulary. We also read three books together, looking for A through D sounds, colors, and familiar words throughout. He is more and more confident speaking.', '54', '2022-04-12 20:25:32', '2022-04-12 20:25:32'),
(1029, 94, 98, 95, '2022-04-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Mason and I did exercises from the vocabulary book on prefixes, suffixes, base words, and root words. I enjoyed the book because it builds up from circling the prefixes to identifying and explaining definitions gradually. We also learned words that we use in the English language that come from other languages and we practiced using them in sentences. I assigned two prefix/suffix homework assignments. Next week, we will get into the reading comprehension book.', '25', '2022-04-12 22:38:15', '2022-04-12 22:38:15'),
(1030, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, the session was cancelled 10min after the start time. I\'m not sure what the policy is on that.', '45', '2022-04-12 22:39:14', '2022-04-12 22:39:14'),
(1031, 34, 91, 88, '2022-04-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Markus: 30 min. Lesson 22 in Hands-On-Algebra\r\nTyler: 30 min. Lesson 7.1 homework review and Tyler got another assignment from the same section, with the goal of being more careful with the negatives.', '79', '2022-04-12 23:07:24', '2022-04-12 23:07:24'),
(1032, 34, 80, 59, '2022-04-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Lesson 72 homework', '70', '2022-04-12 23:07:44', '2022-04-12 23:07:44'),
(1033, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we learned two irregular past tense verbs (ir, ser) and a (-ir, -er) past tense regular verbs. I tried to speak in Brendon\'s language by teaching patterns. We practiced by making sentences and doing a worksheet. I had him try erasing his answers and trying again and again and each time he got better.', '45', '2022-04-14 23:01:38', '2022-04-14 23:01:38'),
(1034, 103, 107, 106, '2022-04-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I completed pages 5-7 of the spectrum math grade 4 book, I assigned page 8 for a little h.w. practice, and during it we completed an activity from education.com which included a magic trick (to practice addition, multiplication, and memory). \r\n\r\nImpressions:\r\n#1: Mason is very smart and quick with great attention to detail (he can identify quickly when he made a mistake and how to fix it).\r\n#2: Mason followed directions well, remained engaged, and showed all the steps to get the correct answer when we did activity.\r\nwith great attention to detail (he can identify quickly when he made a mistake and how to fix it).\r\n#3:  Mason has good understanding of word sentence structure in regards to word problems and identifies which operations to use to solve the word problem on his own.\r\n#4:  Mason is looking forward to doing multiplication, fractions and division!', '35', '2022-04-14 23:57:37', '2022-04-14 23:57:37'),
(1035, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon\'s mom asked me to help with his Spanish project. We reviewed irregular and present regular conjugations of verbs, learned this/that in Spanish, and then used these words to write paragraphs about items of clothing to make an outfit.', '45', '2022-04-16 18:39:43', '2022-04-16 18:39:43'),
(1036, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon\'s mom asked me to help check Brendon\'s Spanish project. We went through each 5 outfits and checked the grammar, practicing singular/plural ser conjugations, stem changers, and esto/esta/estas/estos. I am proud of him for his hard work on this difficult project!', '45', '2022-04-18 01:12:20', '2022-04-18 01:12:20'),
(1037, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we read \"The Most Beautiful Thing\", one of my favorite children\'s books about the power and beauty of grandparents. We learned about a Hmong family and Brendon shared with me how he related to the book as his family had to struggle to come to the US. I had him write his takeaways, practice summarizing, context clues, and ultimately write to his grandparents. I shared with him the value of being kind and asking questions to older adults, and what I have learned from older adults through working in a nursing home.', '45', '2022-04-18 21:48:42', '2022-04-18 21:48:42'),
(1038, 60, 73, 67, '2022-04-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on adding and subtracting three digit numbers with and without regrouping. Did a basic introduction to subtraction with regrouping. Started learning about nouns and did a basic worksheet identifying them. Finished reading “The Little Mermaid”.', '20', '2022-04-19 02:43:31', '2022-04-19 02:43:31'),
(1039, 60, 66, 67, '2022-04-18', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on operations with fractions and reviewed LCM and GCF.', '20', '2022-04-19 02:43:56', '2022-04-19 02:43:56'),
(1040, 38, 89, 85, '2022-04-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'There must be a reason for why my discovery was so belated, but only today when I was searching for a interesting topic to review with Sarah did I find That Howard County Public Schools itself had a link to \"Getting Ready for Algebra\" on the Khan Academy website. Not that we haven\'t been already doing that for months, but now we can really zero in on Sarah\'s areas of \"needing strengthening\". We went right to the unit test, so we can accomplish this task as efficiently as possible.  So far, we have discovered that exponents rules is an area that will require some additional focus.  I am invigorated by the whole thing!  And Sarah is as well.  And once we complete preparing for algebra , HCPS has also linked us directly to algebra 1 topics as well on Khan Academy in order to give Sarah an even stronger head start!', '50', '2022-04-19 14:17:26', '2022-04-19 14:17:26'),
(1041, 34, 95, 88, '2022-04-19', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Reviewed and completed lesson 21 in Hands on Equations.\r\nTyler: Reviewed section 7.2, multi-step equations.', '79', '2022-04-19 23:03:42', '2022-04-19 23:03:42'),
(1042, 34, 80, 59, '2022-04-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Divisibility rules for 2,3,4,5,6,9', '70', '2022-04-19 23:04:01', '2022-04-19 23:04:01'),
(1043, 34, 91, 88, '2022-04-20', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Lesson 23 in Hands on Equations\r\nTyler: Lesson 7.3', '79', '2022-04-21 00:09:11', '2022-04-21 00:09:11'),
(1044, 34, 45, 46, '2022-04-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Order of operations practice + minesweeper.', '75', '2022-04-21 00:09:43', '2022-04-21 00:09:43'),
(1045, 38, 56, 57, '2022-04-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian\'s Mom provided the link to a website that has been integrated into Ian\'s workload, so we spent the day going through a set of problems that were waiting there for us.  Some of the highlights included scientific notation and algebra, with Ian and I mixing in a bit of Gundam Kyrios to keep it interesting.  Ian excelled, and a fun time was had by all!  Mom mentioned something about exponential transformations which I did not see during our session.  We can address that topic at our next meeting.  I will seek clarification. Great job Ian!', '50', '2022-04-21 14:52:00', '2022-04-21 14:52:00'),
(1046, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'This week, Brendon and I worked on past tense regular and irregular verbs, including me te le les, stem changers, and reflexive verbs. I think his spanish teacher is going a little fast so I did some present tense review so Brendon doesn\'t lose the progress he is making on the basics.', '45', '2022-04-21 23:12:44', '2022-04-21 23:12:44'),
(1047, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we did a \"repaso\" or review of present tense verb conjugations. We practiced sounding words out in \"voz alta\" or out loud. I told him that I still practice reading out loud because it is a valuable skill to have. I had Brendon design a play (with stick figures) to practice present and past tense verb conjugations. He made a play about himself and a friend. I was happy with how hard he worked on it and how creative he was with it. Future playwright??', '45', '2022-04-21 23:15:21', '2022-04-21 23:15:21'),
(1048, 38, 74, 71, '2022-04-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I missed Timur for our lesson today.  I appreciate that Mom contacted me, and look forward to future lessons with my super student. As stated in our tutoring agreement, 24 hours notice is required for cancelling/rescheduling to avoid being charged the full fee of the lesson.  Please be in touch if you need to contact me.  Please send regards to Timur, and have a wonderful week.  Be well.', '50', '2022-04-25 14:17:23', '2022-04-25 14:17:23'),
(1049, 60, 75, 72, '2022-04-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed school assignment. Reviewed multiplication from 2-5. Reviewed how to read a clock and how you use the five times table for the minute hand. Did a word scrabble.', '20', '2022-04-25 16:29:34', '2022-04-25 16:29:34'),
(1050, 34, 91, 88, '2022-04-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Markus only: Lesson 24 plus Nerdle plus Minesweeper.', '79', '2022-04-25 20:12:38', '2022-04-25 20:12:38'),
(1051, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we practiced preterite. I had him write a play in the past tense. We reviewed conjugation rules and worked on an online preterite homework assignment. Once he repeated the conjugations on paper three times, he did great!', '45', '2022-04-25 22:36:00', '2022-04-25 22:36:00'),
(1052, 38, 89, 85, '2022-04-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I continued our diligent and focused work on \"Getting Ready for Algebra\".  Not only is Sarah proving convincingly what she already knows, but is highlighting as well those few concepts that require some strengthening. We are making note of these \"areas of improvement\" for later review.  It is quite exciting to be able to assist Sarah in becoming fully prepared for the challenging GT Algebra she will be dealing with next year.  She is doing great!', '50', '2022-04-26 14:12:59', '2022-04-26 14:12:59'),
(1053, 34, 91, 88, '2022-04-26', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Reviewed homework, and played minesweeper, intermediate level.\r\nTyler: reviewed homework and learned section 7.4', '79', '2022-04-26 23:03:34', '2022-04-26 23:03:34'),
(1054, 34, 80, 59, '2022-04-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Learned to play minesweeper.', '70', '2022-04-26 23:03:55', '2022-04-26 23:03:55'),
(1055, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued to work on the first few letters of the alphabet and on basic number sense.', '54', '2022-04-26 23:10:48', '2022-04-26 23:10:48'),
(1056, 42, 104, 102, '2022-04-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I continued to work on his reading comprehension skills, answering questions based on context clues.', '54', '2022-04-26 23:16:13', '2022-04-26 23:16:13'),
(1057, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon and I learned irregular past tense verbs (which I believe his teacher is moving wayyyyy too fast in, but I understand it\'s the curriculum not her). I would rather Brendon reinforce and solidify concepts he already has down like present and past regular before moving on to crazy irregular verbs. But we made the best of it and Brendon is a fast learner.', '45', '2022-04-26 23:18:17', '2022-04-26 23:18:17'),
(1058, 42, 93, 90, '2022-04-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I went over a variety of skills he\'s been grappling with including word problems and dividing fractions.', '54', '2022-04-26 23:18:25', '2022-04-26 23:18:25'),
(1059, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I worked on recognizing different animals and connecting them to letter and vowel sounds. We also continued to work on number sense.', '54', '2022-04-26 23:20:27', '2022-04-26 23:20:27'),
(1060, 42, 106, 105, '2022-04-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Riley and I spent a bit of time getting to know each other before beginning to work through the book. She is quick on the uptake and eager to learn more.', '54', '2022-04-26 23:24:48', '2022-04-26 23:24:48'),
(1061, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued to work with number sense and connecting phonics to words. He was tired and generally struggled to focus. 3 days a week is tough on him, but mom insists.', '54', '2022-04-26 23:36:01', '2022-04-26 23:36:01'),
(1062, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I worked on some basic addition and subtraction, while also looking at math vocabulary and related phonics. We then reviewed the letters E and F, practicing handwriting and connecting letter sounds to the actual letters.', '54', '2022-04-26 23:45:35', '2022-04-26 23:45:35'),
(1063, 60, 66, 67, '2022-04-25', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Continued practicing addition, subtraction, and multiplication with fractions as well as the GCF and LCM. Started working on reciprocals and fraction division.', '20', '2022-04-27 04:33:29', '2022-04-27 04:33:29'),
(1064, 60, 73, 67, '2022-04-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed school language arts and math homework. Practiced counting by 2s, 3s, and 5s. Started reading “Lady and the Tramp”.', '20', '2022-04-27 04:34:28', '2022-04-27 04:34:28'),
(1065, 60, 60, 62, '2022-04-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on math homework with beginning of single variable expressions and equations and the distributive property. Continued reading “The Sword in the Stone” and answered questions in annotations.', '20', '2022-04-27 04:41:13', '2022-04-27 04:41:13'),
(1066, 34, 95, 88, '2022-04-27', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus and Tyler: quick prep for ISEE', '79', '2022-04-27 23:10:24', '2022-04-27 23:10:24'),
(1067, 34, 45, 46, '2022-04-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Quick review of solving one step equations, and then Fur Families logic puzzle from education.com', '75', '2022-04-28 00:12:33', '2022-04-28 00:12:33'),
(1068, 38, 56, 57, '2022-04-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'The \"Get More Math\" website that Mom clued me in on has been a great asset in my work with Ian!  It has provided a solid review of concepts that Ian has seen throughout the year, and that require some strengthening.  And Ian is focused and engaged throughout the session! For sure Ian has become proficient at scientific natation, which appears quite frequently in the section we are covering.  Ian is doing great!', '50', '2022-04-28 15:12:20', '2022-04-28 15:12:20'),
(1069, 60, 75, 72, '2022-04-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed multiplication facts and started learning 6s. Reviewed about how to write fractions and represent them in images.', '20', '2022-04-28 17:10:55', '2022-04-28 17:10:55'),
(1070, 94, 45, 46, '2022-04-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we reviewed regular and some irregular past tense verbs. I had him practice the conjugations first on his own without notes, then go over the correct answers, then re-do it, and then re-do it a third time to repeat and solidify these patterns and concepts. We learned many new verbs and practiced them in sentences.', '45', '2022-04-28 23:00:50', '2022-04-28 23:00:50'),
(1071, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I worked on some basic number recognition and reviewed letter sounds A-H', '54', '2022-04-30 20:45:56', '2022-04-30 20:45:56'),
(1072, 42, 93, 90, '2022-04-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew started doing basic geometry so we did some practice and went over accompanying word problems', '54', '2022-04-30 20:48:37', '2022-04-30 20:48:37'),
(1073, 42, 105, 104, '2022-04-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I read together and continued to build his vocabulary around numbers and parts of the body.', '54', '2022-04-30 20:49:50', '2022-04-30 20:49:50'),
(1074, 34, 80, 59, '2022-05-01', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed practice test in preparation for test on Tuesday.', '70', '2022-05-02 00:54:53', '2022-05-02 00:54:53'),
(1075, 38, 74, 71, '2022-05-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was wonderful to see Timur again after a break.  He was ready to go, so after a short review of adding and subtracting polynomials, we tried our hand at a new topic: multiplying monomials.  Timur picked up the tool quickly, and was quite proficient at it by the end of the session.  Timur is a humble young man with tremendous potential and talent.  He is bound for greatness!', '50', '2022-05-02 13:58:30', '2022-05-02 13:58:30'),
(1076, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we went over irregular Spanish verb conjugations such as estar, andar, querer, tener, and hacer. I had him practice repeating without looking and watch how he got better every time to show the value of practice and repetition. I had him make sentences with the new verb conjugations. He is doing great!', '45', '2022-05-02 21:54:52', '2022-05-02 21:54:52'),
(1077, 38, 89, 85, '2022-05-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'After completing our \"Getting Ready for Algebra\" exam, Sarah and I noticed that there were 45 items that the test did not cover from the course. WOW!  And they admitted it!  Luckily, they offered us the opportunity to take it again with a completely different set of questions.  Our hope is that different topics will be highlighted, thereby enabling Sarah and me to identify other concepts that may require strengthening.  We don\'t necessarily want to create a long list, but WE do want to be thorough.  From the first pass, we reviewed exponents, and will look at roots next time before beginning the second exam. Sarah and I will leave no stone unturned!', '50', '2022-05-03 18:24:31', '2022-05-03 18:24:31'),
(1078, 34, 91, 88, '2022-05-03', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Lesson 25 in in Hands on Algebra\r\nTyler: Did not complete homework so lesson did not happen', '79', '2022-05-03 21:56:56', '2022-05-03 21:56:56'),
(1079, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we did an English lesson and he asked to learn about Rubik\'s Cube. We read a book about it and did a reading comprehension activity. We plotted the storyline. I had him use inferences and predictions based on the reading to make his own Rubik\'s-like invention and predict how well it will do in the market. He is a fabulous reader! He also remembered it was my birthday so that made my day!', '45', '2022-05-03 22:18:18', '2022-05-03 22:18:18'),
(1080, 38, 56, 57, '2022-05-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian is getting into some heavy math here!  WOW!  Today, we worked with word problems to model quadratics, graph them, find minimums and maximums, and even explain what the intercepts, etc. mean!  Ian was stretched, but as flexible as he is, he did not break!  He focused, learned, and integrated the concepts, and will be ready for more of the same at our next session.  Way to go Ian!', '50', '2022-05-05 15:15:19', '2022-05-05 15:15:19'),
(1081, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we pretended that we were at a market in Barcelona and practiced reading schedules, different types of foods, ordering food, buying, prices, and payment methods all in past tense. It was a great and useful lesson!', '45', '2022-05-05 23:03:48', '2022-05-05 23:03:48'),
(1082, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we practiced past tense again for Brendon\'s make up exam Monday. We made up 7 sentences of what he did this weekend and he memorized them and repeated them. We practiced irregular and regular preterite verbs. We also practiced use of \"fue\". He just needs to repeat and he will do great!', '45', '2022-05-07 20:21:35', '2022-05-07 20:21:35'),
(1083, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Brendon wanted help with a part of his presentation of preterite verbs. So, we worked together to make some more sentences in past tense. We practiced it until he performed the presentation three times without any mistakes. Then, I showed him a funny song about how hard it is to learn Spanish.', '45', '2022-05-09 00:59:24', '2022-05-09 00:59:24'),
(1084, 82, 68, 69, '2022-05-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Physics: Review Problems', '50', '2022-05-09 02:14:45', '2022-05-09 02:14:45'),
(1085, 60, 73, 67, '2022-05-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Continued working on three digit addition and subtraction with regrouping. Read more of \"Lady and the Tramp\".', '20', '2022-05-09 02:23:52', '2022-05-09 02:23:52'),
(1086, 60, 66, 67, '2022-05-02', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on area and perimeter of rectangles. Started talking about area of a triangle.', '20', '2022-05-09 02:24:42', '2022-05-09 02:24:42'),
(1087, 60, 60, 62, '2022-05-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Checked through Canvas. Completed math homework about variables with exponents and reviewed the commutative property with variables.', '20', '2022-05-09 02:28:16', '2022-05-09 02:28:16'),
(1088, 60, 75, 72, '2022-05-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced multiplication from 2-6. Practiced finding the main idea and supporting ideas in a paragraph.', '20', '2022-05-09 02:29:24', '2022-05-09 02:29:24'),
(1089, 38, 74, 71, '2022-05-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'I missed Timur for our lesson today. I appreciate that Mom contacted me, and look forward to future lessons with my super student. As stated in our tutoring agreement, 24 hours notice is required for cancelling/rescheduling to avoid being charged the full fee of the lesson. Please be in touch if you need to contact me. Please send regards to Timur, and have a wonderful week. Be well.', '50', '2022-05-09 13:53:53', '2022-05-09 13:53:53'),
(1090, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we did a worksheet practicing preterite (past tense) verbs in questions. So, Brendon answered many questions and had to conjugate his answers in the \"yo\" form. We reviewed question words like when, where, how, what time. Brendon is doing a good job remembering his regular conjugation rules.', '45', '2022-05-09 21:55:13', '2022-05-09 21:55:13'),
(1091, 38, 89, 85, '2022-05-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Sarah and I focused today on one of the areas we determined to be in need of some strengthening: radicals and their properties.  Sarah has not done much prior work on this topic, but succeeded in adding this tool to her inventory.  We then proceeded to attack our second \"Pre-Algebra Course Challenge\" as recommended by the the county school website.  We look forward to continuing to fill in pre-algebra gaps before moving on to more advanced algebra topics.  Sarah is a model student!', '50', '2022-05-10 16:55:10', '2022-05-10 16:55:10'),
(1092, 103, 91, 88, '2022-05-10', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus and Tyler both had 45 minutes,\r\n.\r\n\r\nHomework was not sent prior so Markus and Tyler and I could not review this in depth (Tyler hopped on late and his dad sent the picture at 651 so I prioritized the lesson instead. He was very out of it. I had him try problems with me and seems like he got it but needs encouragement. I should have probably played a game (just didnt know which one).\r\n\r\nMarkus  did 4/7 of his HW and got stuck. We reviewed all 7 and he seemed much more comfortable. Can do them on his own, takes a little bit but its OK.He had an Aha! moment when he realized where he went wrong with each, and that is what mattered to me. \r\n\r\nWe did not get to the worksheets as he needed time to understand his HW. I sent in the combining like terms (and reminded him about variables and exponents needing to be the same) and will try to squeeze in that other sheet , probably 2 odd numbers or something. \r\n\r\nThanks!', '35', '2022-05-10 22:50:44', '2022-05-10 22:50:44'),
(1093, 103, 91, 88, '2022-05-05', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'see email', '35', '2022-05-10 22:51:02', '2022-05-10 22:51:02'),
(1094, 42, 104, 102, '2022-05-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I continued working through reading comprehension exercises. He sometimes falls into the trap of over analyzing questions and talking himself out of the correct answer. Otherwise, I’m seeing improvements with every session.', '54', '2022-05-11 20:31:07', '2022-05-11 20:31:07'),
(1096, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I went over letters A through H and continued to explore vocabulary related to food and clothes.', '54', '2022-05-11 20:37:03', '2022-05-11 20:37:03'),
(1097, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'After reading together, Alex and I continued working on phonics and vocabulary', '54', '2022-05-11 20:39:13', '2022-05-11 20:39:13'),
(1098, 42, 93, 90, '2022-05-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew continues to find word problems difficult, so we worked through multi step problems involving several concepts he’s studied this year.', '54', '2022-05-11 20:46:02', '2022-05-11 20:46:02'),
(1099, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex was given a list of sight words at school to study. He can identify letters but is unable to blend sounds together without help. We focused back on phonics and expanding Alex’s vocabulary.', '54', '2022-05-11 20:51:53', '2022-05-11 20:51:53'),
(1100, 38, 56, 57, '2022-05-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian was assigned a set of binomials to multiply, and had not yet met \"Mr. FOIL\".  So I introduced my wonderful student to the tool, and he ran with it!  Ian quickly transformed himself onto a FOIL expert, although he still needs to be careful with his positive and negative signs.  We also used graphs to come up with solutions to quadratic equations, although it took us a bit to understand what the assignment was even asking.  We remained patient, put on our thinking caps, and learned a great deal in the process.  Great work Ian.  Have a nice weekend!', '50', '2022-05-12 14:59:51', '2022-05-12 14:59:51'),
(1101, 38, 74, 71, '2022-05-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In a rare midweek session to replace a future session to be missed, Timur and I began preparing for his upcoming Algebra 1 final. Although Timur seemed rusty in many of the concepts that we covered in this session, he assured me that he can recall what he needs when he needs it.  I challenged him by letting him that he needs it right now, and remain uncertain about how this magical recall power actually works.  We will continue to review over the next few weeks in an effort to bring to the surface that which Timur will need to succeed on the exam.', '50', '2022-05-13 14:44:20', '2022-05-13 14:44:20'),
(1102, 42, 93, 90, '2022-05-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I looked at some order of operations problems, dealing with both word problems and regular problems. He made a few minor mistakes, but generally has an excellent grasp of the material.', '54', '2022-05-15 19:08:53', '2022-05-15 19:08:53'),
(1103, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued to work on phonics and connecting letter sounds to the letters themselves. He is improving when it comes to speaking but is struggling with reading.', '54', '2022-05-15 19:22:52', '2022-05-15 19:22:52'),
(1104, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued on connecting letter sound to letters along with phonics. We mainly focused on vowels, which are sometimes confusing for him.', '54', '2022-05-15 19:24:30', '2022-05-15 19:24:30'),
(1105, 60, 60, 62, '2022-05-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on school math homework and vocab in The Sword in the Stone.', '20', '2022-05-16 04:10:15', '2022-05-16 04:10:15'),
(1106, 60, 75, 72, '2022-05-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced multiplication by sixes and took a quiz. Reviewed basic 2D and 3D shapes. Completed an addition and subtraction math puzzle.', '20', '2022-05-16 04:11:04', '2022-05-16 04:11:04'),
(1107, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We played a fun game today like Jeopardy to earn fake money by answering Spanish past tense questions. We practiced preterite and learned many new verbs and reinforced the old ones.', '45', '2022-05-17 01:50:24', '2022-05-17 01:50:24'),
(1108, 38, 43, 40, '2022-05-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although it was only for a single session that I had a chance to work with Mallory again, it was still wonderful to have a chance to catch up.  I was so happy to hear that my super student was breezing through her recent geometry units.  Although the most recent subject matter concerning the different forms of the equation of a line was giving Mallory some trouble, we did our best to break it down and simplify the matter.  It seems that by the end of the session, although the issues were not totally clarified in Mallory\'s mind, that she had a better grasp of the concepts.  If she needs any additional time to go over it, I would e happy to meet with Mallory again.  Have a great rest of the school year!', '50', '2022-05-17 16:36:53', '2022-05-17 16:36:53'),
(1109, 34, 80, 59, '2022-05-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'reviewed homework and played No Dice', '70', '2022-05-17 23:12:19', '2022-05-17 23:12:19'),
(1110, 34, 95, 88, '2022-05-17', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Began work on fractions from Hands on Equations, completed 3 lessons\r\nTyler: Lesson 7.6 was poorly understood so we studied it again', '79', '2022-05-17 23:13:10', '2022-05-17 23:13:10'),
(1111, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We did a review session of preterite (past tense) verbs before Brendon\'s test this Thursday. We went over last week\'s verbs. I played a game with him where I put on different zoom backgrounds and he practiced the verb \"estar\" to be past tense to describe where I was.', '45', '2022-05-18 01:03:50', '2022-05-18 01:03:50'),
(1112, 60, 60, 62, '2022-05-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed Asia history quiz. Worked on math homework about exponents. Went back in SITS to read more critically and focus more on comprehension.', '20', '2022-05-18 02:24:36', '2022-05-18 02:24:36'),
(1113, 34, 45, 46, '2022-05-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Solving two-step equations, and distributive property.', '75', '2022-05-19 00:04:12', '2022-05-19 00:04:12'),
(1114, 34, 95, 88, '2022-05-18', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: continued with fractions workbook, and word problems\r\nTyler: Lesson 7.7 Simple interest', '79', '2022-05-19 00:04:54', '2022-05-19 00:04:54'),
(1115, 82, 100, 98, '2022-05-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Math:  Review for Test', '54', '2022-05-19 00:13:33', '2022-05-19 00:13:33'),
(1116, 38, 56, 57, '2022-05-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian does not waste his time just memorizing formulas ands methodologies while applying them on auto pilot. No sir! Take today\' s session on residuals and regression lines, for example. Of course, we did the calculations and made the graphs. But in addition, Ian had to interpret and explain what was going on...and he did a fine job!  I was truly impressed.  We did not have a chance to finish the assignment, but I let Ian know that I am available for additional sessions if he needs me.  Great job Ian. Have a nice weekend!', '50', '2022-05-19 14:35:04', '2022-05-19 14:35:04'),
(1117, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we did an English lesson on fidget spinners as per Brendon\'s request. We read a book on anxiety, and then an article about the cons/pros of fidget spinners and if the data supports them. Then, we used critical thinking skills to summarize different parts of the readings and pulled from anecdotal data to make a cost/benefit list of fidget spinners. We determined that the decrease in anxiety outweighed the possible distraction and therefore, fidget spinners should have a place in learning environments. I taught him this tool to use in future readings and in life.', '45', '2022-05-20 00:20:04', '2022-05-20 00:20:04'),
(1118, 34, 91, 88, '2022-05-21', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Continued with Hands on FRactions, and worked on combining like terms using number tiles\r\nTyler: compound interest formula', '79', '2022-05-21 22:57:51', '2022-05-21 22:57:51'),
(1119, 38, 74, 71, '2022-05-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although the end of the school year is closing in, Timur\'s workload is not slowing down in the least.  Our work this evening involved a slew of advanced topics, including determining vertices and intercepts from quadratic  equations, as well as creating and interpreting regression lines.  Timur rose to the occasion, and solidified his already strong skills in these areas.  I am proud that my super student continues to give his best effort all the way to the finish line. Go Timur!', '50', '2022-05-23 14:07:45', '2022-05-23 14:07:45'),
(1120, 60, 75, 72, '2022-05-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on multiplication of 6s and 7s by playing hopscotch. Practiced nouns, verbs, and adjectives with Madlibs.', '20', '2022-05-23 17:33:28', '2022-05-23 17:33:28'),
(1121, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued to work on phonics and connecting letters to their sounds in addition to our usual reading. He is making progress in his speaking but still needs to develop his vocabulary.', '54', '2022-05-23 18:53:12', '2022-05-23 18:53:12'),
(1122, 42, 93, 90, '2022-05-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I continued to work on complex, multi-function word problems involving order of operations. He has become much better at finding and correcting his mistakes as they happen. Writing down his work is now second nature.', '54', '2022-05-23 18:57:11', '2022-05-23 18:57:11'),
(1123, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I focused on developing his vocabulary and gaining confidence speaking. I asked him to show me his favorite cars and any details he could share. Talking about things he loves gives him the motivation to speak.', '54', '2022-05-23 19:00:17', '2022-05-23 19:00:17'),
(1124, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I did some reading and then continued to develop his skills with phonics. We also looked over vocabulary related to the household.', '54', '2022-05-23 19:01:54', '2022-05-23 19:01:54'),
(1125, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we read an article about shopping in different hispanic communities: New York, Miami, Los Angeles, and San Antonio. We learned many items in Spanish, practiced past tense verbs, and practiced common phrases. We answered comprehension questions and he practiced reading and pronunciation skills.', '45', '2022-05-23 22:13:49', '2022-05-23 22:13:49'),
(1126, 34, 91, 88, '2022-05-24', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: Combining like terms with algebra tiles. Reviewed order of operations by playing Nerdle.\r\nTyler: Didn\'t come due to incomplete homework :(', '79', '2022-05-24 23:20:54', '2022-05-24 23:20:54'),
(1127, 34, 80, 59, '2022-05-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed for upcoming test. Discussed interesting properties (and names) of polygons and circles.', '70', '2022-05-24 23:21:27', '2022-05-24 23:21:27'),
(1128, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we reviewed for Brendon\'s preterite exam by playing preterite (past tense) Jeopardy (sound effects and all). I found out that Brendon\'s issue was that he was adding a few letters on to his tú form verb conjugations so we practiced/reviewed the difference between vosotros and tú forms.', '45', '2022-05-25 15:42:51', '2022-05-25 15:42:51'),
(1129, 34, 95, 88, '2022-05-25', NULL, '1:30', '1.5', 'Markus: fractions work continued, combining like terms, minesweeper.\r\nTyler: compound interest formula, and intro to functions', '79', '2022-05-25 23:59:10', '2022-05-25 23:59:10'),
(1130, 34, 45, 46, '2022-05-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Solving two-step equations. Nerdle.', '75', '2022-05-25 23:59:28', '2022-05-25 23:59:28'),
(1131, 38, 56, 57, '2022-05-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Ian and I had to wing it a bit, as we were not certain that we had the correct assignment, we still managed to rise above the challenge, focus on the concepts, and come away with new skills and increased confidence.  Ian now understands the different forms that a quadratic can take on, their advantages and disadvantages, and how to convert from one form to another. As we want to make sure that our efforts align well with what is required of Ian, he has committed to pay closer attention to the \"transfer\" of information from classroom to tutoring session.  Ian is continuing to grow in his studies.  Great work!', '50', '2022-05-26 14:56:24', '2022-05-26 14:56:24'),
(1132, 60, 60, 62, '2022-05-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on school math homework with exponents, variables, and absolute value. Discussed chapter one of TSitS and started reading chapter two with a heavy focus on comprehension and vocabulary.', '20', '2022-05-28 12:46:46', '2022-05-28 12:46:46'),
(1133, 60, 75, 72, '2022-05-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Started reading The Magic Treehouse. Practiced multiplication of 6s and 7s. Completed a worksheet about perimeter.', '20', '2022-05-28 12:47:42', '2022-05-28 12:47:42'),
(1134, 38, 74, 71, '2022-05-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'The year may be winding down, but the level of work that Timur is doing is definitely heating up.  Parabolas, vertices, and lines were among the cast of characters we dealt with this evening, with the plot centering around their equations and  intersections.  Timur remains focused and  seems ready to call up all the necessary resources for the final push towards the finish line.  He has made me proud to call him my student.  Go Timur!', '50', '2022-05-30 14:59:07', '2022-05-30 14:59:07'),
(1135, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued working on phonics and developing his vocabulary. He is talking more and more and asking questions. Alex is very playful and sometimes will pretend not to know answers or will delay answering by asking questions. He can be challenging to redirect, but he always eventually gets there.', '54', '2022-05-31 16:14:00', '2022-05-31 16:14:00'),
(1136, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I worked on identifying beginning sounds, middle sounds, and end sounds. Sometimes, Alex struggles to follow sequencing vocabulary so we paused to review those words.', '54', '2022-05-31 16:16:53', '2022-05-31 16:16:53'),
(1137, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex had an excellent session and was much more focused and easier to redirect. We continued developing his vocabulary, focusing on rooms in the house and furniture in addition to reviewing previous vocabulary.', '54', '2022-05-31 16:18:06', '2022-05-31 16:18:06'),
(1138, 42, 104, 102, '2022-05-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'This was Caden\'s best session to date. We did two critical reading exercises and he answered all but one question out of 20 correctly. He is getting much better at decoding unfamiliar vocabulary words and is displaying much more confidence.', '54', '2022-05-31 16:19:48', '2022-05-31 16:19:48'),
(1139, 42, 93, 90, '2022-05-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew was not in the best mood this session and needed a great deal of encouragement. Matthew has come such a long way with his math skills, but he continually engages in negative self-talk, frequently \r\ncalling himself stupid. Matthew has a hard time shaking off small mistakes and I am concerned about how this is getting in the way of his progress.', '54', '2022-05-31 16:21:48', '2022-05-31 16:21:48'),
(1140, 42, 105, 104, '2022-05-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex had an excellent session. We reviewed beginning and ending sounds and reviewed rhyming sounds. Alex still struggles with sequencing vocabulary, so we did some exercises to go over those words and concepts. He was at his most talkative and asked many questions.', '54', '2022-05-31 16:23:12', '2022-05-31 16:23:12'),
(1141, 94, 45, 46, '2022-05-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we learned about engineering. We learned about the process about identifying a problem designing a solution, re-evaluating, and making it better (in Spanish). We read a book in English, watched a video, and saw some idea maps in Spanish. Brendon practiced paraphrasing, summarizing, and writing new verbs in English and Spanish.', '45', '2022-05-31 23:12:55', '2022-05-31 23:12:55'),
(1142, 60, 60, 62, '2022-05-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed absolute value and graphing inequalities. Discussed SitS responses for chapter two and completed pre reading activities for chapter three.', '20', '2022-06-01 12:30:06', '2022-06-01 12:30:06'),
(1143, 38, 74, 71, '2022-06-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I prepared for his final exam in Algebra this afternoon by doing a whirlwind review of the year\'s topics.  The teacher distributed a set of practice problems, and through working them, we hopefully brought back all of the \"fond memories\" that Timur will need to recall for success on the exam.   With each problem reviewed, Timur confirmed his comprehension and ability to apply the concepts.  I found the whole exercise quite nostalgic.  Have a great summer Timur.  You had an excellent year!', '50', '2022-06-02 15:32:09', '2022-06-02 15:32:09'),
(1144, 38, 56, 57, '2022-06-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I wrapped up the year by preparing for his final exam in Algebra.  The  teacher distributed a very comprehensive review packet, which we attempted to condense by focusing on the \"talking points\" and \":key terms\" sections.  It brought back all of the fond memories of the year, and if  Ian spends some extra time \"reviewing our review\", he should be well prepared to score big.  I truly enjoyed working with this wonderful young man throughout the school year, and if needed, I would treasure an opportunity to continue in the future.  Have a wonderful summer Ian!', '50', '2022-06-02 15:39:35', '2022-06-02 15:39:35'),
(1145, 94, 45, 46, '2022-06-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we watched a narrated story book about a pet fly in Spanish and broke down all of the sentences and parts of the story. I had him give himself an award like the awards in the story and he chose \"el niño más chistoso\" the funniest kid, which I thought was cute! We went over question words and practiced with some pictures and questions about the pictures.', '45', '2022-06-02 23:16:47', '2022-06-02 23:16:47'),
(1146, 60, 75, 72, '2022-06-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Learned about fractions on khan academy with a focus on the numerator, denominator, and what they represent. Continued reading “The Magic Treehouse”. Practiced multiplication of 7s', '20', '2022-06-06 13:59:01', '2022-06-06 13:59:01'),
(1147, 94, 45, 46, '2022-06-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'They were traveling and forgot about the tutoring lesson so Thu kindly offered to pay for the lesson.', '45', '2022-06-06 21:55:00', '2022-06-06 21:55:00'),
(1148, 42, 105, 104, '2022-06-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued to work on phonics and vocabulary, focusing on correct sequencing and comparison words. Alex is picking up vocabulary quickly, but is struggling with some phonetic sounds. He mixes up g and c as well as d and t.', '54', '2022-06-07 22:50:06', '2022-06-07 22:50:06'),
(1149, 42, 104, 102, '2022-06-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden needed help with a book report for school, so we focused on writing strong summaries, pre-writing, and how to craft an opinion. His writing has grown significantly more expressive and his spelling/phonetic awareness more confident.', '54', '2022-06-07 22:51:52', '2022-06-07 22:51:52'),
(1150, 42, 105, 104, '2022-06-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex continues to struggle with some phonetic sounds, but he did much better this session with correctly identifying beginning sounds in some words. His focus and concentration was also much stronger.', '54', '2022-06-07 22:55:10', '2022-06-07 22:55:10'),
(1151, 94, 45, 46, '2022-06-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon reviewed present tense and subjects in Spanish (yo, tu, el/ella/ud, nosotros, ellos/uds.). We did a choose your own adventure type sentence game with present tense. We also played charades where I would act out something and he would have to conjugate a present tense sentence in spanish and tell me what I was doing.', '45', '2022-06-08 00:56:58', '2022-06-08 00:56:58'),
(1152, 103, 91, 88, '2022-06-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'For hour on 5/15 starting at 5:30pm. Mark and I met while Markus got settled and he asked to be done earlier. He  cut the 1.5 hr into one hour to go to basketball, I had forgot to log in the hour after reviewing their homework and selecting their homework for the next time. SORRY!', '35', '2022-06-08 22:06:12', '2022-06-08 22:06:12'),
(1153, 60, 60, 62, '2022-06-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced plotting points in different quadrants and identifying when the x and y-coordinates are positive and/or negative. Reviewed comprehension questions from The Sword in the Stone Chapter Three.', '20', '2022-06-10 06:09:03', '2022-06-10 06:09:03'),
(1154, 60, 73, 67, '2022-06-08', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed addition and subtraction with regrouping. Spent some time with borrowing in subtraction (ex. 67 is 6 tens and 7 ones, but 5 tens and 17 ones is also 67).', '20', '2022-06-10 06:10:28', '2022-06-10 06:10:28'),
(1155, 60, 66, 67, '2022-06-08', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed finding the GCF and LCM of numbers. Continued practicing addition, subtraction, and multiplication of fractions.', '20', '2022-06-10 06:11:52', '2022-06-10 06:11:52'),
(1156, 94, 45, 46, '2022-06-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we read a book on space in Spanish. We learned many new vocab words, practiced question words, and practiced aquí/acá (here) vs. allí/allá (there). We practiced conversations about summer and about topics he enjoys talking about, such as Mars.', '45', '2022-06-14 23:22:59', '2022-06-14 23:22:59'),
(1157, 60, 75, 72, '2022-06-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Read The Magic Treehouse and reviewed all multiplication with online games.', '20', '2022-06-15 13:04:13', '2022-06-15 13:04:13'),
(1158, 42, 93, 90, '2022-06-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew is approaching the end of his school year so we began by reviewing some of what we worked on throughout the school year. We focused on 3 digit multiplication and complex division, going over strategies to address both.', '54', '2022-06-15 21:11:07', '2022-06-15 21:11:07'),
(1159, 42, 105, 104, '2022-06-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I worked on identifying beginning and ending sounds as well as beginning and ending blends. He is far more confident speaking and asking questions. Alex is very playful and will often pretend not to know the answer, but he is getting much better at being redirected and refocused.', '54', '2022-06-15 21:26:44', '2022-06-15 21:26:44'),
(1160, 42, 104, 102, '2022-06-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I went over the final draft of his book report. His pre-writing was hugely helpful and his final draft was written with confidence. We did a little more writing on the opinion section of the report and Caden seems to be growing in confidence and enjoyment with his writing.', '54', '2022-06-15 21:38:46', '2022-06-15 21:38:46'),
(1161, 42, 105, 104, '2022-06-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I continued practicing identifying phonetic sounds and connecting them with the accompanying letters. We also looked at vocabulary connected to size (big vs. small, heavy vs. light) and some basic number sense.', '54', '2022-06-15 21:43:19', '2022-06-15 21:43:19');
INSERT INTO `timesheets` (`timesheet_id`, `tutor_id`, `student_id`, `user_id`, `date`, `time`, `duration`, `duration2`, `description`, `hourly_pay_rate`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1162, 42, 105, 104, '2022-06-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Alex and I reviewed what we\'ve learned together, focusing on phonemic awareness, number sense, and vocabulary. He has come a long way and was the most chatty he\'s ever been. \r\n\r\nI doubled this session to account for the session we had last pay cycle that wasn\'t covered by credits.', '54', '2022-06-15 21:56:22', '2022-06-17 02:11:00'),
(1163, 42, 93, 90, '2022-06-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew and I discussed factorials, a new concept for him, and a good way for him to continue to practice his multiplication skills. We then finished by working on some more challenging division problems. He is definitely more comfortable with division than he was before and is growing in confidence when it comes to picking the right strategy.', '54', '2022-06-15 22:06:24', '2022-06-15 22:06:24'),
(1164, 60, 60, 62, '2022-06-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Planned out summer sessions. Reviewed Chapter Three and talked about writing in the same tense. Learned how to make in text citations and quotes of quotes. Began reading Chapter Four.', '20', '2022-06-16 04:21:49', '2022-06-16 04:21:49'),
(1167, 60, 73, 67, '2022-06-15', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Read “Should I Share My Ice cream” and finished “Lady and the Tramp” focusing on reading all words and comprehension. Practiced how to borrow for subtraction.', '20', '2022-06-16 04:23:57', '2022-06-16 04:23:57'),
(1168, 94, 45, 46, '2022-06-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon practiced \"voy a + infinitive verb (ir) ____\" sentences saying what he will do and what has he done. It will be very helpful in communicating in spanish. We did an activity about what he will do this summer. We practiced present tense, past tense, and summer vocabulary words and made fun sentences.', '45', '2022-06-16 19:28:03', '2022-06-16 19:28:03'),
(1169, 60, 66, 67, '2022-06-17', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', '(Met on Wednesday but forgot to log) Finished fraction operation worksheet and reviewed division of fractions.', '20', '2022-06-18 00:41:12', '2022-06-18 00:41:12'),
(1170, 42, 104, 102, '2022-06-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In our continued work on reading fluency and comprehension, Caden and I started reading Marcus Samuelsson\'s first cookbook. Caden loves cooking and reading cookbooks, so to get him more excited, I had him read through several recipes and recount the process of making them in his own words. I\'ve never seen Caden more excited about reading. I found that this was also a great way to improve Caden\'s ability to decode unfamiliar words using context clues.', '54', '2022-06-18 03:33:13', '2022-06-18 03:33:13'),
(1171, 42, 93, 90, '2022-06-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Matthew is now on summer vacation so we are now focusing on concepts that will be introduced next school year as well as building Matthew\'s confidence with skills from this past school year. Today we looked at calculating the surface area of rectangular prisms and cubes. Matthew struggled with the idea conceptually, but quickly adapted once he recognized the formula.', '54', '2022-06-20 22:47:18', '2022-06-20 22:47:18'),
(1172, 38, 56, 57, '2022-06-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian is amazing!  He is taking a summer math  course, PLUS meeting with a tutor (ME!) for enrichment.  Mom wants to be sure that Ian is ready for Algebra 2, so my super student and I began a review of the concepts from the past year. And Ian was on fire!  He knew the material as if he wrote the textbook!  Once we are both confident that  Ian is solid with Algebra 1, we will proceed to the new material.  After today\'s performance, I anticipate that it will not take long!  Go Ian!', '50', '2022-06-23 14:16:32', '2022-06-23 14:16:32'),
(1174, 82, 55, 56, '2022-06-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Pre-Calc.  Solved Test review Problems', '45', '2022-06-23 14:50:15', '2022-06-23 14:50:15'),
(1175, 42, 104, 102, '2022-06-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I did another non-fiction critical reading exercise on walruses and the book I’ve been using for him has become too easy. He’s reading faster and with more confidence and I’m on the hunt for more challenging material', '54', '2022-06-27 18:28:04', '2022-06-27 18:28:04'),
(1176, 42, 104, 102, '2022-06-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I did another non-fiction critical reading exercise on walruses and the book I’ve been using for him has become too easy. He’s reading faster and with more confidence and I’m on the hunt for more challenging material', '54', '2022-06-27 18:28:05', '2022-06-27 18:28:05'),
(1177, 42, 104, 102, '2022-06-23', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Caden and I continued with our critical reading book before we returned to looking at the Marcus Samuelson cookbook. He did an excellent job reading the recipes and re-wording them in his own language.', '54', '2022-06-27 18:31:21', '2022-06-27 18:31:21'),
(1178, 94, 58, 59, '2022-06-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Addi and I started \"The Night Diary\", a tale about a young girl writing letters to her deceased mother about her life being half-Muslim half-Hindu in India before the split with Pakistan. We made a \"character list\" to get the characters straight and we practiced context clues, summarizing texts, making educated guesses, and foreshadowing. I learned a little about her and shared a little about me. We finished with a summarizing activity about the setting, characters, plot events, and hypothesizing possible solutions. Addi is off to a fabulous start! I love her energy and positivity!', '45', '2022-06-29 16:50:57', '2022-06-29 16:50:57'),
(1179, 94, 80, 59, '2022-06-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Emme and I started \"Wonder\", a tale about a boy with disabilities dealing with the struggles of going to school and dealing with bullies and other difficulties of being different. We made a \"character list\" to get the characters straight and we practiced context clues, summarizing texts, making educated guesses, and foreshadowing. I learned a little about her and shared a little about me. We made a cost/benefit list about the decision of August going to school and we concluded that the benefits outweigh the costs. We finished with a summarizing activity about the setting, characters, plot events, and hypothesizing possible solutions. I love Emme\'s enthusiasm, kindness, and interest in the book. Both girls are FABULOUS at participating and staying engaged.', '45', '2022-06-29 16:53:19', '2022-06-29 16:53:19'),
(1180, 38, 56, 57, '2022-06-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I are having a blast as we continue to solidify the gains he made throughout the last academic year in Algebra 1.  In the more relaxed environment of summer vacation, my super student is truly shining.  His confidence is high, his questions are great, and his focus is sharp.  Ian has made me one proud tutor!', '50', '2022-06-30 20:58:11', '2022-06-30 20:58:11'),
(1181, 82, 55, 56, '2022-06-30', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Pre Calc review', '45', '2022-07-01 10:55:30', '2022-07-01 10:55:30'),
(1182, 82, 55, 56, '2022-07-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Precalculus Review For Final', '45', '2022-07-06 03:57:10', '2022-07-06 03:57:10'),
(1183, 60, 80, 59, '2022-07-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked with both girls together. Did a full review of decimals. Started with place value and rounding. Then reviewed addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division (with a quick introduction of long division for Emme). Finished with some decimal word problems.', '45', '2022-07-06 21:09:35', '2022-07-06 21:09:35'),
(1184, 38, 56, 57, '2022-07-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Despite the elevated level of distractions during the summer break, Ian is steadfast in his desire to solidify and advance in his math skills.  We are currently spending our time on \"getting ready\" for Algebra 2,which translates into reviewing the skills the student was expected to integrate during Algebra 1.  Ian is definitely demonstrating a higher level of proficiency than during the year.  Hopefully, we will soon transition into acquiring the new tools needed for Algebra 2.  Ian introduced me to \"panel lining\" on \"action figures\", as well as a fairly new Star Wars game that failed to upload during our session.  Maybe next time (I hope!).', '50', '2022-07-07 14:31:53', '2022-07-07 14:31:53'),
(1185, 94, 58, 59, '2022-07-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Addi and I continued reading the Night Diaries. We learned more about India and Pakistan. We practiced writing with the 5 senses and provoking imagery with words. We practiced summarizing, similes/metaphors, and context clues. Addi is a fabulous student and I am enjoying every minute of working with her!', '45', '2022-07-09 19:19:27', '2022-07-09 19:19:27'),
(1186, 94, 80, 59, '2022-07-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emmie and I continued reading \"Wonder\". We read a side resource about how to really help people with disabilities through empowerment instead of doing things for them without asking. We also practiced writing with the 5 senses. We practiced reading skills, sounding out hard words, and prefixes and root words. She is a joy to work with!', '45', '2022-07-09 19:26:57', '2022-07-09 19:26:57'),
(1187, 60, 60, 62, '2022-07-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Talked about discussion questions from Chapters 3 and 4. Worked on the Khan Academy pre assessment.', '20', '2022-07-13 14:26:09', '2022-07-13 14:26:09'),
(1188, 60, 75, 72, '2022-07-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed multiplication facts from 2-6. Learned about perimeter and area.', '20', '2022-07-13 14:26:39', '2022-07-13 14:26:39'),
(1189, 38, 56, 57, '2022-07-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Factoring by grouping was the highlight of today\'s session with Ian.  Actually, Ian\'s quick refresh and return to proficiency was the true highlight.  Ian maintains a super attitude as we review this summer, and I am proud of his tremendous progress. We ended the session with a first hand exposure to Ian\'s high level of talent at a Star Wars video game.  May the force continue to be with you Ian!', '50', '2022-07-14 16:55:18', '2022-07-14 16:55:18'),
(1190, 38, 110, 108, '2022-07-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a pleasure to begin work today with Leighton, a gifted young man with stellar character traits who has requested tutoring assistance with a pre-algebra requirement from the prior academic year. It is clear that Leighton has a solid foundation of skills, and my role will be \"refresh\" them as much as possible so that he will be able to easily access them for the more advanced material of the next school year. We began with a simulated \"pre-algebra final exam\", and I was extremely impressed with Leighton\'s quick ability to learn and integrate. I am optimistic that with serious review and regular practice outside of the sessions,  Leighton will be able to achieve his goals. I truly look forward to working with him. Great work Leighton!', '50', '2022-07-14 22:17:14', '2022-07-14 22:17:14'),
(1191, 60, 73, 67, '2022-07-13', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Learned about coins (there names, how much they are worth, and how many of them fit in a dollar)', '20', '2022-07-15 15:13:55', '2022-07-15 15:14:04'),
(1192, 60, 66, 67, '2022-07-13', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed fraction operations, LCM, and GCF.', '20', '2022-07-15 15:15:00', '2022-07-15 15:15:00'),
(1193, 60, 60, 62, '2022-07-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed how to factor expressions with like terms. Discussed chapter 5 of The Sword in the Stone.', '20', '2022-07-15 15:16:41', '2022-07-15 15:16:41'),
(1194, 38, 110, 108, '2022-07-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton and I are actually having fun in covering a miscellany of Pre-Algebra topics,  I attribute the positive atmosphere to this young man\'s great attitude and strong desire to grow. For purposes of the contract with the school, I am tracking the topics we cover, as well as areas that Leighton may need some additional support.  He is doing great!', '50', '2022-07-15 20:57:24', '2022-07-15 20:57:24'),
(1195, 94, 58, 59, '2022-07-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Addi and I continued reading \"The Night Diaries\" and learned more about India and Pakistan. We practiced imagery, personification, and using context clues to figure out unknown words. We did an exercise on writing letters. Addi decided to write a letter to her dog that passed away. It was a very sweet letter and we went over how writing can be a healthy coping mechanism and how letters are the best gifts.', '45', '2022-07-16 03:32:28', '2022-07-16 03:32:28'),
(1196, 94, 80, 59, '2022-07-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Emme and I continued reading \"Wonder\". I love her take on the book and how engaged she is when reading and analyzing. We went over using journaling as a healthy coping tool and she wrote a journal entry based on the book.', '45', '2022-07-16 03:35:02', '2022-07-16 03:35:02'),
(1197, 94, 45, 46, '2022-07-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon and I reviewed Spanish present tense, past tense, and present progressive. We played a game to jog his memory on family members\' names. We then practiced writing a post card from disney world where he went and practiced weiting sentences with the verb tenses we went over.', '45', '2022-07-16 03:36:08', '2022-07-16 03:36:08'),
(1198, 38, 110, 108, '2022-07-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton is climbing the learning curve and should be proud of his progress.  Today, we reviewed functions, graphs, and various algebraic skills, with my super student demonstrating well his ability to learn and integrate.  I am optimistic that Leighton will achieve the goals he has established for himself through our collaboration. Great work Leighton!', '50', '2022-07-20 18:56:25', '2022-07-20 18:56:25'),
(1199, 94, 45, 46, '2022-07-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We went over the difference between \"ser\" y \"estar\" and practiced the doctor/place pneumonic. We went over conjugations and made sentences. Brendon seems to enjoy patterns and pneumonic devices. He struggles in retaining information that we go over and over. I have been working with him on patterns and trying to tailor our lessons to the way he thinks, with formulas and patterns. I am trying to help him to feel more comfortable talking and making mistakes because that is part of the language-learning process. He just needs to go over conjugations more on his own.', '45', '2022-07-21 21:29:11', '2022-07-21 21:29:11'),
(1200, 38, 110, 108, '2022-07-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton is a marvel to work with!  In our tour of pre-algebra concepts today, we covered exponents, box plots and proportions.  My super student is able to refresh many concepts that have become stale through inactivity, and these advances will serve him well entering next year.  Keep growing Leighton.  You are doing great!', '50', '2022-07-22 13:59:55', '2022-07-22 13:59:55'),
(1202, 60, 58, 59, '2022-07-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed first couple of pages of summer review packet. Practiced with fraction operations and the order of operations.', '45', '2022-07-23 17:58:25', '2022-07-23 17:58:25'),
(1203, 60, 80, 59, '2022-07-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Went over beginning of math summer review packet. Talked about place value, decimal operations, and exponents.', '45', '2022-07-23 18:00:05', '2022-07-23 18:00:05'),
(1204, 60, 73, 67, '2022-07-20', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed coins and practiced writing and spelling while creating a full coin guide.', '20', '2022-07-23 18:13:03', '2022-07-23 18:13:03'),
(1205, 60, 66, 67, '2022-07-20', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Continued practicing fraction operations in the new Spectrum book.', '20', '2022-07-23 18:18:00', '2022-07-23 18:18:00'),
(1206, 60, 60, 62, '2022-07-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced factoring expressions and combining like terms on Khan Academy. Reviewed quotation marks and in-text citations.', '20', '2022-07-23 18:23:02', '2022-07-23 18:23:02'),
(1207, 94, 58, 59, '2022-07-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Addi and I continued reading \"The Night Diary\", which we are almost finished with. We discussed literary devices such as \"idiom\", \"pun\", and \"hyperbole\". We discussed first person, second person, and third person. Her job was to write part of the story from a different character perspective and I had to guess who it was. I gave her homework of finishing the book and highlighting the words we went over and the figurative language.', '45', '2022-07-26 04:17:02', '2022-07-26 04:17:02'),
(1208, 94, 80, 59, '2022-07-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emme and I continued reading \"Wonder\". We discussed the importance of storytelling and learning our histories. We also discussed literary devices such as \"idiom\", \"personification\" and \"onomatopoeia\". She has the homework of continuing reading and calling her grandparents to ask about their stories growing up. I want her to practice creative writing and healthy coping mechanisms such as journaling. I love her happiness and passion for the story!', '45', '2022-07-26 04:20:02', '2022-07-26 04:21:00'),
(1209, 94, 80, 59, '2022-07-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emme and I continued reading Wonder. We went over the homework and reviewed the literary devices we learned last week. We did an exercise on first, second, and third person in writing. I assigned her to write from a different perspective of a character other than August from the book. We also discussed genetics and different facial deformities as that is a theme in the book. I love Emme\'s curiosity and her genuine enthusiasm. She was so sweet to ask me when I was graduating Nursing School and was so happy for me. I told her if I can do it, so can you! Which is the truth!', '45', '2022-07-28 04:01:42', '2022-07-28 04:01:42'),
(1210, 94, 58, 59, '2022-07-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Since Addi finished the book \"The Night DIary\", we did several reflection activities. We broke down the ending, our thoughts, and reflected on the story overall. We listened to the author of the book and the editor have a conversation about their inspiration for the book and their childhoods. We read a piece on \"cultural goggles\" and learned more about Pakistani culture. We then went over her writing assignment and I helped her do some planning. Addi is so bright and a joy to work with!', '45', '2022-07-28 04:08:44', '2022-07-28 04:08:44'),
(1211, 94, 45, 46, '2022-07-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon and I reviewed the verb \"tener\", both present and past tenses. Then we played a board game using tener + hambre, sed, miedo, sueño, etc. to make sentences about being hungry, thirsty, scared, and tired. Brendon seemed to be doing a lot better today. I gave him some extra time to answer questions and let him figure it out, which seemed to work well.', '45', '2022-07-28 04:10:53', '2022-07-28 04:10:53'),
(1212, 38, 110, 108, '2022-07-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton and I kept the momentum going as we continues to refresh pre-algebra concepts that have become stale to inactivity.  I recommend that Leighton do his best to find some quiet time between sessions to review on his own as well.  He is a pleasure to work with.', '50', '2022-07-28 20:34:56', '2022-07-28 20:34:56'),
(1213, 38, 110, 108, '2022-07-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton and I finished up the week strongly, once again being exposed to formulating and solving simultaneous equations. I learned that he will be taking a practice exam to formulate a baseline, and I look forward to working with Leighton to leave that baseline in the dust by the end of our tutoring engagement.  Of course, Leighton is aware of our mutual responsibility to make that happen. He is doing great!', '50', '2022-07-29 13:17:38', '2022-07-29 13:17:38'),
(1214, 60, 75, 72, '2022-07-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed practice in Advanced 2nd Grade book with patterns and writing numbers.', '20', '2022-07-30 02:22:16', '2022-07-30 02:22:16'),
(1215, 60, 58, 59, '2022-07-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed math summer review packet. Practiced order of operations and adding and subtracting fractions by finding a like denominator.', '45', '2022-07-30 02:23:49', '2022-07-30 02:28:41'),
(1216, 60, 80, 59, '2022-07-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed math summer packet. Practiced long division with decimals and learned how to find a remainder in decimal form.', '45', '2022-07-30 02:29:40', '2022-07-30 02:29:40'),
(1217, 60, 73, 67, '2022-07-27', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced money by having a store. Reviewed how to tell the coins apart, how much they are worth, and how to make change.', '20', '2022-07-30 02:30:21', '2022-07-30 02:30:21'),
(1218, 60, 66, 67, '2022-07-27', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced adding fractions that have different denominators and finding like denominators using the LCM.', '20', '2022-07-30 03:30:39', '2022-07-30 03:30:39'),
(1219, 60, 60, 62, '2022-07-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced finding equal expressions and combining like terms on Khan Academy.', '20', '2022-07-30 03:31:55', '2022-07-30 03:31:55'),
(1220, 38, 56, 57, '2022-07-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was factoring, factoring, and more factoring  today, as Ian and I covered factoring quadratics with differences of squares among other critical foundational concepts for Algebra 2.  We plan to begin with the distributive property for polynomial operations at our next session.  Ian is having a great summer!', '50', '2022-07-31 20:33:59', '2022-07-31 20:33:59'),
(1221, 38, 110, 108, '2022-08-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton had a tough football practice yesterday, yet still came through to have our session today.  We are nearing the end of the pre-algebra review, and Leighton seems to be managing to refresh several concepts.  I will contact Mom to discuss the best direction to go after we complete the review.', '50', '2022-08-03 14:46:25', '2022-08-03 14:46:25'),
(1222, 60, 75, 72, '2022-08-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed how to add and subtract two digit numbers with regrouping. Started reading the first passage in Reading Spectrum book and answered a comprehension question.', '20', '2022-08-04 05:06:23', '2022-08-04 05:06:23'),
(1223, 60, 80, 59, '2022-08-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed finding the LCM and GCF of two numbers. Practiced fraction operations.', '45', '2022-08-04 05:07:18', '2022-08-04 05:07:18'),
(1224, 60, 73, 67, '2022-08-03', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Went over homework. Practiced adding and subtracting two two-digit numbers without regrouping. Completed some money practice.', '20', '2022-08-04 05:08:02', '2022-08-04 05:08:02'),
(1225, 60, 66, 67, '2022-08-03', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed how to simplify fractions and convert them from improper fractions to mixed numbers and vice versa. Reviewed factorization and when numbers were divisible by 2, 3, 5, 6, and 10.', '20', '2022-08-04 05:12:35', '2022-08-04 05:12:35'),
(1226, 60, 60, 62, '2022-08-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced with beginning algebraic operations with adding, subtracting, dividing, and multiplying. Reviewed angles and how to deconstruct them.', '20', '2022-08-04 05:13:21', '2022-08-04 05:13:21'),
(1227, 94, 58, 59, '2022-08-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We started by going over her assignment, a letter to her future self such as the story we read, The Night Diary. I showed her how I like to make checklists for each assignment, ensuring that all instructions and requirements are met. We went over hers, found the missing requirements, and she wrote a new letter including the new ones. We went over gratitude journals. We then started a new book \"The Key from Spain\" based on a true story about a Jewish woman fleeing Spain during WWII to Croatia and then to the US. I am impressed by her analysis of the take-home messages/themes of the story such as the importance of music, family, and tradition.', '45', '2022-08-04 19:53:12', '2022-08-04 19:53:12'),
(1228, 94, 80, 59, '2022-08-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Emme and I continued reading Wonder. She did an exercise to further practice perspectives such as first person, second person, and third person by making a Yearbook for the main character. We signed the yearbook from other characters in the story and then had Auggie sign the yearbooks of his classmates. I love her creative answers. We discussed how to treat people with disabilities normally and the importance of apologizing (from the story). I love her kind spirit!', '45', '2022-08-04 19:55:42', '2022-08-04 19:55:42'),
(1229, 38, 56, 57, '2022-08-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian had a summer assignment that needed attention, so we spent today\'s session on that item.  The focus of the practice set was binomial multiplication and factoring, and it seems that Ian\'s confidence has increased significantly since his \"early days\" of tutoring.  We ended the session with a lecture and visual tour of two models that Ian had recently fabricated.  Thank you Ian!', '50', '2022-08-04 20:14:04', '2022-08-04 20:14:04'),
(1230, 38, 110, 108, '2022-08-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton and I completed the pre-algebra practice exam we have been working on, and proceeded to circle back to really focus on those concepts that he has found troublesome. Today, we spent some time on adding and subtracting integers; by the end of our practice, it seemed that Leighton had become more proficient.  We plan to continue along the same lines next week before wrapping up the summer tutoring engagement.  Good work, Leighton!', '50', '2022-08-08 15:50:27', '2022-08-08 15:50:27'),
(1231, 38, 110, 108, '2022-08-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'In our next to last session, Leighton and I had a strategy session with Mom about how best to serve Leighton now and in the future.  Leighton and I then began our final push to focus on topics with which he has struggled.  Today\'s highlight was arithmetic and geometric sequences, which in actuality, Leighton claimed to have never encountered.  He now has an enriching too to take into next year.  Good work Leighton!', '50', '2022-08-10 13:33:57', '2022-08-10 13:33:57'),
(1232, 38, 56, 57, '2022-08-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I continues with his summer work, and today focused on functions, domains, and ranges.  I have definitely seen tangible growth in Ian\'s understanding of many fundamental concepts, and remain optimistic that this advancement will continue.  Great job Ian!', '50', '2022-08-11 12:40:25', '2022-08-11 12:40:25'),
(1233, 94, 58, 59, '2022-08-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addi and I started a new book \"New Vacancy\" about a family struggling to run a motel. I am impressed with Addi\'s interest in the book, critical thinking skills, and predictions about the plot. We went over her work for her assignment, made some corrections and additions, and did an activity about reflecting and making predictions when reading. I love her enthusiasm and kindness!', '45', '2022-08-11 23:36:33', '2022-08-11 23:36:33'),
(1234, 94, 80, 59, '2022-08-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'They accidentally overslept so I only saw Emme for a little bit (mom OK\'d the credit for the lesson). But I gave her an assignment and quickly went over the new part of the book that she read. I am excited to get started on her school assignment once we finish \"Wonder\" and make comparisons of the book and the movie.', '45', '2022-08-11 23:38:10', '2022-08-11 23:38:10'),
(1235, 38, 110, 108, '2022-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leighton and I wrapped up our summer tutoring engagement today with a review of the slope intercept formula of a line, as well as \"translation\" skills for word problems.  I wish Leighton only success as he begins Algebra 1, and want him to know that I am available for additional support throughout the academic year if needed.  Leighton, you are a pleasure to work with.  Have a great football season!', '50', '2022-08-12 14:54:28', '2022-08-12 14:54:28'),
(1236, 94, 45, 46, '2022-08-11', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon and I went over ways to say \"I like, I really like, so/so, and I really don\'t like\" in Spanish. We did an exercise on things Brendon likes and I taught him how to ask me if I liked those things. We practiced commands (mandatos). We reviewed the verbs ir present (to go), poder (to be able to), and ser/estar (to be). I am trying to encourage Brendon to be comfortable making mistakes and trying in Spanish instead of defaulting to English. This will get better and better with time, but I want to help him to break his fear of making mistakes. Es normal! (it\'s normal!)', '45', '2022-08-12 23:55:24', '2022-08-12 23:55:24'),
(1241, 60, 73, 67, '2022-08-10', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed adding and subtracting with regrouping for the last time! Reviewed capitalization rules.', '20', '2022-08-13 02:08:02', '2022-08-13 02:08:02'),
(1242, 60, 75, 72, '2022-08-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on addition and subtraction with regrouping, with a little bit of word problems.', '20', '2022-08-13 02:08:19', '2022-08-13 02:08:19'),
(1243, 60, 58, 59, '2022-08-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed incorrect fraction operations from two weeks ago. Worked on putting fractions in order from least to greatest and solving proportions with cross multiplication. Practiced converting fractions, decimals, and percentages. Started negative number operations.', '45', '2022-08-13 02:08:33', '2022-08-13 02:08:33'),
(1244, 60, 80, 59, '2022-08-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed fraction practice problems from Addi\'s packet and practiced plotting points on Khan Academy.', '45', '2022-08-13 02:08:55', '2022-08-13 02:08:55'),
(1245, 60, 66, 67, '2022-08-10', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed how to add and subtract with regrouping.', '20', '2022-08-13 02:09:11', '2022-08-13 02:09:11'),
(1246, 60, 60, 62, '2022-08-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced finding the area of shapes by splitting them into rectangles and triangles on Khan Academy. Reviewed the proper format for writing quotes. Discussed Sword in the Stone.', '20', '2022-08-13 02:20:02', '2022-08-13 02:20:02'),
(1247, 82, 111, 109, '2022-08-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Parabolic Equations-Algebra', '54', '2022-08-17 03:30:12', '2022-08-17 03:30:12'),
(1248, 82, 111, 109, '2022-08-16', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Algebra-Graphing Parabolic Equations', '54', '2022-08-17 03:31:49', '2022-08-17 03:31:49'),
(1249, 38, 56, 57, '2022-08-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'As Ian and I approach the end of the summer, he continues to impress with his great attitude and dynamic work ethic towards his \"non-mandatory\" studies.  We continued our introduction to Algebra 2 concepts (partially involving the strengthening of Algebra 1 concepts), with  Ian demonstrating that his math skills are aging like a \"fine wine\". Today\'s highlights included functions and their transformations, which we will delve into deeper at our next session.  Ian is on the ball!', '50', '2022-08-18 13:45:04', '2022-08-18 13:45:04'),
(1250, 94, 58, 59, '2022-08-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'This week, since Addi is going to Puerto Rico soon, we did a lesson all about Puerto Rico. We read a book all about Puerto Rico\'s history and their current status as a \"commonwealth\" and what that means. We reviewed context clues and deciphering difficult words and concepts. We learned about Puerto Rican traditions, culture, foods, and beautiful places. We reflected on the concept of colonization and the pros/cons of Puerto Rican statehood. I enjoyed giving the reading lesson since I spent a summer in Puerto Rico a few years ago.', '45', '2022-08-22 06:02:20', '2022-08-22 06:02:20'),
(1251, 94, 80, 59, '2022-08-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We finished the book \"Wonder\" and reflected on the ending and the development of the different characters. We did several activities reflecting on the characters, the precepts, and the significant quotes from the book. We watched a video on the real person that plays Auggie in the movie and his hundreds of surgeries. We also watched a video on the author reflecting on what the book meant to her. We finished one activity from her summer assignments together and I gave her the homework of watching the movie and starting the other homework assignments comparing the book and the movie.', '45', '2022-08-22 06:05:18', '2022-08-22 06:05:18'),
(1252, 60, 75, 72, '2022-08-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Set up a new reward system with beads and stickers. Reviewed addition and subtraction with regrouping and completed 3 Ken-ken puzzles. Worked on quick addition and subtraction mental math. Reviewed proper and common nouns and started a crossword puzzle.', '20', '2022-08-25 03:51:21', '2022-08-25 03:51:21'),
(1253, 60, 66, 67, '2022-08-24', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Finished worksheet about subtraction with regrouping. Worked on mixed multiplication facts from 1-10.', '20', '2022-08-25 03:51:59', '2022-08-25 03:51:59'),
(1254, 60, 73, 67, '2022-08-24', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced writing numbers by splitting them into hundreds, tens, and ones and also writing them out in words. Completed a worksheet comparing three digit numbers.', '20', '2022-08-25 03:53:12', '2022-08-25 03:53:12'),
(1255, 38, 56, 57, '2022-08-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It as \"absolutely\" a great session today with Ian, as we focused on transformations of absolute value functions.  In addition, my super student gave me a guided tour of his \"action figure\" portfolio.  We plan to change our session time next week as Ian is returning to school. You had a great summer Ian.  Let\'s carry it through to the upcoming academic year!', '50', '2022-08-25 14:56:52', '2022-08-25 14:56:52'),
(1256, 94, 45, 46, '2022-08-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, I gave Brendon a lesson on the parts of the body in Spanish, and also a mini-lesson on medical spanish. I taught him the basics of what to say at the doctor\'s office if something is hurting and different important medical words in Spanish. We reviewed a lot of the parts of the body multiple times and I had Brendon point to them, repeat them, and then we filled out a blank labeled diagram. I had Brendon come up with situations/stories of how his friends or how he hurt different parts of the body and how to say that to a doctor in Spanish. It was a fun lesson and I was happy of how he is working around unknown words better and not asking me every single word.', '45', '2022-08-25 21:48:26', '2022-08-25 21:48:26'),
(1257, 60, 80, 59, '2022-08-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed plotting points on Khan Academy. Practiced comparing fractions and place value. Reviewed dividing and multiplying with decimals.', '45', '2022-08-29 18:18:08', '2022-08-29 18:18:08'),
(1258, 60, 58, 59, '2022-08-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed long division. Practiced with negative number operations and order of operations with negative numbers.', '45', '2022-08-29 18:19:39', '2022-08-29 18:19:39'),
(1259, 94, 58, 59, '2022-08-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Addie learned about journaling techniques, writing about feelings, questions, beliefs, things you learned, and reflecting on experiences. She practiced this teaching by writing about her experience traveling to Puerto Rico. I love how she reflected on the loss of power after Hurricane Maria and she has such great empathy to reflect on how difficult that would be. We continued reading \"No Vacancy\", and we made a pro/con list about moving from the city to the county like the character in the book. I love Addie\'s passion and love for reading and stories! She is so empathetic and kind.', '45', '2022-08-31 15:15:49', '2022-08-31 15:15:49'),
(1260, 94, 80, 59, '2022-08-31', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Emme and I also went over the importance of journaling. I had her do a different type of journal, based on her feelings, emotions, and reflecting on how she will be tomorrow with her new teachings. She said that she is proud of herself for not touching a parrot again with a no touch sign in Puerto Rico, which I thought was really sweet and honest. She also reflected that she will be nicer to her sister. I reassured her that sister drama is normal and the fact that she is even conscious of her actions is a step ahead of most. We then went over and finished all of her summer assignments for \"Wonder\", reflecting on the differences between the book and the movie. I love her kind and patient spirit!', '45', '2022-08-31 15:40:18', '2022-08-31 15:40:18'),
(1261, 60, 73, 67, '2022-08-31', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Continued working on writing numbers in expanded form and writing them out in words. Wrote two sentences about her favorite part of school.', '20', '2022-09-01 05:36:38', '2022-09-01 05:36:38'),
(1262, 60, 66, 67, '2022-08-31', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced with mixed multiplication', '20', '2022-09-01 05:36:55', '2022-09-01 05:36:55'),
(1263, 38, 56, 57, '2022-09-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Since Ian had just started school this week, he did not have much work in the way of assignments. So we continued in our preparatory work for Algebra 2, including solving for zeroes, and utilizing various forms of the equation of the parabola.  We will continue along those lines at our next session, as well as support Ian in his homework assignments.  I look forward to a great year for Ian!.', '50', '2022-09-01 23:02:14', '2022-09-01 23:02:14'),
(1264, 38, 111, 109, '2022-09-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a pleasure to begin work today with Mason, a bright young man with stellar character traits who has requested support in geometry for the upcoming academic year.  Mason was prepared, focused, and quite eager to learn and understand.  We began with his current assignment, which dealt with geometric constructions.  Although challenging, we clarified several concepts and enabled Mason to keep on track.  I am confident that with disciplined review and practice, Mason can have a productive year.  I look forward to working with this hard working young man.', '50', '2022-09-02 02:22:33', '2022-09-02 02:22:33'),
(1265, 60, 60, 62, '2022-09-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on editing letter to English teacher. Focused on organizing ideas and editing for fluency.', '30', '2022-09-04 02:06:32', '2022-09-04 02:06:32'),
(1266, 38, 56, 57, '2022-09-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian came today with an interesting assignment involving \"block functions\" and sequence formulas.  I appreciate very much that he provide page 1 as well so that I could piece together the assignment. I encouraged my super student to be diligent to bring everything we will need to be efficient with our time.  It\'s a new year, and all beginnings are difficult. Ian is in for a great year!', '50', '2022-09-08 16:29:41', '2022-09-08 16:29:41'),
(1267, 38, 111, 109, '2022-09-07', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'What a great session for Mason and me today!  We continued with our deep dive into geometric constructions, with Mason being very engaged, inquisitive, and ultimately very successful.  I can see that this young man is very motivated to learn, and his efforts are being rewarded.  Mason is a a pleasure to work with!', '50', '2022-09-08 16:34:05', '2022-09-08 16:34:05'),
(1268, 94, 45, 46, '2022-09-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon did an activity reviewing the parts of the body in Spanish. We played a quick game practicing listening and talking in Spanish where I asked him to name things that he saw, almost like I spy. We reviewed present and past tense verbs because Brendon will be learning past tense again in class and I wanted him to be ahead. Lastly, we read an article about cats in Spanish in honor of Snowball, his newest furry friend.', '45', '2022-09-08 21:47:35', '2022-09-08 21:47:35'),
(1269, 60, 73, 67, '2022-09-07', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Corrected school assignment with backwards \"b\"s and \"d\"s and some spelling mistakes. Worked on a short writing assignment about her least favorite thing at school.', '30', '2022-09-10 20:37:22', '2022-09-10 20:37:22'),
(1270, 60, 66, 67, '2022-09-07', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced multiplication in the workbook. Reviewed place value and rounding.', '30', '2022-09-10 20:38:00', '2022-09-10 20:38:00'),
(1271, 60, 75, 72, '2022-09-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced fast fact addition. Read a short story and answered comprehension questions. Worked on multiplication.', '30', '2022-09-10 20:50:58', '2022-09-10 20:50:58'),
(1272, 60, 60, 62, '2022-09-08', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Met online. Worked on missed school reading comprehension assignment. Practiced negative number operations on Khan Academy.', '30', '2022-09-10 20:53:43', '2022-09-10 20:53:43'),
(1273, 38, 111, 109, '2022-09-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I worked our way through several geometric construction practice problems on our way to ensuring that he would be ready for his exam.  With the aid of some graphics found on the web, we were able to develop confidence and proficiency in replicating the constructions.  Mason, as always, was extremely conscientious to ensure that he felt solid in his skills. I am confident that he will come through with a \"win\" on the quiz.  Go Mason!', '50', '2022-09-13 16:41:38', '2022-09-13 16:41:38'),
(1274, 60, 73, 67, '2022-09-14', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on completing a writing prompt about her favorite season. Practiced finding the greatest number out of 2, three-digit numbers. Practiced counting three-digit numbers.', '30', '2022-09-15 14:35:51', '2022-09-15 14:35:51'),
(1275, 60, 66, 67, '2022-09-14', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced multiplication and explaining fractions in terms of decimals.', '30', '2022-09-15 14:38:51', '2022-09-15 14:38:51'),
(1276, 38, 56, 57, '2022-09-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian and I worked on vertex form and standard form for quadratics, and even learned how to develop the standard equation given three points in the plane.  I had Ian do one himself, and he successfully demonstrated that he will be able to do it on his own.  It is truly rewarding to watch this young man grow in his skills and confidence.', '50', '2022-09-15 14:53:45', '2022-09-15 14:53:45'),
(1277, 38, 111, 109, '2022-09-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I graduated form geometric constructions (for the most part), and transitioned into transformations today, specifically those of the rigid variety. Mason thinks that his quiz earlier in the week went well, and I am anxious to hear of his great results.  He continues to be focused, and asks great questions. Mason\'s progress is truly inspiring.', '50', '2022-09-15 14:59:31', '2022-09-15 14:59:31'),
(1278, 94, 45, 46, '2022-09-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we went over grammar, estar/ser, family member names, animals such as farm animals, and we played tic tac toe with sentences in Spanish. It was a fun class and I am happy to see Brendon enjoying learning Spanish!', '45', '2022-09-15 22:32:22', '2022-09-15 22:32:22'),
(1279, 60, 60, 62, '2022-09-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed scalar multiples in shapes. Talked about how area increases when you increase the side length of a square. (ex. side length increases by 2, area increases by 2^2). Practiced adding and subtracting negative numbers.', '30', '2022-09-16 00:26:26', '2022-09-16 00:26:26'),
(1280, 34, 45, 46, '2022-09-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Histograms, reviewed how to find the median in an even data set, and played KenKen.', '75', '2022-09-20 00:04:45', '2022-09-20 00:04:45'),
(1281, 38, 111, 109, '2022-09-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I covered a miscellany of transformation problems today, including ones involving \"translation vectors.\"  My super student is more that just \"keeping up\", as he even challenges me when he sees things a different way.  His input is so appreciated, and keeps me on my toes.  Mason is conscientious, motivated, and  growing!  He is doing great!', '50', '2022-09-20 15:14:44', '2022-09-20 15:14:44'),
(1282, 60, 60, 62, '2022-09-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on memorizing the location of European countries by working through a European online map quiz. Looked over math quiz and talked about all incorrect questions. Reviewed how to do quiz corrections for class.', '30', '2022-09-21 03:45:26', '2022-09-21 03:45:26'),
(1283, 38, 56, 57, '2022-09-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian\'s instructor is providing the students with excellent opportunities to review and strengthen previously learned concepts, and that is good news!  Today, my super student and I encountered the various methods of factoring, which gave us an opportunity to truly anchor these concepts.  Ian surely benefitted from it, and he should be well prepared tom further advance in the class.  Great work ian!', '50', '2022-09-21 13:56:44', '2022-09-21 13:56:44'),
(1284, 34, 91, 88, '2022-09-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Prep for upcoming test: basic functions, word problems, properties of addition and multiplication', '79', '2022-09-22 00:20:37', '2022-09-22 00:20:37'),
(1285, 60, 73, 67, '2022-09-21', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Completed a writing prompt about her favorite holiday and why. Practiced skip counting forward and backwards by different numbers with three-digits.', '30', '2022-09-22 14:09:49', '2022-09-22 14:09:49'),
(1286, 60, 66, 67, '2022-09-21', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced multiplication with fast facts and two pages of practice questions.', '30', '2022-09-22 14:10:14', '2022-09-22 14:10:14'),
(1287, 38, 111, 109, '2022-09-21', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I continued our journey through rigid transformations, looking at them from various perspectives to enhance our understanding of their structure and function.  Mason is demonstrating that he is learning and integrating the various concepts.  We even began to examine rotational symmetry today.  Mason is, without a doubt, on an upward trajectory.  He is doing great!', '50', '2022-09-22 14:25:17', '2022-09-22 14:25:17'),
(1288, 94, 45, 46, '2022-09-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, we went over planning for his future project. We chose a friend of his to be his pretend exchange student friend from Puerto Rico. We practiced asking and answering interview-style introductory questions (which is super common and he will definitely use). We also did a whole lesson on accents. We did several worksheets on accent marks and I had him sound them out and practice using accents over different vowels. I taught him some tricks and patterns to make this easier in the future.', '45', '2022-09-22 22:01:10', '2022-09-22 22:01:10'),
(1289, 60, 75, 72, '2022-09-22', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on school math assignments with adding, subtracting, and rounding.', '30', '2022-09-22 23:34:44', '2022-09-22 23:34:44'),
(1290, 96, 112, 110, '2022-09-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Did math homework, learned grid method for multiplication, and worked on math facts.', '20', '2022-09-25 20:30:00', '2022-09-25 20:30:00'),
(1291, 34, 45, 46, '2022-09-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Problem Solving word problems, with a focus on mean.', '75', '2022-09-27 00:10:01', '2022-09-27 00:10:01'),
(1292, 34, 91, 88, '2022-09-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Reviewed errors from recent test, practiced combining like terms. Nerdle.', '79', '2022-09-29 00:25:54', '2022-09-29 00:25:54'),
(1293, 38, 111, 109, '2022-09-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although the intent of some of the questions in Mason\'s most recent assignment was not clear to us, we did our best to give a viable interpretation.  In the process, we did a solid review of rigid transformations as well as both reflective and rotational symmetry.  Mason always comes ready to work and does not coast at all.  He is doing very well, and is a pleasure to work with.', '50', '2022-09-29 19:44:59', '2022-09-29 19:44:59'),
(1294, 94, 45, 46, '2022-09-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon and I reviewed saber vs. conocer and their different uses (to know vs. to meet). We played a \"I\'m thinking of a person\" game where I asked him questions and tried to guess who he was and vice versa. This was a fun exercise to practice question words in spanish and past tense verbs. Brendon guessed all of my people soooo fast though!', '45', '2022-09-29 22:57:04', '2022-09-29 22:57:04'),
(1295, 60, 60, 62, '2022-09-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Checked over Canvas. Worked on European map. Practiced scalars on Khan Academy. Talked about using ratios to equate scalars. Set up a homework and agenda book plan.', '30', '2022-09-30 04:52:35', '2022-09-30 04:52:35'),
(1296, 60, 73, 67, '2022-09-28', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Completed writing prompt about her favorite candy. Practiced counting up and down by 5s, 10s, and 100s.', '30', '2022-09-30 04:53:09', '2022-09-30 04:53:09'),
(1297, 60, 66, 67, '2022-09-28', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced multiplication and factoring numbers.', '30', '2022-09-30 04:53:58', '2022-09-30 04:53:58'),
(1298, 60, 75, 72, '2022-09-29', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Practiced subtracting two digit numbers from three digit numbers. Worked on rounding to the nearest tens and hundreds place. Worked on a word search.', '30', '2022-09-30 05:12:18', '2022-09-30 05:12:18'),
(1299, 96, 114, 112, '2022-09-26', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on area model and long divison', '20', '2022-10-01 11:11:53', '2022-10-01 11:11:53'),
(1300, 96, 115, 112, '2022-09-26', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced addition and subtraction methods', '20', '2022-10-01 11:12:22', '2022-10-01 11:12:22'),
(1301, 96, 112, 110, '2022-09-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Did homework, revisited area model, and practiced math facts', '20', '2022-10-01 11:12:49', '2022-10-01 11:12:49'),
(1302, 34, 45, 46, '2022-10-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Box and Whisker Plots', '75', '2022-10-04 00:02:16', '2022-10-04 00:02:16'),
(1304, 38, 111, 109, '2022-10-04', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason\'s teacher is certainly into review, review, and more review. But we do not mind.  Even though we  see many of the same transformation problems from week to week, we always manage to gain a new fact or insight.  Mason is building himself up to proficiency before our very eyes. Great work Mason!', '50', '2022-10-04 14:59:01', '2022-10-04 14:59:01'),
(1305, 82, 117, 99, '2022-10-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Explained angles conversion, degrees to radians and visa versa.  Solved worksheet.', '50', '2022-10-05 18:25:16', '2022-10-11 01:12:17');
INSERT INTO `timesheets` (`timesheet_id`, `tutor_id`, `student_id`, `user_id`, `date`, `time`, `duration`, `duration2`, `description`, `hourly_pay_rate`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1306, 94, 45, 46, '2022-10-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, Brendon and I studied his vocab words for class, and practiced asking each other question words. We practiced conversations and reviewed question words. I taught him my study techniques and how much I love flash cards. We then played a game of who am I (I\'m thinking of a person).', '45', '2022-10-06 22:40:57', '2022-10-06 22:40:57'),
(1307, 60, 60, 62, '2022-10-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Met online. Checked over everything on Canvas. Worked on the European map and finding the scalar in scale figures.', '30', '2022-10-06 23:57:41', '2022-10-06 23:57:41'),
(1308, 60, 75, 72, '2022-10-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on school math homework and rounding exercises in the Spectrum book.', '30', '2022-10-06 23:58:24', '2022-10-06 23:58:24'),
(1309, 38, 56, 57, '2022-10-06', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian is getting into some truly \"complex\" topics, but we did our best to keep it \"real\".  In this evening\'s session, we covered the gamut from natural numbers to complex numbers, as well as using vectors to add and subtract the latter in the complex plane. We took a \"rational\" approach to it all, and Ian came out \"whole\" with no nicks or cuts.  Great job Ian!', '50', '2022-10-07 14:24:34', '2022-10-07 14:24:34'),
(1310, 82, 117, 99, '2022-10-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Trig functions equations and graphs', '50', '2022-10-10 19:13:27', '2022-10-10 19:13:27'),
(1311, 34, 45, 46, '2022-10-10', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on an Act-3 task, IT All Adds Up', '75', '2022-10-11 00:09:40', '2022-10-11 00:09:40'),
(1312, 96, 112, 110, '2022-10-05', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Did homework and reviewed operations with fractions', '20', '2022-10-12 21:25:42', '2022-10-12 21:25:42'),
(1314, 34, 91, 88, '2022-10-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Prep for test: order of operations, absolute value, coordinate plane, multiplying variables with coefficients.', '79', '2022-10-13 00:01:42', '2022-10-13 00:01:42'),
(1315, 96, 115, 112, '2022-10-09', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Addition and subtraction word problems', '20', '2022-10-13 00:55:03', '2022-10-13 00:55:03'),
(1316, 96, 114, 112, '2022-10-09', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Long division and operations with fractions', '20', '2022-10-13 00:55:27', '2022-10-13 00:55:27'),
(1317, 82, 117, 99, '2022-10-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Solve worksheet-Precalculus', '50', '2022-10-13 04:48:13', '2022-10-13 04:48:13'),
(1318, 38, 111, 109, '2022-10-12', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I reviewed for his cumulative exam on transformations and symmetry.  I was surprised to see several problems requesting proofs and explanations about angle concepts (e.g., alternate interior, vertical, and bisectors). I personally did not remember discussing these ideas in prior sessions.  I encouraged Mason to make his best effort to keep current on what we should cover in our sessions so we can maximize our readiness for exams.  Mason continues to maintain a great work ethic and be extremely conscientious.', '50', '2022-10-13 15:19:06', '2022-10-13 15:19:06'),
(1319, 94, 45, 46, '2022-10-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'We reviewed question words, practiced using the word cual in a sentence with choosing pictures, went over the difference in question words with and without accent marks. We then reviewed his study guide from his class, with vocab words ranging from numbers to conversational questions and sentences. We then reviewed some recipes in Spanish. His homework is to make flashcards of his study guide material which I gave him last week but he forgot about.', '45', '2022-10-13 22:08:30', '2022-10-13 22:08:30'),
(1320, 60, 73, 67, '2022-10-12', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on two writing prompts and handwriting. Practiced skip counting.', '30', '2022-10-15 16:26:38', '2022-10-15 16:26:38'),
(1321, 60, 66, 67, '2022-10-12', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Practiced factorization and identifying prime and composite numbers.', '30', '2022-10-15 16:26:59', '2022-10-15 16:26:59'),
(1322, 60, 75, 72, '2022-10-13', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Completed school homework with addition and subtraction using a number line and decomposition. Completed a reading and answered analysis questions. Practiced multiplication.', '30', '2022-10-15 16:34:07', '2022-10-15 16:34:07'),
(1323, 60, 60, 62, '2022-10-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on quiz corrections for the last quiz. Started learning about slope and how it relates to ratios.', '30', '2022-10-15 16:35:31', '2022-10-15 16:35:31'),
(1324, 82, 117, 99, '2022-10-17', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Precalculus-Solved worksheet', '50', '2022-10-17 19:41:12', '2022-10-17 19:41:12'),
(1325, 96, 112, 110, '2022-10-18', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Homework and additive methods', '20', '2022-10-18 23:40:01', '2022-10-18 23:40:01'),
(1326, 34, 91, 88, '2022-10-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Rewriting repeated decimals as fractions, operations with negative fractions, categorizing numbers.', '79', '2022-10-20 00:24:43', '2022-10-20 00:24:43'),
(1327, 82, 117, 99, '2022-10-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Angular vs linear velocity-solved worksheet', '50', '2022-10-20 09:46:38', '2022-10-20 09:46:38'),
(1329, 38, 74, 71, '2022-10-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur returned with a vengeance, as after a move to a new house and starting a new school, he requested assistance with one our \"favorite \" topics: geometric rotations.  We both refreshed some significant concepts, and successfully completed the assignment. It is wonderful to be working with this young man again.  Welcome back Timur!', '50', '2022-10-21 14:10:02', '2022-10-21 14:10:02'),
(1330, 38, 111, 109, '2022-10-19', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason is putting in the effort to master some tricky concepts, including parallel lines, corresponding angles, and translations.  This young man will not give up, and his efforts are paying off and will continue to do so..  I am attempting to incorporate as many visual resources as possible to facilitate communication of the major ideas.  I am confident that Mason\'s diligence and commitment will reap a bountiful harvest!', '50', '2022-10-21 14:27:01', '2022-10-21 14:27:01'),
(1331, 38, 56, 57, '2022-10-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Ian\'s teacher does not hesitate to challenge the students.  Today, we were faced with a \"maximization of water flow\" problem given constraints on the size of the opening.  Ian and I were certainly challenged, but came up with what we are confident is a correct solution.  Ian had a hard day at school today, but remained dedicated to self advancement by being engaged in the session.  Ian is doing great!', '50', '2022-10-21 14:57:06', '2022-10-21 14:57:06'),
(1332, 96, 62, 64, '2022-10-20', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on homework (scale factors)', '20', '2022-10-21 16:07:03', '2022-10-21 16:07:03'),
(1333, 34, 45, 46, '2022-10-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Writing two-term expressions via pattern recognition in word problems. pre-cursor to functions.', '75', '2022-10-25 00:37:04', '2022-10-25 00:37:04'),
(1334, 60, 75, 72, '2022-10-20', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on reading and reading comprehension. Practiced adding and subtracting 3 and 4-digit numbers and rounding. Practiced quick addition and multiplication facts.', '30', '2022-10-25 13:46:03', '2022-10-25 13:46:03'),
(1335, 38, 118, 114, '2022-10-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was a pleasure to begin work with Michael, a bright young man with stellar character traits who has requested some support in filling in some gaps resulting from his advancement to an above level class.  Today, we worked on long division, with Michael demonstrating his conscientiousness and commitment to success.  We utilized worksheets and games. I look forward to working with Michael.', '50', '2022-10-25 15:09:09', '2022-10-25 15:09:09'),
(1336, 38, 111, 109, '2022-10-24', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I did a quick and comprehensive review of the material we have been covering over the past few weeks in preparation for an exam. Highlights included parallel lines, angles, congruence, and proofs, with my super student demonstrating that he has advanced significantly.  I am optimistic that the results will reflect that progress.  Mason continues to climb the learning curve!', '50', '2022-10-25 15:17:54', '2022-10-25 15:17:54'),
(1337, 82, 117, 99, '2022-10-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Precalculus-Trig Identities', '50', '2022-10-26 18:05:36', '2022-10-26 18:05:36'),
(1338, 34, 91, 88, '2022-10-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Adding and subtracting fractions and mixed numbers, with unlike denominators.', '79', '2022-10-27 00:01:24', '2022-10-27 00:01:24'),
(1339, 38, 118, 114, '2022-10-26', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Michael\'s exam in multiplication and division was delayed until tomorrow, so we spent our 30 minutes doing some additional review.  The session was very instructive, as we learned that Michael can significantly improve his performance, when he slows down, focuses, and checks his work.  I look forward to hearing of his his great results!', '50', '2022-10-27 16:31:37', '2022-11-01 14:39:01'),
(1340, 38, 74, 71, '2022-10-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur is expanding his mathematical horizons significantly these days, as he is covering algebraic and geometric proofs. Once we learned the definitions and properties, Timur was immediately proficient in applying them to the proofs assigned.  No matter how challenging the problem may be,  Timur keeps cools and finds a path to success!', '50', '2022-10-27 16:35:46', '2022-10-27 16:35:46'),
(1341, 38, 111, 109, '2022-10-26', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Mason may not have passed his recent quiz, our session revealed some causes we had not previously been aware of.  Mason admitted that he needs to take better advantage of me as a resource, by showing me his classwork and having  me provide supplemental explanations.  Mason is even able to prepare a study sheet that he can bring into the exam;  I knew nothing about that.  I am optimistic that with our new framework, we can elevate Mason to a more positive vantage point in his class.', '50', '2022-10-27 16:53:38', '2022-10-27 16:53:38'),
(1342, 38, 118, 114, '2022-10-20', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'It was Zachary\'s turn today, and what a pleasure it was to meet this young man. My newest super student is in second grade, and need a little support with fundamental math skills. Today\'s highlights included number line word problems, with Zach doing just fine. I look forward to working with Zach, who scored some extra points by liking my jokes!', '50', '2022-10-28 15:23:06', '2022-10-28 15:23:06'),
(1343, 94, 45, 46, '2022-10-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today we reviewed a packet of vocab from his class. We practiced the word \"ya\" which means already. It is a really tricky word because in Spanish it goes at the beginning or end of a sentence whereas in English we put \"already\" wherever we want it. It took him a little bit to catch on but then he was on a roll! It was fun seeing him get excited about it too once he got it. We also worked a little bit on ordering food. I want to do a whole lesson on that because in my humble opinion, that is one of the most useful things to know in Spanish.', '45', '2022-10-28 23:29:23', '2022-10-28 23:29:23'),
(1344, 60, 73, 67, '2022-10-26', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Worked on writing prompts and school addition homework. Talked about why adding by 5s makes the ones place alternate between two numbers. Practiced quick addition facts and repeated addition.', '30', '2022-10-29 03:49:47', '2022-10-29 03:49:47'),
(1345, 60, 66, 67, '2022-10-26', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Reviewed multiplication. Quick addition and subtraction review and a little bit of factoring Talked a little about geography and history.', '30', '2022-10-29 03:50:38', '2022-10-29 03:50:38'),
(1346, 60, 75, 72, '2022-10-27', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on school homework with intro to multiplication. Practiced quick addition, subtraction, and multiplication facts. Practiced adding and subtracting 3-4 digit numbers.  Completed a reading comprehension activity.', '30', '2022-10-29 04:27:47', '2022-10-29 04:27:47'),
(1347, 60, 60, 62, '2022-10-28', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Worked on organization!! Went through all assignments and made a game plan for reviewing for reading quiz retake.', '30', '2022-10-29 04:29:52', '2022-10-29 04:29:52'),
(1348, 96, 114, 112, '2022-10-28', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Operations with fractions', '20', '2022-10-29 13:41:07', '2022-10-29 13:41:07'),
(1349, 96, 115, 112, '2022-10-28', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Multiplications and sentence structures', '20', '2022-10-29 13:41:25', '2022-10-29 13:41:25'),
(1350, 96, 62, 64, '2022-10-27', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Scale factor and unit/rate conversion', '20', '2022-10-29 13:42:11', '2022-10-29 13:42:11'),
(1351, 96, 112, 110, '2022-10-25', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Addition and multiplication standard algorithm', '20', '2022-10-29 13:42:38', '2022-10-29 13:42:38'),
(1352, 115, 48, 49, '2022-11-01', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Leena and I talked about her current teachers and difficulties in the classroom so far, so that I could get a handle on where she is. We worked through her homework for the week with diagrams and process charts and planned to work more on dividing fractions the next time we meet.', '30', '2022-11-01 22:53:42', '2022-11-01 22:53:42'),
(1353, 34, 91, 88, '2022-11-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Last minute cancellation, Markus wanted to go to his mom\'s game.', '79', '2022-11-03 00:59:43', '2022-11-03 00:59:43'),
(1354, 38, 118, 114, '2022-11-02', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'Zachary and I tackled 3 digit subtraction today, with great results for my super student.  By zeroing in on some simple errors that Zach is prone to, we ensured that he will improve his performance and generate the results that he is capable of!   Great work Zachary!', '50', '2022-11-04 01:42:46', '2022-11-15 23:06:01'),
(1355, 38, 111, 109, '2022-11-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Mason and I focused on congruence and transformations in his challenging \"Cumulative Practice Problems\" review sheets.  Although it seems that Mason may be struggling, this young man remains as committed to success as ever, approaching each session with optimism and enthusiasm.  I am confident that his efforts will be rewarded.', '50', '2022-11-04 01:57:07', '2022-11-04 01:57:07'),
(1356, 38, 74, 71, '2022-11-02', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'It was all about triangle congruence proofs for Timur and me this evening. It will take some dedication to gain mastery, but Timur has never let me down. I am confident that he will put in the necessary effort and add these skills to his inventory.  Timur can do it!', '50', '2022-11-04 02:00:36', '2022-11-04 02:00:36'),
(1357, 38, 119, 114, '2022-11-03', NULL, '0:30', '0.5', 'I missed Michael for our scheduled session today.  I spoke with Mom, but my super student never appeared. I look forward to continuing working with this bright young man at our next session.', '50', '2022-11-04 14:35:06', '2022-11-04 14:35:06'),
(1358, 38, 56, 57, '2022-11-03', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Ian did not do as well as he would have liked on his recent test on parabolas and patterns, we took advantage of the opportunity he was given to rework the problems and hand in his work for extra points.  We made significant progress, but we were not able to finish.  if Mon wants another session before the work is due, i would be happy to accommodate her.  Keep pushing Ian. You can do this!', '50', '2022-11-04 14:40:36', '2022-11-04 14:40:36'),
