(1432, 38, 56, 57, '2022-12-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Although Ian\'s Mom reported that Ian has not been doing as well as we all would have liked, we did get feedback from the teacher about where to focus.  It seems that the quadratic equation with all of its associated applications has been a trouble spot for Ian, so we got to work on it right away.  It is my belief that if we put in a joint effort, things can turn around for Ian.', '50', '2022-12-15 17:59:33', '2022-12-15 17:59:33'),
(1433, 38, 74, 71, '2022-12-14', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Timur and I focused on points of concurrency of the triangle. He had covered two of them in class, which we reviewed. We then proceeded to learn two more, for which we applied the concepts to some problems as well.  Timur did a great job!', '50', '2022-12-15 18:01:54', '2022-12-15 18:01:54'),
(1434, 94, 45, 46, '2022-12-15', NULL, '1:00', '1', 'Today, We reinforced and practiced reflexive verbs. I had him use a stuffed animal because reflexive verbs are doing an action on one\'s self (ex. getting dressed, washing one\'s hands, brushing one\'s hair, etc.). I had him say what the stuffed animal was doing, and I used a rat stuffed animal as my example. It was fun and Brendon made progress in conjugating reflexive verbs!', '45', '2022-12-15 23:31:02', '2022-12-15 23:31:02'),
