(82, 'Murad', 'Khalaf', 'tutor', 'muradkhalaf@yahoo.com', '$2y$10$xI1qofJ4vWHb94XNiO1.mOIcb0z8Aujy9tsQEke1JLzcWtLZ4oDK.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Eastern Time', 'active', '443-788-0206', 'profile-1631115643-788865.jpeg', 'Hello, my name is Murad Khalaf, I have been teaching and tutoring math and physics for more than 15 years. I taught at Carroll Community College, Anne Arundel Community College and Frostburg State University.  I earned my post graduate degrees in electrical engineering from the University of Pittsburgh.  In Electrical Engineering, math and physics are applied in most courses, this is how I established a strong command in all math and physics disciplines .  I adopt my teaching style to the individual student’s needs and give them the challenge to build their confidence to overcome their difficulties, improve grades and go beyond and ahead of the course.', 'Subscribe', '524994145', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-09-06 06:25:07', '2024-10-14 20:47:30'),
